53 public:
54 JSCallReducerAssembler(JSGraph* jsgraph, Zone* zone, Node* node)
55 : JSGraphAssembler(jsgraph, zone, nullptr, kMarkLoopExits),
56 node_(node),
57 outermost_catch_scope_(CatchScope::Outermost(zone)),
58 catch_scope_(&outermost_catch_scope_) {
59 InitializeEffectControl(NodeProperties::GetEffectInput(node),
60 NodeProperties::GetControlInput(node));
61
62 // Finish initializing the outermost catch scope.
63 bool has_handler =
64 NodeProperties::IsExceptionalCall(node, &outermost_handler_);
65 outermost_catch_scope_.set_has_handler(has_handler);
66 outermost_catch_scope_.set_gasm(this);
67 }

92 // TODO(jgruber): Currently IfBuilder0 and IfBuilder1 are implemented as
93 // separate classes. If, in the future, we encounter additional use cases that
94 // return more than 1 value, we should merge these back into a single variadic
95 // implementation.
96 class IfBuilder0 final {
97 public:
98 IfBuilder0(JSGraphAssembler* gasm, TNode<Boolean> cond, bool negate_cond)
99 : gasm_(gasm),
100 cond_(cond),
101 negate_cond_(negate_cond),
102 initial_effect_(gasm->effect()),
103 initial_control_(gasm->control()) {}
104
105 IfBuilder0& ExpectTrue() {
106 DCHECK_EQ(hint_, BranchHint::kNone)((void) 0);
107 hint_ = BranchHint::kTrue;
108 return *this;
109 }
110 IfBuilder0& ExpectFalse() {
111 DCHECK_EQ(hint_, BranchHint::kNone)((void) 0);
112 hint_ = BranchHint::kFalse;
113 return *this;
114 }
115
116 IfBuilder0& Then(const VoidGenerator0& body) {
117 then_body_ = body;
118 return *this;
119 }
120 IfBuilder0& Else(const VoidGenerator0& body) {
121 else_body_ = body;
122 return *this;
123 }
124
125 ~IfBuilder0() {
126 // Ensure correct usage: effect/control must not have been modified while
127 // the IfBuilder0 instance is alive.
128 DCHECK_EQ(gasm_->effect(), initial_effect_)((void) 0);
129 DCHECK_EQ(gasm_->control(), initial_control_)((void) 0);
130
131 // Unlike IfBuilder1, this supports an empty then or else body. This is
132 // possible since the merge does not take any value inputs.
133 DCHECK(then_body_ || else_body_)((void) 0);
134
135 if (negate_cond_) std::swap(then_body_, else_body_);
136
137 auto if_true = (hint_ == BranchHint::kFalse) ? gasm_->MakeDeferredLabel()
138 : gasm_->MakeLabel();
139 auto if_false = (hint_ == BranchHint::kTrue) ? gasm_->MakeDeferredLabel()
140 : gasm_->MakeLabel();
141 auto merge = gasm_->MakeLabel();
142 gasm_->Branch(cond_, &if_true, &if_false);
143
144 gasm_->Bind(&if_true);
145 if (then_body_) then_body_();
146 gasm_->Goto(&merge);
147
148 gasm_->Bind(&if_false);
149 if (else_body_) else_body_();
150 gasm_->Goto(&merge);
151
152 gasm_->Bind(&merge);
153 }
154
155 private:
156 JSGraphAssembler* const gasm_;
157 const TNode<Boolean> cond_;
158 const bool negate_cond_;
159 const Effect initial_effect_;
160 const Control initial_control_;
161 BranchHint hint_ = BranchHint::kNone;
162 VoidGenerator0 then_body_;
163 VoidGenerator0 else_body_;
164
165 DISALLOW_COPY_AND_ASSIGN(IfBuilder0)IfBuilder0(const IfBuilder0&) = delete; IfBuilder0& operator
=(const IfBuilder0&) = delete;
166 };

171 template <typename T>
172 class IfBuilder1 {
173 using If1BodyFunction = std::function<TNode<T>()>;
174
175 public:
176 IfBuilder1(JSGraphAssembler* gasm, TNode<Boolean> cond)
177 : gasm_(gasm), cond_(cond) {}
178
179 V8_WARN_UNUSED_RESULT__attribute__((warn_unused_result)) IfBuilder1& ExpectTrue() {
180 DCHECK_EQ(hint_, BranchHint::kNone)((void) 0);
181 hint_ = BranchHint::kTrue;
182 return *this;
183 }
184
185 V8_WARN_UNUSED_RESULT__attribute__((warn_unused_result)) IfBuilder1& ExpectFalse() {
186 DCHECK_EQ(hint_, BranchHint::kNone)((void) 0);
187 hint_ = BranchHint::kFalse;
188 return *this;
189 }
190
191 V8_WARN_UNUSED_RESULT__attribute__((warn_unused_result)) IfBuilder1& Then(const If1BodyFunction& body) {
192 then_body_ = body;
193 return *this;
194 }
195 V8_WARN_UNUSED_RESULT__attribute__((warn_unused_result)) IfBuilder1& Else(const If1BodyFunction& body) {
196 else_body_ = body;
197 return *this;
198 }
199
200 V8_WARN_UNUSED_RESULT__attribute__((warn_unused_result)) TNode<T> Value() {
201 DCHECK(then_body_)((void) 0);
202 DCHECK(else_body_)((void) 0);
203 auto if_true = (hint_ == BranchHint::kFalse) ? gasm_->MakeDeferredLabel()
204 : gasm_->MakeLabel();
205 auto if_false = (hint_ == BranchHint::kTrue) ? gasm_->MakeDeferredLabel()
206 : gasm_->MakeLabel();
207 auto merge = gasm_->MakeLabel(kPhiRepresentation);
208 gasm_->Branch(cond_, &if_true, &if_false);
209
210 gasm_->Bind(&if_true);
211 TNode<T> then_result = then_body_();
212 gasm_->Goto(&merge, then_result);
213
214 gasm_->Bind(&if_false);
215 TNode<T> else_result = else_body_();
216 gasm_->Goto(&merge, else_result);
217
218 gasm_->Bind(&merge);
219 return merge.PhiAt<T>(0);
220 }
221
222 private:
223 static constexpr MachineRepresentation kPhiRepresentation =
224 MachineRepresentation::kTagged;
225
226 JSGraphAssembler* const gasm_;
227 const TNode<Boolean> cond_;
228 BranchHint hint_ = BranchHint::kNone;
229 If1BodyFunction then_body_;
230 If1BodyFunction else_body_;
231 };

276 void MaybeInsertMapChecks(MapInference* inference,
277 bool has_stability_dependency) {
278 // TODO(jgruber): Implement MapInference::InsertMapChecks in graph
279 // assembler.
280 if (!has_stability_dependency) {
281 Effect e = effect();
282 inference->InsertMapChecks(jsgraph(), &e, Control{control()}, feedback());
283 InitializeEffectControl(e, control());
284 }

287 // TODO(jgruber): Currently, it's the responsibility of the developer to note
288 // which operations may throw and appropriately wrap these in a call to
289 // MayThrow (see e.g. JSCall3 and CallRuntime2). A more methodical approach
290 // would be good.
291 TNode<Object> MayThrow(const NodeGenerator0& body) {
292 TNode<Object> result = body();
293
294 if (catch_scope()->has_handler()) {
295 // The IfException node is later merged into the outer graph.
296 // Note: AddNode is intentionally not called since effect and control
297 // should not be updated.
298 Node* if_exception =
299 graph()->NewNode(common()->IfException(), effect(), control());
300 catch_scope()->RegisterIfExceptionNode(if_exception);
301
302 // Control resumes here.
303 AddNode(graph()->NewNode(common()->IfSuccess(), control()));
304 }
305
306 return result;
307 }

309 // A catch scope represents a single catch handler. The handler can be
310 // custom catch logic within the reduction itself; or a catch handler in the
311 // outside graph into which the reduction will be integrated (in this case
312 // the scope is called 'outermost').
313 class CatchScope {
314 private:
315 // Only used to partially construct the outermost scope.
316 explicit CatchScope(Zone* zone) : if_exception_nodes_(zone) {}
317
318 // For all inner scopes.
319 CatchScope(Zone* zone, JSCallReducerAssembler* gasm)
320 : gasm_(gasm),
321 parent_(gasm->catch_scope_),
322 has_handler_(true),
323 if_exception_nodes_(zone) {
324 gasm_->catch_scope_ = this;
325 }
326
327 public:
328 ~CatchScope() { gasm_->catch_scope_ = parent_; }
329
330 static CatchScope Outermost(Zone* zone) { return CatchScope{zone}; }
331 static CatchScope Inner(Zone* zone, JSCallReducerAssembler* gasm) {
332 return {zone, gasm};
333 }
334
335 bool has_handler() const { return has_handler_; }
336 bool is_outermost() const { return parent_ == nullptr; }
337 CatchScope* parent() const { return parent_; }
338
339 // Should only be used to initialize the outermost scope (inner scopes
340 // always have a handler and are passed the gasm pointer at construction).
341 void set_has_handler(bool v) {
342 DCHECK(is_outermost())((void) 0);
343 has_handler_ = v;
344 }
345 void set_gasm(JSCallReducerAssembler* v) {
346 DCHECK(is_outermost())((void) 0);
347 gasm_ = v;
348 }
349
350 bool has_exceptional_control_flow() const {
351 return !if_exception_nodes_.empty();
352 }
353
354 void RegisterIfExceptionNode(Node* if_exception) {
355 DCHECK(has_handler())((void) 0);
356 if_exception_nodes_.push_back(if_exception);
357 }
358
359 void MergeExceptionalPaths(TNode<Object>* exception_out, Effect* effect_out,
360 Control* control_out) {
361 DCHECK(has_handler())((void) 0);
362 DCHECK(has_exceptional_control_flow())((void) 0);
363
364 const int size = static_cast<int>(if_exception_nodes_.size());
365
366 if (size == 1) {
367 // No merge needed.
368 Node* e = if_exception_nodes_.at(0);
369 *exception_out = TNode<Object>::UncheckedCast(e);
370 *effect_out = Effect(e);
371 *control_out = Control(e);
372 } else {
373 DCHECK_GT(size, 1)((void) 0);
374
375 Node* merge = gasm_->graph()->NewNode(gasm_->common()->Merge(size),
376 size, if_exception_nodes_.data());
377
378 // These phis additionally take {merge} as an input. Temporarily add
379 // it to the list.
380 if_exception_nodes_.push_back(merge);
381 const int size_with_merge =
382 static_cast<int>(if_exception_nodes_.size());
383
384 Node* ephi = gasm_->graph()->NewNode(gasm_->common()->EffectPhi(size),
385 size_with_merge,
386 if_exception_nodes_.data());
387 Node* phi = gasm_->graph()->NewNode(
388 gasm_->common()->Phi(MachineRepresentation::kTagged, size),
389 size_with_merge, if_exception_nodes_.data());
390 if_exception_nodes_.pop_back();
391
392 *exception_out = TNode<Object>::UncheckedCast(phi);
393 *effect_out = Effect(ephi);
394 *control_out = Control(merge);
395 }
396 }
397
398 private:
399 JSCallReducerAssembler* gasm_ = nullptr;
400 CatchScope* const parent_ = nullptr;
401 bool has_handler_ = false;
402 NodeVector if_exception_nodes_;
403 };

405 class TryCatchBuilder0 {
406 public:
407 using TryFunction = VoidGenerator0;
408 using CatchFunction = std::function<void(TNode<Object>)>;
409
410 TryCatchBuilder0(JSCallReducerAssembler* gasm, const TryFunction& try_body)
411 : gasm_(gasm), try_body_(try_body) {}
412
413 void Catch(const CatchFunction& catch_body) {
414 TNode<Object> handler_exception;
415 Effect handler_effect{nullptr};
416 Control handler_control{nullptr};
417
418 auto continuation = gasm_->MakeLabel();
419
420 // Try.
421 {
422 CatchScope catch_scope = CatchScope::Inner(gasm_->temp_zone(), gasm_);
423 try_body_();
424 gasm_->Goto(&continuation);
425
426 catch_scope.MergeExceptionalPaths(&handler_exception, &handler_effect,
427 &handler_control);
428 }
429
430 // Catch.
431 {
432 gasm_->InitializeEffectControl(handler_effect, handler_control);
433 catch_body(handler_exception);
434 gasm_->Goto(&continuation);
435 }
436
437 gasm_->Bind(&continuation);
438 }
439
440 private:
441 JSCallReducerAssembler* const gasm_;
442 const VoidGenerator0 try_body_;
443 };
444
445 TryCatchBuilder0 Try(const VoidGenerator0& try_body) {
446 return {this, try_body};
447 }

449 using ConditionFunction1 = std::function<TNode<Boolean>(TNode<Number>)>;
450 using StepFunction1 = std::function<TNode<Number>(TNode<Number>)>;
451 class ForBuilder0 {
452 using For0BodyFunction = std::function<void(TNode<Number>)>;
453
454 public:
455 ForBuilder0(JSGraphAssembler* gasm, TNode<Number> initial_value,
456 const ConditionFunction1& cond, const StepFunction1& step)
457 : gasm_(gasm),
458 initial_value_(initial_value),
459 cond_(cond),
460 step_(step) {}
461
462 void Do(const For0BodyFunction& body) {
463 auto loop_exit = gasm_->MakeLabel();
464
465 {
466 GraphAssembler::LoopScope<kPhiRepresentation> loop_scope(gasm_);
467
468 auto loop_header = loop_scope.loop_header_label();
469 auto loop_body = gasm_->MakeLabel();
470
471 gasm_->Goto(loop_header, initial_value_);
472
473 gasm_->Bind(loop_header);
474 TNode<Number> i = loop_header->PhiAt<Number>(0);
475
476 gasm_->BranchWithHint(cond_(i), &loop_body, &loop_exit,
477 BranchHint::kTrue);
478
479 gasm_->Bind(&loop_body);
480 body(i);
481 gasm_->Goto(loop_header, step_(i));
482 }
483
484 gasm_->Bind(&loop_exit);
485 }
486
487 private:
488 static constexpr MachineRepresentation kPhiRepresentation =
489 MachineRepresentation::kTagged;
490
491 JSGraphAssembler* const gasm_;
492 const TNode<Number> initial_value_;
493 const ConditionFunction1 cond_;
494 const StepFunction1 step_;
495 };

497 ForBuilder0 ForZeroUntil(TNode<Number> excluded_limit) {
498 TNode<Number> initial_value = ZeroConstant();
499 auto cond = [=](TNode<Number> i) {
500 return NumberLessThan(i, excluded_limit);
501 };
502 auto step = [=](TNode<Number> i) { return NumberAdd(i, OneConstant()); };
503 return {this, initial_value, cond, step};
504 }

506 ForBuilder0 Forever(TNode<Number> initial_value, const StepFunction1& step) {
507 return {this, initial_value, [=](TNode<Number>) { return TrueConstant(); },
508 step};
509 }

511 using For1BodyFunction = std::function<void(TNode<Number>, TNode<Object>*)>;
512 class ForBuilder1 {
513 public:
514 ForBuilder1(JSGraphAssembler* gasm, TNode<Number> initial_value,
515 const ConditionFunction1& cond, const StepFunction1& step,
516 TNode<Object> initial_arg0)
517 : gasm_(gasm),
518 initial_value_(initial_value),
519 cond_(cond),
520 step_(step),
521 initial_arg0_(initial_arg0) {}
522
523 V8_WARN_UNUSED_RESULT__attribute__((warn_unused_result)) ForBuilder1& Do(const For1BodyFunction& body) {
524 body_ = body;
525 return *this;
526 }
527
528 V8_WARN_UNUSED_RESULT__attribute__((warn_unused_result)) TNode<Object> Value() {
529 DCHECK(body_)((void) 0);
530 TNode<Object> arg0 = initial_arg0_;
531
532 auto loop_exit = gasm_->MakeDeferredLabel(kPhiRepresentation);
533
534 {
535 GraphAssembler::LoopScope<kPhiRepresentation, kPhiRepresentation>
536 loop_scope(gasm_);
537
538 auto loop_header = loop_scope.loop_header_label();
539 auto loop_body = gasm_->MakeDeferredLabel(kPhiRepresentation);
540
541 gasm_->Goto(loop_header, initial_value_, initial_arg0_);
542
543 gasm_->Bind(loop_header);
544 TNode<Number> i = loop_header->PhiAt<Number>(0);
545 arg0 = loop_header->PhiAt<Object>(1);
546
547 gasm_->BranchWithHint(cond_(i), &loop_body, &loop_exit,
548 BranchHint::kTrue, arg0);
549
550 gasm_->Bind(&loop_body);
551 body_(i, &arg0);
552 gasm_->Goto(loop_header, step_(i), arg0);
553 }
554
555 gasm_->Bind(&loop_exit);
556 return TNode<Object>::UncheckedCast(loop_exit.PhiAt<Object>(0));
557 }

559 void ValueIsUnused() { USE(Value())do { ::v8::base::Use unused_tmp_array_for_use_macro[]{Value()
}; (void)unused_tmp_array_for_use_macro; } while (false); }
560
561 private:
562 static constexpr MachineRepresentation kPhiRepresentation =
563 MachineRepresentation::kTagged;
564
565 JSGraphAssembler* const gasm_;
566 const TNode<Number> initial_value_;
567 const ConditionFunction1 cond_;
568 const StepFunction1 step_;
569 For1BodyFunction body_;
570 const TNode<Object> initial_arg0_;
571 };
572
573 ForBuilder1 For1(TNode<Number> initial_value, const ConditionFunction1& cond,
574 const StepFunction1& step, TNode<Object> initial_arg0) {
575 return {this, initial_value, cond, step, initial_arg0};
576 }
577
578 ForBuilder1 For1ZeroUntil(TNode<Number> excluded_limit,
579 TNode<Object> initial_arg0) {
580 TNode<Number> initial_value = ZeroConstant();
581 auto cond = [=](TNode<Number> i) {
582 return NumberLessThan(i, excluded_limit);
583 };
584 auto step = [=](TNode<Number> i) { return NumberAdd(i, OneConstant()); };
585 return {this, initial_value, cond, step, initial_arg0};
586 }
587
588 void ThrowIfNotCallable(TNode<Object> maybe_callable,
589 FrameState frame_state) {
590 IfNot(ObjectIsCallable(maybe_callable))
591 .Then(_ {
592 JSCallRuntime2(Runtime::kThrowTypeError,
593 NumberConstant(static_cast<double>(
594 MessageTemplate::kCalledNonCallable)),
595 maybe_callable, frame_state);
596 Unreachable(); // The runtime call throws unconditionally.
597 })
598 .ExpectTrue();
599 }
600
601 const FeedbackSource& feedback() const {
602 CallParameters const& p = CallParametersOf(node_ptr()->op());
603 return p.feedback();
604 }
605
606 int ArgumentCount() const { return JSCallNode{node_ptr()}.ArgumentCount(); }
607
608 TNode<Object> Argument(int index) const {
609 return TNode<Object>::UncheckedCast(JSCallNode{node_ptr()}.Argument(index));
610 }
611
612 template <typename T>
613 TNode<T> ArgumentAs(int index) const {
614 return TNode<T>::UncheckedCast(Argument(index));
615 }
616
617 TNode<Object> ArgumentOrNaN(int index) {
618 return TNode<Object>::UncheckedCast(
619 ArgumentCount() > index ? Argument(index) : NaNConstant());
620 }
621
622 TNode<Object> ArgumentOrUndefined(int index) {
623 return TNode<Object>::UncheckedCast(
624 ArgumentCount() > index ? Argument(index) : UndefinedConstant());
625 }
626
627 TNode<Number> ArgumentOrZero(int index) {
628 return TNode<Number>::UncheckedCast(
629 ArgumentCount() > index ? Argument(index) : ZeroConstant());
630 }
631
632 TNode<Context> ContextInput() const {
633 return TNode<Context>::UncheckedCast(
634 NodeProperties::GetContextInput(node_));
635 }
636
637 FrameState FrameStateInput() const {
638 return FrameState(NodeProperties::GetFrameStateInput(node_));
639 }
640
641 JSOperatorBuilder* javascript() const { return jsgraph()->javascript(); }

647 Node* outermost_handler_;
648 CatchScope* catch_scope_;
649 friend class CatchScope;

696 private:
697 // Returns {index,value}. Assumes that the map has not changed, but possibly
698 // the length and backing store.
699 std::pair<TNode<Number>, TNode<Object>> SafeLoadElement(ElementsKind kind,
700 TNode<JSArray> o,
701 TNode<Number> index) {
702 // Make sure that the access is still in bounds, since the callback could
703 // have changed the array's size.
704 TNode<Number> length = LoadJSArrayLength(o, kind);
705 index = CheckBounds(index, length);
706
707 // Reload the elements pointer before calling the callback, since the
708 // previous callback might have resized the array causing the elements
709 // buffer to be re-allocated.
710 TNode<HeapObject> elements =
711 LoadField<HeapObject>(AccessBuilder::ForJSObjectElements(), o);
712 TNode<Object> value = LoadElement<Object>(
713 AccessBuilder::ForFixedArrayElement(kind, LoadSensitivity::kCritical),
714 elements, index);
715 return std::make_pair(index, value);
716 }
717
718 template <typename... Vars>
719 TNode<Object> MaybeSkipHole(
720 TNode<Object> o, ElementsKind kind,
721 GraphAssemblerLabel<sizeof...(Vars)>* continue_label,
722 TNode<Vars>... vars) {
723 if (!IsHoleyElementsKind(kind)) return o;
724
725 std::array<MachineRepresentation, sizeof...(Vars)> reps = {
726 MachineRepresentationOf<Vars>::value...};
727 auto if_not_hole =
728 MakeLabel<sizeof...(Vars)>(reps, GraphAssemblerLabelType::kNonDeferred);
729 BranchWithHint(HoleCheck(kind, o), continue_label, &if_not_hole,
730 BranchHint::kFalse, vars...);
731
732 // The contract is that we don't leak "the hole" into "user JavaScript",
733 // so we must rename the {element} here to explicitly exclude "the hole"
734 // from the type of {element}.
735 Bind(&if_not_hole);
736 return TypeGuardNonInternal(o);
737 }
738
739 TNode<Smi> LoadJSArrayLength(TNode<JSArray> array, ElementsKind kind) {
740 return LoadField<Smi>(AccessBuilder::ForJSArrayLength(kind), array);
741 }
742 void StoreJSArrayLength(TNode<JSArray> array, TNode<Number> value,
743 ElementsKind kind) {
744 StoreField(AccessBuilder::ForJSArrayLength(kind), array, value);
745 }
746 void StoreFixedArrayBaseElement(TNode<FixedArrayBase> o, TNode<Number> index,
747 TNode<Object> v, ElementsKind kind) {
748 StoreElement(AccessBuilder::ForFixedArrayElement(kind), o, index, v);
749 }
750
751 TNode<FixedArrayBase> LoadElements(TNode<JSObject> o) {
752 return LoadField<FixedArrayBase>(AccessBuilder::ForJSObjectElements(), o);
753 }
754 TNode<Smi> LoadFixedArrayBaseLength(TNode<FixedArrayBase> o) {
755 return LoadField<Smi>(AccessBuilder::ForFixedArrayLength(), o);
756 }
757
758 TNode<Boolean> HoleCheck(ElementsKind kind, TNode<Object> v) {
759 return IsDoubleElementsKind(kind)
760 ? NumberIsFloat64Hole(TNode<Number>::UncheckedCast(v))
761 : IsTheHole(v);
762 }
763
764 TNode<Number> CheckFloat64Hole(TNode<Number> value,
765 CheckFloat64HoleMode mode) {
766 return AddNode<Number>(
767 graph()->NewNode(simplified()->CheckFloat64Hole(mode, feedback()),
768 value, effect(), control()));
769 }
770
771 // May deopt for holey double elements.
772 TNode<Object> TryConvertHoleToUndefined(TNode<Object> value,
773 ElementsKind kind) {
774 DCHECK(IsHoleyElementsKind(kind))((void) 0);
775 if (kind == HOLEY_DOUBLE_ELEMENTS) {
776 // TODO(7409): avoid deopt if not all uses of value are truncated.
777 TNode<Number> number = TNode<Number>::UncheckedCast(value);
778 return CheckFloat64Hole(number, CheckFloat64HoleMode::kAllowReturnHole);
779 }
780
781 return ConvertTaggedHoleToUndefined(value);
782 }
783};

876class FastApiCallReducerAssembler : public JSCallReducerAssembler {
877 public:
878 FastApiCallReducerAssembler(
879 JSGraph* jsgraph, Zone* zone, Node* node, Address c_function,
880 const CFunctionInfo* c_signature,
881 const FunctionTemplateInfoRef function_template_info, Node* receiver,
882 Node* holder, const SharedFunctionInfoRef shared, Node* target,
883 const int arity, Node* effect)
884 : JSCallReducerAssembler(jsgraph, zone, node),
885 c_function_(c_function),
886 c_signature_(c_signature),
887 function_template_info_(function_template_info),
888 receiver_(receiver),
889 holder_(holder),
890 shared_(shared),
891 target_(target),
892 arity_(arity) {
893 DCHECK_EQ(IrOpcode::kJSCall, node->opcode())((void) 0);
894 DCHECK_NE(c_function_, kNullAddress)((void) 0);
895 CHECK_NOT_NULL(c_signature_)do { if ((__builtin_expect(!!(!((c_signature_) != nullptr)), 0
))) { V8_Fatal("Check failed: %s.", "(c_signature_) != nullptr"
); } } while (false);
896 InitializeEffectControl(effect, NodeProperties::GetControlInput(node));
897 }
898
899 TNode<Object> ReduceFastApiCall() {
900 JSCallNode n(node_ptr());
901 // C arguments include the receiver at index 0. Thus C index 1 corresponds
902 // to the JS argument 0, etc.
903 const int c_argument_count =
904 static_cast<int>(c_signature_->ArgumentCount());
905 CHECK_GE(c_argument_count, kReceiver)do { bool _cmp = ::v8::base::CmpGEImpl< typename ::v8::base
::pass_value_or_ref<decltype(c_argument_count)>::type, typename
::v8::base::pass_value_or_ref<decltype(kReceiver)>::type
>((c_argument_count), (kReceiver)); do { if ((__builtin_expect
(!!(!(_cmp)), 0))) { V8_Fatal("Check failed: %s.", "c_argument_count"
" " ">=" " " "kReceiver"); } } while (false); } while (false
);
906
907 int cursor = 0;
908 base::SmallVector<Node*, kInlineSize> inputs(c_argument_count + arity_ +
909 kExtraInputsCount);
910 inputs[cursor++] = ExternalConstant(ExternalReference::Create(c_function_));
911
912 inputs[cursor++] = n.receiver();
913
914 // TODO(turbofan): Consider refactoring CFunctionInfo to distinguish
915 // between receiver and arguments, simplifying this (and related) spots.
916 int js_args_count = c_argument_count - kReceiver;
917 for (int i = 0; i < js_args_count; ++i) {
918 if (i < n.ArgumentCount()) {
919 inputs[cursor++] = n.Argument(i);
920 } else {
921 inputs[cursor++] = UndefinedConstant();
922 }
923 }
924
925 // Here we add the arguments for the slow call, which will be
926 // reconstructed at a later phase. Those are effectively the same
927 // arguments as for the fast call, but we want to have them as
928 // separate inputs, so that SimplifiedLowering can provide the best
929 // possible UseInfos for each of them. The inputs to FastApiCall
930 // look like:
931 // [fast callee, receiver, ... C arguments,
932 // call code, external constant for function, argc, call handler info data,
933 // holder, receiver, ... JS arguments, context, new frame state]
934 CallHandlerInfoRef call_handler_info = *function_template_info_.call_code();
935 Callable call_api_callback = CodeFactory::CallApiCallback(isolate());
936 CallInterfaceDescriptor cid = call_api_callback.descriptor();
937 CallDescriptor* call_descriptor =
938 Linkage::GetStubCallDescriptor(graph()->zone(), cid, arity_ + kReceiver,
939 CallDescriptor::kNeedsFrameState);
940 ApiFunction api_function(call_handler_info.callback());
941 ExternalReference function_reference = ExternalReference::Create(
942 &api_function, ExternalReference::DIRECT_API_CALL);
943
944 Node* continuation_frame_state =
945 CreateGenericLazyDeoptContinuationFrameState(
946 jsgraph(), shared_, target_, ContextInput(), receiver_,
947 FrameStateInput());
948
949 inputs[cursor++] = HeapConstant(call_api_callback.code());
950 inputs[cursor++] = ExternalConstant(function_reference);
951 inputs[cursor++] = NumberConstant(arity_);
952 inputs[cursor++] = Constant(call_handler_info.data());
953 inputs[cursor++] = holder_;
954 inputs[cursor++] = receiver_;
955 for (int i = 0; i < arity_; ++i) {
956 inputs[cursor++] = Argument(i);
957 }
958 inputs[cursor++] = ContextInput();
959 inputs[cursor++] = continuation_frame_state;
960 inputs[cursor++] = effect();
961 inputs[cursor++] = control();
962
963 DCHECK_EQ(cursor, c_argument_count + arity_ + kExtraInputsCount)((void) 0);
964
965 return FastApiCall(call_descriptor, inputs.begin(), inputs.size());
966 }
967
968 private:
969 static constexpr int kTarget = 1;
970 static constexpr int kEffectAndControl = 2;
971 static constexpr int kContextAndFrameState = 2;
972 static constexpr int kCallCodeDataAndArgc = 3;
973 static constexpr int kHolder = 1, kReceiver = 1;
974 static constexpr int kExtraInputsCount =
975 kTarget * 2 + kEffectAndControl + kContextAndFrameState +
976 kCallCodeDataAndArgc + kHolder + kReceiver;
977 static constexpr int kInlineSize = 12;
978
979 TNode<Object> FastApiCall(CallDescriptor* descriptor, Node** inputs,
980 size_t inputs_size) {
981 return AddNode<Object>(graph()->NewNode(
982 simplified()->FastApiCall(c_signature_, feedback(), descriptor),
983 static_cast<int>(inputs_size), inputs));
984 }
985
986 const Address c_function_;
987 const CFunctionInfo* const c_signature_;
988 const FunctionTemplateInfoRef function_template_info_;
989 Node* const receiver_;
990 Node* const holder_;
991 const SharedFunctionInfoRef shared_;
992 Node* const target_;
993 const int arity_;
994};

1099TNode<JSArray> JSCallReducerAssembler::AllocateEmptyJSArray(
1100 ElementsKind kind, const NativeContextRef& native_context) {
1101 // TODO(jgruber): Port AllocationBuilder to JSGraphAssembler.
1102 MapRef map = native_context.GetInitialJSArrayMap(kind);
1103
1104 AllocationBuilder ab(jsgraph(), effect(), control());
1105 ab.Allocate(map.instance_size(), AllocationType::kYoung, Type::Array());
1106 ab.Store(AccessBuilder::ForMap(), map);
1107 Node* empty_fixed_array = jsgraph()->EmptyFixedArrayConstant();
1108 ab.Store(AccessBuilder::ForJSObjectPropertiesOrHashKnownPointer(),
1109 empty_fixed_array);
1110 ab.Store(AccessBuilder::ForJSObjectElements(), empty_fixed_array);
1111 ab.Store(AccessBuilder::ForJSArrayLength(kind), jsgraph()->ZeroConstant());
1112 for (int i = 0; i < map.GetInObjectProperties(); ++i) {
1113 ab.Store(AccessBuilder::ForJSObjectInObjectProperty(map, i),
1114 jsgraph()->UndefinedConstant());
1115 }
1116 Node* result = ab.Finish();
1117 InitializeEffectControl(result, control());
1118 return TNode<JSArray>::UncheckedCast(result);
1119}

1121TNode<Object> JSCallReducerAssembler::ReduceMathUnary(const Operator* op) {
1122 TNode<Object> input = Argument(0);
1123 TNode<Number> input_as_number = SpeculativeToNumber(input);
1124 return TNode<Object>::UncheckedCast(graph()->NewNode(op, input_as_number));
1125}
1126
1127TNode<Object> JSCallReducerAssembler::ReduceMathBinary(const Operator* op) {
1128 TNode<Object> left = Argument(0);
1129 TNode<Object> right = ArgumentOrNaN(1);
1130 TNode<Number> left_number = SpeculativeToNumber(left);
1131 TNode<Number> right_number = SpeculativeToNumber(right);
1132 return TNode<Object>::UncheckedCast(
1133 graph()->NewNode(op, left_number, right_number));
1134}
1135
1136TNode<String> JSCallReducerAssembler::ReduceStringPrototypeSubstring() {
1137 TNode<Object> receiver = ReceiverInput();
1138 TNode<Object> start = Argument(0);
1139 TNode<Object> end = ArgumentOrUndefined(1);
1140
1141 TNode<String> receiver_string = CheckString(receiver);
1142 TNode<Number> start_smi = CheckSmi(start);
1143
1144 TNode<Number> length = StringLength(receiver_string);
1145
1146 TNode<Number> end_smi = SelectIf<Number>(IsUndefined(end))
1147 .Then(_ { return length; })
1148 .Else(_ { return CheckSmi(end); })
1149 .ExpectFalse()
1150 .Value();
1151
1152 TNode<Number> zero = TNode<Number>::UncheckedCast(ZeroConstant());
1153 TNode<Number> finalStart = NumberMin(NumberMax(start_smi, zero), length);
1154 TNode<Number> finalEnd = NumberMin(NumberMax(end_smi, zero), length);
1155 TNode<Number> from = NumberMin(finalStart, finalEnd);
1156 TNode<Number> to = NumberMax(finalStart, finalEnd);
1157
1158 return StringSubstring(receiver_string, from, to);
1159}
1160
1161TNode<String> JSCallReducerAssembler::ReduceStringPrototypeSlice() {
1162 TNode<Object> receiver = ReceiverInput();
1163 TNode<Object> start = Argument(0);
1164 TNode<Object> end = ArgumentOrUndefined(1);
1165
1166 TNode<String> receiver_string = CheckString(receiver);
1167 TNode<Number> start_smi = CheckSmi(start);
1168
1169 TNode<Number> length = StringLength(receiver_string);
1170
1171 TNode<Number> end_smi = SelectIf<Number>(IsUndefined(end))
1172 .Then(_ { return length; })
1173 .Else(_ { return CheckSmi(end); })
1174 .ExpectFalse()
1175 .Value();
1176
1177 TNode<Number> zero = TNode<Number>::UncheckedCast(ZeroConstant());
1178 TNode<Number> from_untyped =
1179 SelectIf<Number>(NumberLessThan(start_smi, zero))
1180 .Then(_ { return NumberMax(NumberAdd(length, start_smi), zero); })
1181 .Else(_ { return NumberMin(start_smi, length); })
1182 .ExpectFalse()
1183 .Value();
1184 // {from} is always in non-negative Smi range, but our typer cannot figure
1185 // that out yet.
1186 TNode<Smi> from = TypeGuardUnsignedSmall(from_untyped);
1187
1188 TNode<Number> to_untyped =
1189 SelectIf<Number>(NumberLessThan(end_smi, zero))
1190 .Then(_ { return NumberMax(NumberAdd(length, end_smi), zero); })
1191 .Else(_ { return NumberMin(end_smi, length); })
1192 .ExpectFalse()
1193 .Value();
1194 // {to} is always in non-negative Smi range, but our typer cannot figure that
1195 // out yet.
1196 TNode<Smi> to = TypeGuardUnsignedSmall(to_untyped);
1197
1198 return SelectIf<String>(NumberLessThan(from, to))
1199 .Then(_ { return StringSubstring(receiver_string, from, to); })
1200 .Else(_ { return EmptyStringConstant(); })
1201 .ExpectTrue()
1202 .Value();
1203}

1213 TNode<Object> receiver;

1215 TNode<Object> this_arg;
1216 TNode<Object> original_length;
1217};
1218
1219FrameState ForEachLoopLazyFrameState(const ForEachFrameStateParams& params,
1220 TNode<Object> k) {
1221 Builtins::Name builtin = Builtins::kArrayForEachLoopLazyDeoptContinuation;
1222 Node* checkpoint_params[] = {params.receiver, params.callback,
1223 params.this_arg, k, params.original_length};
1224 return CreateJavaScriptBuiltinContinuationFrameState(
1225 params.jsgraph, params.shared, builtin, params.target, params.context,
1226 checkpoint_params, arraysize(checkpoint_params)(sizeof(ArraySizeHelper(checkpoint_params))), params.outer_frame_state,
1227 ContinuationFrameStateMode::LAZY);
1228}

1230FrameState ForEachLoopEagerFrameState(const ForEachFrameStateParams& params,
1231 TNode<Object> k) {
1232 Builtins::Name builtin = Builtins::kArrayForEachLoopEagerDeoptContinuation;
1233 Node* checkpoint_params[] = {params.receiver, params.callback,
1234 params.this_arg, k, params.original_length};
1235 return CreateJavaScriptBuiltinContinuationFrameState(
1236 params.jsgraph, params.shared, builtin, params.target, params.context,
1237 checkpoint_params, arraysize(checkpoint_params)(sizeof(ArraySizeHelper(checkpoint_params))), params.outer_frame_state,
1238 ContinuationFrameStateMode::EAGER);

1242
1243TNode<Object>
1244IteratingArrayBuiltinReducerAssembler::ReduceArrayPrototypeForEach(
1245 MapInference* inference, const bool has_stability_dependency,
1246 ElementsKind kind, const SharedFunctionInfoRef& shared) {
1247 FrameState outer_frame_state = FrameStateInput();
1248 TNode<Context> context = ContextInput();
1249 TNode<Object> target = TargetInput();
1250 TNode<JSArray> receiver = ReceiverInputAs<JSArray>();
1251 TNode<Object> fncallback = ArgumentOrUndefined(0);
1252 TNode<Object> this_arg = ArgumentOrUndefined(1);
1253
1254 TNode<Number> original_length = LoadJSArrayLength(receiver, kind);
1255
1256 ForEachFrameStateParams frame_state_params{
1257 jsgraph(), shared, context, target, outer_frame_state,
1258 receiver, fncallback, this_arg, original_length};
1259
1260 ThrowIfNotCallable(fncallback, ForEachLoopLazyFrameState(frame_state_params,
1261 ZeroConstant()));
1262
1263 ForZeroUntil(original_length).Do([&](TNode<Number> k) {
1264 Checkpoint(ForEachLoopEagerFrameState(frame_state_params, k));
1265
1266 // Deopt if the map has changed during the iteration.
1267 MaybeInsertMapChecks(inference, has_stability_dependency);
1268
1269 TNode<Object> element;
1270 std::tie(k, element) = SafeLoadElement(kind, receiver, k);
1271
1272 auto continue_label = MakeLabel();
1273 element = MaybeSkipHole(element, kind, &continue_label);
1274
1275 TNode<Number> next_k = NumberAdd(k, OneConstant());
1276 JSCall3(fncallback, this_arg, element, k, receiver,
1277 ForEachLoopLazyFrameState(frame_state_params, next_k));
1278
1279 Goto(&continue_label);
1280 Bind(&continue_label);
1281 });
1282
1283 return UndefinedConstant();
1284}

1360
1361TNode<Object> IteratingArrayBuiltinReducerAssembler::ReduceArrayPrototypeReduce(
1362 MapInference* inference, const bool has_stability_dependency,
1363 ElementsKind kind, ArrayReduceDirection direction,
1364 const SharedFunctionInfoRef& shared) {
1365 FrameState outer_frame_state = FrameStateInput();
1366 TNode<Context> context = ContextInput();
1367 TNode<Object> target = TargetInput();
1368 TNode<JSArray> receiver = ReceiverInputAs<JSArray>();
1369 TNode<Object> fncallback = ArgumentOrUndefined(0);
1370
1371 ReduceFrameStateParams frame_state_params{
1372 jsgraph(), shared, direction, context, target, outer_frame_state};
1373
1374 TNode<Number> original_length = LoadJSArrayLength(receiver, kind);
1375
1376 // Set up variable behavior depending on the reduction kind (left/right).
1377 TNode<Number> k;
1378 StepFunction1 step;
1379 ConditionFunction1 cond;
1380 TNode<Number> zero = ZeroConstant();
1381 TNode<Number> one = OneConstant();
1382 if (direction == ArrayReduceDirection::kLeft) {
1383 k = zero;
1384 step = [&](TNode<Number> i) { return NumberAdd(i, one); };
1385 cond = [&](TNode<Number> i) { return NumberLessThan(i, original_length); };
1386 } else {
1387 k = NumberSubtract(original_length, one);
1388 step = [&](TNode<Number> i) { return NumberSubtract(i, one); };
1389 cond = [&](TNode<Number> i) { return NumberLessThanOrEqual(zero, i); };
1390 }
1391
1392 ThrowIfNotCallable(
1393 fncallback, ReducePreLoopLazyFrameState(frame_state_params, receiver,
1394 fncallback, k, original_length));
1395
1396 // Set initial accumulator value.
1397 TNode<Object> accumulator;
1398 if (ArgumentCount() > 1) {
1399 accumulator = Argument(1); // Initial value specified by the user.
1400 } else {
1401 // The initial value was not specified by the user. In this case, the first
1402 // (or last in the case of reduceRight) non-holey value of the array is
1403 // used. Loop until we find it. If not found, trigger a deopt.
1404 // TODO(jgruber): The deopt does not seem necessary. Instead we could simply
1405 // throw the TypeError here from optimized code.
1406 auto found_initial_element = MakeLabel(MachineRepresentation::kTagged,
1407 MachineRepresentation::kTagged);
1408 Forever(k, step).Do([&](TNode<Number> k) {
1409 Checkpoint(ReducePreLoopEagerFrameState(frame_state_params, receiver,
1410 fncallback, original_length));
1411 CheckIf(cond(k), DeoptimizeReason::kNoInitialElement);
1412
1413 TNode<Object> element;
1414 std::tie(k, element) = SafeLoadElement(kind, receiver, k);
1415
1416 auto continue_label = MakeLabel();
1417 GotoIf(HoleCheck(kind, element), &continue_label);
1418 Goto(&found_initial_element, k, TypeGuardNonInternal(element));
1419
1420 Bind(&continue_label);
1421 });
1422 Unreachable(); // The loop is exited either by deopt or a jump to below.
1423 InitializeEffectControl(nullptr, nullptr);
1424
1425 // TODO(jgruber): This manual fiddling with blocks could be avoided by
1426 // implementing a `break` mechanic for loop builders.
1427 Bind(&found_initial_element);
1428 k = step(found_initial_element.PhiAt<Number>(0));
1429 accumulator = found_initial_element.PhiAt<Object>(1);
1430 }
1431
1432 TNode<Object> result =
1433 For1(k, cond, step, accumulator)
1434 .Do([&](TNode<Number> k, TNode<Object>* accumulator) {
1435 Checkpoint(ReduceLoopEagerFrameState(frame_state_params, receiver,
1436 fncallback, k, original_length,
1437 *accumulator));
1438
1439 // Deopt if the map has changed during the iteration.
1440 MaybeInsertMapChecks(inference, has_stability_dependency);
1441
1442 TNode<Object> element;
1443 std::tie(k, element) = SafeLoadElement(kind, receiver, k);
1444
1445 auto continue_label = MakeLabel(MachineRepresentation::kTagged);
1446 element =
1447 MaybeSkipHole(element, kind, &continue_label, *accumulator);
1448
1449 TNode<Number> next_k = step(k);
1450 TNode<Object> next_accumulator = JSCall4(
1451 fncallback, UndefinedConstant(), *accumulator, element, k,
1452 receiver,
1453 ReduceLoopLazyFrameState(frame_state_params, receiver,
1454 fncallback, next_k, original_length));
1455 Goto(&continue_label, next_accumulator);
1456
1457 Bind(&continue_label);
1458 *accumulator = continue_label.PhiAt<Object>(0);
1459 })
1460 .Value();
1461
1462 return result;
1463}
1464

1516
1517TNode<JSArray> IteratingArrayBuiltinReducerAssembler::ReduceArrayPrototypeMap(
1518 MapInference* inference, const bool has_stability_dependency,
1519 ElementsKind kind, const SharedFunctionInfoRef& shared,
1520 const NativeContextRef& native_context) {
1521 FrameState outer_frame_state = FrameStateInput();
1522 TNode<Context> context = ContextInput();
1523 TNode<Object> target = TargetInput();
1524 TNode<JSArray> receiver = ReceiverInputAs<JSArray>();
1525 TNode<Object> fncallback = ArgumentOrUndefined(0);
1526 TNode<Object> this_arg = ArgumentOrUndefined(1);
1527
1528 TNode<Number> original_length = LoadJSArrayLength(receiver, kind);
1529
1530 // If the array length >= kMaxFastArrayLength, then CreateArray
1531 // will create a dictionary. We should deopt in this case, and make sure
1532 // not to attempt inlining again.
1533 original_length = CheckBounds(original_length,
1534 NumberConstant(JSArray::kMaxFastArrayLength));
1535
1536 // Even though {JSCreateArray} is not marked as {kNoThrow}, we can elide the
1537 // exceptional projections because it cannot throw with the given
1538 // parameters.
1539 TNode<Object> array_ctor =
1540 Constant(native_context.GetInitialJSArrayMap(kind).GetConstructor());
1541
1542 MapFrameStateParams frame_state_params{
1543 jsgraph(), shared, context, target, outer_frame_state,
1544 receiver, fncallback, this_arg, {} /* TBD */, original_length};
1545
1546 TNode<JSArray> a =
1547 CreateArrayNoThrow(array_ctor, original_length,
1548 MapPreLoopLazyFrameState(frame_state_params));
1549 frame_state_params.a = a;
1550
1551 ThrowIfNotCallable(fncallback,
1552 MapLoopLazyFrameState(frame_state_params, ZeroConstant()));
1553
1554 ForZeroUntil(original_length).Do([&](TNode<Number> k) {
1555 Checkpoint(MapLoopEagerFrameState(frame_state_params, k));
1556 MaybeInsertMapChecks(inference, has_stability_dependency);
1557
1558 TNode<Object> element;
1559 std::tie(k, element) = SafeLoadElement(kind, receiver, k);
1560
1561 auto continue_label = MakeLabel();
1562 element = MaybeSkipHole(element, kind, &continue_label);
1563
1564 TNode<Object> v = JSCall3(fncallback, this_arg, element, k, receiver,
1565 MapLoopLazyFrameState(frame_state_params, k));
1566
1567 // The array {a} should be HOLEY_SMI_ELEMENTS because we'd only come into
1568 // this loop if the input array length is non-zero, and "new Array({x > 0})"
1569 // always produces a HOLEY array.
1570 MapRef holey_double_map =
1571 native_context.GetInitialJSArrayMap(HOLEY_DOUBLE_ELEMENTS);
1572 MapRef holey_map = native_context.GetInitialJSArrayMap(HOLEY_ELEMENTS);
1573 TransitionAndStoreElement(holey_double_map, holey_map, a, k, v);
1574
1575 Goto(&continue_label);
1576 Bind(&continue_label);
1577 });
1578
1579 return a;
1580}
1581

1598 TNode<Number> k, TNode<Number> to,

1600 Node* checkpoint_params[] = {params.receiver,
1601 params.callback,

1616 const FilterFrameStateParams& params, TNode<Number> k, TNode<Number> to,

1618 // Note that we are intentionally reusing the
1619 // Builtins::kArrayFilterLoopLazyDeoptContinuation as an *eager* entry point
1620 // in this case. This is safe, because re-evaluating a [ToBoolean] coercion is
1621 // safe.

1623 params.callback,
1624 params.this_arg,
1625 params.a,
1626 k,
1627 params.original_length,
1628 element,
1629 to,
1630 callback_value};
1631 return CreateJavaScriptBuiltinContinuationFrameState(
1632 params.jsgraph, params.shared,
1633 Builtins::kArrayFilterLoopLazyDeoptContinuation, params.target,
1634 params.context, checkpoint_params, arraysize(checkpoint_params)(sizeof(ArraySizeHelper(checkpoint_params))),
1635 params.outer_frame_state, ContinuationFrameStateMode::EAGER);
1636}

1641 params.callback,
1642 params.this_arg,
1643 params.a,
1644 k,
1645 params.original_length,
1646 to};
1647 return CreateJavaScriptBuiltinContinuationFrameState(
1648 params.jsgraph, params.shared,
1649 Builtins::kArrayFilterLoopEagerDeoptContinuation, params.target,

1651 params.outer_frame_state, ContinuationFrameStateMode::EAGER);

1655
1656TNode<JSArray>
1657IteratingArrayBuiltinReducerAssembler::ReduceArrayPrototypeFilter(
1658 MapInference* inference, const bool has_stability_dependency,
1659 ElementsKind kind, const SharedFunctionInfoRef& shared,
1660 const NativeContextRef& native_context) {
1661 FrameState outer_frame_state = FrameStateInput();
1662 TNode<Context> context = ContextInput();
1663 TNode<Object> target = TargetInput();
1664 TNode<JSArray> receiver = ReceiverInputAs<JSArray>();
1665 TNode<Object> fncallback = ArgumentOrUndefined(0);
1666 TNode<Object> this_arg = ArgumentOrUndefined(1);
1667
1668 // The output array is packed (filter doesn't visit holes).
1669 const ElementsKind packed_kind = GetPackedElementsKind(kind);
1670 TNode<JSArray> a = AllocateEmptyJSArray(packed_kind, native_context);
1671
1672 TNode<Number> original_length = LoadJSArrayLength(receiver, kind);
1673
1674 FilterFrameStateParams frame_state_params{
1675 jsgraph(), shared, context, target, outer_frame_state,
1676 receiver, fncallback, this_arg, a, original_length};
1677
1678 // This frame state doesn't ever call the deopt continuation, it's only
1679 // necessary to specify a continuation in order to handle the exceptional
1680 // case. We don't have all the values available to completely fill out
1681 // the checkpoint parameters yet, but that's okay because it'll never be
1682 // called.
1683 TNode<Number> zero = ZeroConstant();
1684 ThrowIfNotCallable(fncallback, FilterLoopLazyFrameState(frame_state_params,
1685 zero, zero, zero));
1686
1687 TNode<Number> initial_a_length = zero;
1688 For1ZeroUntil(original_length, initial_a_length)
1689 .Do([&](TNode<Number> k, TNode<Object>* a_length_object) {
1690 TNode<Number> a_length = TNode<Number>::UncheckedCast(*a_length_object);
1691 Checkpoint(FilterLoopEagerFrameState(frame_state_params, k, a_length));
1692 MaybeInsertMapChecks(inference, has_stability_dependency);
1693
1694 TNode<Object> element;
1695 std::tie(k, element) = SafeLoadElement(kind, receiver, k);
1696
1697 auto continue_label = MakeLabel(MachineRepresentation::kTaggedSigned);
1698 element = MaybeSkipHole(element, kind, &continue_label, a_length);
1699
1700 TNode<Object> v = JSCall3(
1701 fncallback, this_arg, element, k, receiver,
1702 FilterLoopLazyFrameState(frame_state_params, k, a_length, element));
1703
1704 // We need an eager frame state for right after the callback function
1705 // returned, just in case an attempt to grow the output array fails.
1706 Checkpoint(FilterLoopEagerPostCallbackFrameState(frame_state_params, k,
1707 a_length, element, v));
1708
1709 GotoIfNot(ToBoolean(v), &continue_label, a_length);
1710
1711 // Since the callback returned a trueish value, store the element in a.
1712 {
1713 TNode<Number> a_length1 = TypeGuardFixedArrayLength(a_length);
1714 TNode<FixedArrayBase> elements = LoadElements(a);
1715 elements = MaybeGrowFastElements(kind, FeedbackSource{}, a, elements,
1716 a_length1,
1717 LoadFixedArrayBaseLength(elements));
1718
1719 TNode<Number> new_a_length = NumberInc(a_length1);
1720 StoreJSArrayLength(a, new_a_length, kind);
1721 StoreFixedArrayBaseElement(elements, a_length1, element, kind);
1722
1723 Goto(&continue_label, new_a_length);
1724 }
1725
1726 Bind(&continue_label);
1727 *a_length_object =
1728 TNode<Object>::UncheckedCast(continue_label.PhiAt(0));
1729 })
1730 .ValueIsUnused();
1731
1732 return a;
1733}

1794
1795TNode<Object> IteratingArrayBuiltinReducerAssembler::ReduceArrayPrototypeFind(
1796 MapInference* inference, const bool has_stability_dependency,
1797 ElementsKind kind, const SharedFunctionInfoRef& shared,
1798 const NativeContextRef& native_context, ArrayFindVariant variant) {
1799 FrameState outer_frame_state = FrameStateInput();
1800 TNode<Context> context = ContextInput();
1801 TNode<Object> target = TargetInput();
1802 TNode<JSArray> receiver = ReceiverInputAs<JSArray>();
1803 TNode<Object> fncallback = ArgumentOrUndefined(0);
1804 TNode<Object> this_arg = ArgumentOrUndefined(1);
1805
1806 TNode<Number> original_length = LoadJSArrayLength(receiver, kind);
1807
1808 FindFrameStateParams frame_state_params{
1809 jsgraph(), shared, context, target, outer_frame_state,
1810 receiver, fncallback, this_arg, original_length};
1811
1812 ThrowIfNotCallable(
1813 fncallback,
1814 FindLoopLazyFrameState(frame_state_params, ZeroConstant(), variant));
1815
1816 const bool is_find_variant = (variant == ArrayFindVariant::kFind);
1817 auto out = MakeLabel(MachineRepresentation::kTagged);
1818
1819 ForZeroUntil(original_length).Do([&](TNode<Number> k) {
1820 Checkpoint(FindLoopEagerFrameState(frame_state_params, k, variant));
1821 MaybeInsertMapChecks(inference, has_stability_dependency);
1822
1823 TNode<Object> element;
1824 std::tie(k, element) = SafeLoadElement(kind, receiver, k);
1825
1826 if (IsHoleyElementsKind(kind)) {
1827 element = TryConvertHoleToUndefined(element, kind);
1828 }
1829
1830 TNode<Object> if_found_value = is_find_variant ? element : k;
1831 TNode<Number> next_k = NumberInc(k);
1832
1833 // The callback result states whether the desired element was found.
1834 TNode<Object> v =
1835 JSCall3(fncallback, this_arg, element, k, receiver,
1836 FindLoopAfterCallbackLazyFrameState(frame_state_params, next_k,
1837 if_found_value, variant));
1838
1839 GotoIf(ToBoolean(v), &out, if_found_value);
1840 });
1841
1842 // If the loop completed, the element was not found.
1843 TNode<Object> if_not_found_value =
1844 is_find_variant ? TNode<Object>::UncheckedCast(UndefinedConstant())
1845 : TNode<Object>::UncheckedCast(MinusOneConstant());
1846 Goto(&out, if_not_found_value);
1847
1848 Bind(&out);
1849 return out.PhiAt<Object>(0);
1850}

1896TNode<Boolean>
1897IteratingArrayBuiltinReducerAssembler::ReduceArrayPrototypeEverySome(
1898 MapInference* inference, const bool has_stability_dependency,
1899 ElementsKind kind, const SharedFunctionInfoRef& shared,
1900 const NativeContextRef& native_context, ArrayEverySomeVariant variant) {
1901 FrameState outer_frame_state = FrameStateInput();
1902 TNode<Context> context = ContextInput();
1903 TNode<Object> target = TargetInput();
1904 TNode<JSArray> receiver = ReceiverInputAs<JSArray>();
1905 TNode<Object> fncallback = ArgumentOrUndefined(0);
1906 TNode<Object> this_arg = ArgumentOrUndefined(1);
1907
1908 TNode<Number> original_length = LoadJSArrayLength(receiver, kind);
1909
1910 EverySomeFrameStateParams frame_state_params{
1911 jsgraph(), shared, context, target, outer_frame_state,
1912 receiver, fncallback, this_arg, original_length};
1913
1914 ThrowIfNotCallable(
1915 fncallback,
1916 EverySomeLoopLazyFrameState(frame_state_params, ZeroConstant(), variant));
1917
1918 auto out = MakeLabel(MachineRepresentation::kTagged);
1919
1920 ForZeroUntil(original_length).Do([&](TNode<Number> k) {
1921 Checkpoint(EverySomeLoopEagerFrameState(frame_state_params, k, variant));
1922 MaybeInsertMapChecks(inference, has_stability_dependency);
1923
1924 TNode<Object> element;
1925 std::tie(k, element) = SafeLoadElement(kind, receiver, k);
1926
1927 auto continue_label = MakeLabel();
1928 element = MaybeSkipHole(element, kind, &continue_label);
1929
1930 TNode<Object> v =
1931 JSCall3(fncallback, this_arg, element, k, receiver,
1932 EverySomeLoopLazyFrameState(frame_state_params, k, variant));
1933
1934 if (variant == ArrayEverySomeVariant::kEvery) {
1935 GotoIfNot(ToBoolean(v), &out, FalseConstant());
1936 } else {
1937 DCHECK_EQ(variant, ArrayEverySomeVariant::kSome)((void) 0);
1938 GotoIf(ToBoolean(v), &out, TrueConstant());
1939 }
1940 Goto(&continue_label);
1941 Bind(&continue_label);
1942 });
1943
1944 Goto(&out, (variant == ArrayEverySomeVariant::kEvery) ? TrueConstant()
1945 : FalseConstant());
1946
1947 Bind(&out);
1948 return out.PhiAt<Boolean>(0);
1949}

1951namespace {
1952
1953Callable GetCallableForArrayIndexOfIncludes(ArrayIndexOfIncludesVariant variant,
1954 ElementsKind elements_kind,
1955 Isolate* isolate) {
1956 if (variant == ArrayIndexOfIncludesVariant::kIndexOf) {
1957 switch (elements_kind) {
1958 case PACKED_SMI_ELEMENTS:
1959 case HOLEY_SMI_ELEMENTS:
1960 case PACKED_ELEMENTS:
1961 case HOLEY_ELEMENTS:
1962 return Builtins::CallableFor(isolate,
1963 Builtins::kArrayIndexOfSmiOrObject);
1964 case PACKED_DOUBLE_ELEMENTS:
1965 return Builtins::CallableFor(isolate,
1966 Builtins::kArrayIndexOfPackedDoubles);
1967 default:
1968 DCHECK_EQ(HOLEY_DOUBLE_ELEMENTS, elements_kind)((void) 0);
1969 return Builtins::CallableFor(isolate,
1970 Builtins::kArrayIndexOfHoleyDoubles);
1971 }
1972 } else {
1973 DCHECK_EQ(variant, ArrayIndexOfIncludesVariant::kIncludes)((void) 0);
1974 switch (elements_kind) {
1975 case PACKED_SMI_ELEMENTS:
1976 case HOLEY_SMI_ELEMENTS:
1977 case PACKED_ELEMENTS:
1978 case HOLEY_ELEMENTS:
1979 return Builtins::CallableFor(isolate,
1980 Builtins::kArrayIncludesSmiOrObject);
1981 case PACKED_DOUBLE_ELEMENTS:
1982 return Builtins::CallableFor(isolate,
1983 Builtins::kArrayIncludesPackedDoubles);
1984 default:
1985 DCHECK_EQ(HOLEY_DOUBLE_ELEMENTS, elements_kind)((void) 0);
1986 return Builtins::CallableFor(isolate,
1987 Builtins::kArrayIncludesHoleyDoubles);
1988 }
1989 }
1990 UNREACHABLE()V8_Fatal("unreachable code");
1991}
1992
1993} // namespace
1994
1995TNode<Object>
1996IteratingArrayBuiltinReducerAssembler::ReduceArrayPrototypeIndexOfIncludes(
1997 ElementsKind kind, ArrayIndexOfIncludesVariant variant) {
1998 TNode<Context> context = ContextInput();
1999 TNode<JSArray> receiver = ReceiverInputAs<JSArray>();
2000 TNode<Object> search_element = ArgumentOrUndefined(0);
2001 TNode<Object> from_index = ArgumentOrZero(1);
2002
2003 // TODO(jgruber): This currently only reduces to a stub call. Create a full
2004 // reduction (similar to other higher-order array builtins) instead of
2005 // lowering to a builtin call. E.g. Array.p.every and Array.p.some have almost
2006 // identical functionality.
2007
2008 TNode<Number> length = LoadJSArrayLength(receiver, kind);
2009 TNode<FixedArrayBase> elements = LoadElements(receiver);
2010
2011 const bool have_from_index = ArgumentCount() > 1;
2012 if (have_from_index) {
2013 TNode<Smi> from_index_smi = CheckSmi(from_index);
2014
2015 // If the index is negative, it means the offset from the end and
2016 // therefore needs to be added to the length. If the result is still
2017 // negative, it needs to be clamped to 0.
2018 TNode<Boolean> cond = NumberLessThan(from_index_smi, ZeroConstant());
2019 from_index = SelectIf<Number>(cond)
2020 .Then(_ {
2021 return NumberMax(NumberAdd(length, from_index_smi),
2022 ZeroConstant());
2023 })
2024 .Else(_ { return from_index_smi; })
2025 .ExpectFalse()
2026 .Value();
2027 }
2028
2029 return Call4(GetCallableForArrayIndexOfIncludes(variant, kind, isolate()),
2030 context, elements, search_element, length, from_index);
2031}

2035struct PromiseCtorFrameStateParams {
2036 JSGraph* jsgraph;
2037 SharedFunctionInfoRef shared;
2038 Node* node_ptr;
2039 TNode<Context> context;
2040 TNode<Object> target;
2041 FrameState outer_frame_state;
2042};
2043
2044// Remnant of old-style JSCallReducer code. Could be ported to graph assembler,
2045// but probably not worth the effort.
2046FrameState CreateArtificialFrameState(Node* node, Node* outer_frame_state,
2047 int parameter_count, BailoutId bailout_id,
2048 FrameStateType frame_state_type,
2049 const SharedFunctionInfoRef& shared,
2050 Node* context,
2051 CommonOperatorBuilder* common,
2052 Graph* graph) {
2053 const FrameStateFunctionInfo* state_info =
2054 common->CreateFrameStateFunctionInfo(
2055 frame_state_type, parameter_count + 1, 0, shared.object());
2056
2057 const Operator* op = common->FrameState(
2058 bailout_id, OutputFrameStateCombine::Ignore(), state_info);
2059 const Operator* op0 = common->StateValues(0, SparseInputMask::Dense());
2060 Node* node0 = graph->NewNode(op0);
2061
2062 static constexpr int kTargetInputIndex = 0;
2063 static constexpr int kReceiverInputIndex = 1;
2064 const int parameter_count_with_receiver = parameter_count + 1;
2065 std::vector<Node*> params;
2066 params.reserve(parameter_count_with_receiver);
2067 for (int i = 0; i < parameter_count_with_receiver; i++) {
2068 params.push_back(node->InputAt(kReceiverInputIndex + i));
2069 }
2070 const Operator* op_param = common->StateValues(
2071 static_cast<int>(params.size()), SparseInputMask::Dense());
2072 Node* params_node = graph->NewNode(op_param, static_cast<int>(params.size()),
2073 &params.front());
2074 DCHECK(context)((void) 0);
2075 return FrameState(graph->NewNode(op, params_node, node0, node0, context,
2076 node->InputAt(kTargetInputIndex),
2077 outer_frame_state));
2078}
2079
2080FrameState PromiseConstructorFrameState(
2081 const PromiseCtorFrameStateParams& params, CommonOperatorBuilder* common,
2082 Graph* graph) {
2083 DCHECK_EQ(1, params.shared.internal_formal_parameter_count())((void) 0);
2084 return CreateArtificialFrameState(
2085 params.node_ptr, params.outer_frame_state, 1,
2086 BailoutId::ConstructStubInvoke(), FrameStateType::kConstructStub,
2087 params.shared, params.context, common, graph);
2088}
2089
2090FrameState PromiseConstructorLazyFrameState(
2091 const PromiseCtorFrameStateParams& params,
2092 FrameState constructor_frame_state) {
2093 // The deopt continuation of this frame state is never called; the frame state
2094 // is only necessary to obtain the right stack trace.
2095 JSGraph* jsgraph = params.jsgraph;
2096 Node* checkpoint_params[] = {
2097 jsgraph->UndefinedConstant(), /* receiver */
2098 jsgraph->UndefinedConstant(), /* promise */
2099 jsgraph->UndefinedConstant(), /* reject function */
2100 jsgraph->TheHoleConstant() /* exception */
2101 };
2102 return CreateJavaScriptBuiltinContinuationFrameState(
2103 jsgraph, params.shared,
2104 Builtins::kPromiseConstructorLazyDeoptContinuation, params.target,
2105 params.context, checkpoint_params, arraysize(checkpoint_params)(sizeof(ArraySizeHelper(checkpoint_params))),
2106 constructor_frame_state, ContinuationFrameStateMode::LAZY);
2107}
2108
2109FrameState PromiseConstructorLazyWithCatchFrameState(
2110 const PromiseCtorFrameStateParams& params,
2111 FrameState constructor_frame_state, TNode<JSPromise> promise,
2112 TNode<JSFunction> reject) {
2113 // This continuation just returns the created promise and takes care of
2114 // exceptions thrown by the executor.
2115 Node* checkpoint_params[] = {
2116 params.jsgraph->UndefinedConstant(), /* receiver */
2117 promise, reject};
2118 return CreateJavaScriptBuiltinContinuationFrameState(
2119 params.jsgraph, params.shared,
2120 Builtins::kPromiseConstructorLazyDeoptContinuation, params.target,
2121 params.context, checkpoint_params, arraysize(checkpoint_params)(sizeof(ArraySizeHelper(checkpoint_params))),
2122 constructor_frame_state, ContinuationFrameStateMode::LAZY_WITH_CATCH);
2123}

2126
2127TNode<Object> PromiseBuiltinReducerAssembler::ReducePromiseConstructor(
2128 const NativeContextRef& native_context) {
2129 DCHECK_GE(ConstructArity(), 1)((void) 0);
2130
2131 JSConstructNode n(node_ptr());
2132 FrameState outer_frame_state = FrameStateInput();
2133 TNode<Context> context = ContextInput();
2134 TNode<Object> target = TargetInput();
2135 TNode<Object> executor = n.Argument(0);
2136 DCHECK_EQ(target, NewTargetInput())((void) 0);
2137
2138 SharedFunctionInfoRef promise_shared =
2139 native_context.promise_function().shared();
2140
2141 PromiseCtorFrameStateParams frame_state_params{jsgraph(), promise_shared,
2142 node_ptr(), context,
2143 target, outer_frame_state};
2144
2145 // Insert a construct stub frame into the chain of frame states. This will
2146 // reconstruct the proper frame when deoptimizing within the constructor.
2147 // For the frame state, we only provide the executor parameter, even if more
2148 // arguments were passed. This is not observable from JS.
2149 FrameState constructor_frame_state =
2150 PromiseConstructorFrameState(frame_state_params, common(), graph());
2151
2152 ThrowIfNotCallable(executor,
2153 PromiseConstructorLazyFrameState(frame_state_params,
2154 constructor_frame_state));
2155
2156 TNode<JSPromise> promise = CreatePromise(context);
2157
2158 // 8. CreatePromiseResolvingFunctions
2159 // Allocate a promise context for the closures below.
2160 TNode<Context> promise_context = CreateFunctionContext(
2161 native_context, context, PromiseBuiltins::kPromiseContextLength);
2162 StoreContextSlot(promise_context, PromiseBuiltins::kPromiseSlot, promise);
2163 StoreContextSlot(promise_context, PromiseBuiltins::kAlreadyResolvedSlot,
2164 FalseConstant());
2165 StoreContextSlot(promise_context, PromiseBuiltins::kDebugEventSlot,
2166 TrueConstant());
2167
2168 // Allocate closures for the resolve and reject cases.
2169 SharedFunctionInfoRef resolve_sfi(
2170 broker_, broker_->isolate()
2171 ->factory()
2172 ->promise_capability_default_resolve_shared_fun());
2173 TNode<JSFunction> resolve =
2174 CreateClosureFromBuiltinSharedFunctionInfo(resolve_sfi, promise_context);
2175
2176 SharedFunctionInfoRef reject_sfi(
2177 broker_, broker_->isolate()
2178 ->factory()
2179 ->promise_capability_default_reject_shared_fun());
2180 TNode<JSFunction> reject =
2181 CreateClosureFromBuiltinSharedFunctionInfo(reject_sfi, promise_context);
2182
2183 FrameState lazy_with_catch_frame_state =
2184 PromiseConstructorLazyWithCatchFrameState(
2185 frame_state_params, constructor_frame_state, promise, reject);
2186
2187 // 9. Call executor with both resolving functions.
2188 // 10a. Call reject if the call to executor threw.
2189 Try(_ {
2190 CallPromiseExecutor(executor, resolve, reject, lazy_with_catch_frame_state);
2191 }).Catch([&](TNode<Object> exception) {
2192 CallPromiseReject(reject, exception, lazy_with_catch_frame_state);
2193 });
2194
2195 return promise;
2196}

2199
2200bool JSCallReducer::should_disallow_heap_access() const {
2201 return broker_->is_concurrent_inlining();
2202}
2203
2204Reduction JSCallReducer::ReplaceWithSubgraph(JSCallReducerAssembler* gasm,
2205 Node* subgraph) {
2206 // TODO(jgruber): Consider a less fiddly way of integrating the new subgraph
2207 // into the outer graph. For instance, the subgraph could be created in
2208 // complete isolation, and then plugged into the outer graph in one go.
2209 // Instead of manually tracking IfException nodes, we could iterate the
2210 // subgraph.
2211
2212 // Replace the Call node with the newly-produced subgraph.
2213 ReplaceWithValue(gasm->node_ptr(), subgraph, gasm->effect(), gasm->control());
2214
2215 // Wire exception edges contained in the newly-produced subgraph into the
2216 // outer graph.
2217 auto catch_scope = gasm->catch_scope();
2218 DCHECK(catch_scope->is_outermost())((void) 0);
2219
2220 if (catch_scope->has_handler() &&
2221 catch_scope->has_exceptional_control_flow()) {
2222 TNode<Object> handler_exception;
2223 Effect handler_effect{nullptr};
2224 Control handler_control{nullptr};
2225 gasm->catch_scope()->MergeExceptionalPaths(
2226 &handler_exception, &handler_effect, &handler_control);
2227
2228 ReplaceWithValue(gasm->outermost_handler(), handler_exception,
2229 handler_effect, handler_control);
2230 }
2231
2232 return Replace(subgraph);
2233}
2234
2235Reduction JSCallReducer::ReduceMathUnary(Node* node, const Operator* op) {
2236 JSCallNode n(node);
2237 CallParameters const& p = n.Parameters();
2238 if (p.speculation_mode() == SpeculationMode::kDisallowSpeculation) {
2239 return NoChange();
2240 }
2241 if (n.ArgumentCount() < 1) {
2242 Node* value = jsgraph()->NaNConstant();
2243 ReplaceWithValue(node, value);
2244 return Replace(value);
2245 }
2246
2247 JSCallReducerAssembler a(jsgraph(), temp_zone(), node);
2248 Node* subgraph = a.ReduceMathUnary(op);
2249 return ReplaceWithSubgraph(&a, subgraph);
2250}
2251
2252Reduction JSCallReducer::ReduceMathBinary(Node* node, const Operator* op) {
2253 JSCallNode n(node);
2254 CallParameters const& p = n.Parameters();
2255 if (p.speculation_mode() == SpeculationMode::kDisallowSpeculation) {
2256 return NoChange();
2257 }
2258 if (n.ArgumentCount() < 1) {
2259 Node* value = jsgraph()->NaNConstant();
2260 ReplaceWithValue(node, value);
2261 return Replace(value);
2262 }
2263
2264 JSCallReducerAssembler a(jsgraph(), temp_zone(), node);
2265 Node* subgraph = a.ReduceMathBinary(op);
2266 return ReplaceWithSubgraph(&a, subgraph);
2267}
