2269// ES6 section 20.2.2.19 Math.imul ( x, y )
2270Reduction JSCallReducer::ReduceMathImul(Node* node) {
2271 JSCallNode n(node);
2272 CallParameters const& p = n.Parameters();
2273 if (p.speculation_mode() == SpeculationMode::kDisallowSpeculation) {
2274 return NoChange();
2275 }
2276 if (n.ArgumentCount() < 1) {
2277 Node* value = jsgraph()->ZeroConstant();
2278 ReplaceWithValue(node, value);
2279 return Replace(value);
2280 }
2281 Node* left = n.Argument(0);
2282 Node* right = n.ArgumentOr(1, jsgraph()->ZeroConstant());
2283 Effect effect = n.effect();
2284 Control control = n.control();
2285
2286 left = effect =
2287 graph()->NewNode(simplified()->SpeculativeToNumber(
2288 NumberOperationHint::kNumberOrOddball, p.feedback()),
2289 left, effect, control);
2290 right = effect =
2291 graph()->NewNode(simplified()->SpeculativeToNumber(
2292 NumberOperationHint::kNumberOrOddball, p.feedback()),
2293 right, effect, control);
2294 left = graph()->NewNode(simplified()->NumberToUint32(), left);
2295 right = graph()->NewNode(simplified()->NumberToUint32(), right);
2296 Node* value = graph()->NewNode(simplified()->NumberImul(), left, right);
2297 ReplaceWithValue(node, value, effect);
2298 return Replace(value);
2299}
2300
2301// ES6 section 20.2.2.11 Math.clz32 ( x )
2302Reduction JSCallReducer::ReduceMathClz32(Node* node) {
2303 JSCallNode n(node);
2304 CallParameters const& p = n.Parameters();
2305 if (p.speculation_mode() == SpeculationMode::kDisallowSpeculation) {
2306 return NoChange();
2307 }
2308 if (n.ArgumentCount() < 1) {
2309 Node* value = jsgraph()->Constant(32);
2310 ReplaceWithValue(node, value);
2311 return Replace(value);
2312 }
2313 Node* input = n.Argument(0);
2314 Effect effect = n.effect();
2315 Control control = n.control();
2316
2317 input = effect =
2318 graph()->NewNode(simplified()->SpeculativeToNumber(
2319 NumberOperationHint::kNumberOrOddball, p.feedback()),
2320 input, effect, control);
2321 input = graph()->NewNode(simplified()->NumberToUint32(), input);
2322 Node* value = graph()->NewNode(simplified()->NumberClz32(), input);
2323 ReplaceWithValue(node, value, effect);
2324 return Replace(value);
2325}
2326
2327// ES6 section 20.2.2.24 Math.max ( value1, value2, ...values )
2328// ES6 section 20.2.2.25 Math.min ( value1, value2, ...values )
2329Reduction JSCallReducer::ReduceMathMinMax(Node* node, const Operator* op,
2330 Node* empty_value) {
2331 JSCallNode n(node);
2332 CallParameters const& p = n.Parameters();
2333 if (p.speculation_mode() == SpeculationMode::kDisallowSpeculation) {
2334 return NoChange();
2335 }
2336 if (n.ArgumentCount() < 1) {
2337 ReplaceWithValue(node, empty_value);
2338 return Replace(empty_value);
2339 }
2340 Node* effect = NodeProperties::GetEffectInput(node);
2341 Node* control = NodeProperties::GetControlInput(node);
2342
2343 Node* value = effect =
2344 graph()->NewNode(simplified()->SpeculativeToNumber(
2345 NumberOperationHint::kNumberOrOddball, p.feedback()),
2346 n.Argument(0), effect, control);
2347 for (int i = 1; i < n.ArgumentCount(); i++) {
2348 Node* input = effect = graph()->NewNode(
2349 simplified()->SpeculativeToNumber(NumberOperationHint::kNumberOrOddball,
2350 p.feedback()),
2351 n.Argument(i), effect, control);
2352 value = graph()->NewNode(op, value, input);
2353 }
2354
2355 ReplaceWithValue(node, value, effect);
2356 return Replace(value);
2357}
2358
2359Reduction JSCallReducer::Reduce(Node* node) {
2360 DisallowHeapAccessIf disallow_heap_access(should_disallow_heap_access());
2361
2362 switch (node->opcode()) {
2363 case IrOpcode::kJSConstruct:
2364 return ReduceJSConstruct(node);
2365 case IrOpcode::kJSConstructWithArrayLike:
2366 return ReduceJSConstructWithArrayLike(node);
2367 case IrOpcode::kJSConstructWithSpread:
2368 return ReduceJSConstructWithSpread(node);
2369 case IrOpcode::kJSCall:
2370 return ReduceJSCall(node);
2371 case IrOpcode::kJSCallWithArrayLike:
2372 return ReduceJSCallWithArrayLike(node);
2373 case IrOpcode::kJSCallWithSpread:
2374 return ReduceJSCallWithSpread(node);
2375 default:
2376 break;
2377 }
2378 return NoChange();
2379}
2380
2381void JSCallReducer::Finalize() {
2382 // TODO(turbofan): This is not the best solution; ideally we would be able
2383 // to teach the GraphReducer about arbitrary dependencies between different
2384 // nodes, even if they don't show up in the use list of the other node.
2385 std::set<Node*> const waitlist = std::move(waitlist_);
2386 for (Node* node : waitlist) {
2387 if (!node->IsDead()) {
2388 Reduction const reduction = Reduce(node);
2389 if (reduction.Changed()) {
2390 Node* replacement = reduction.replacement();
2391 if (replacement != node) {
2392 Replace(node, replacement);
2393 }
2394 }
2395 }
2396 }
2397}
2398
2399// ES6 section 22.1.1 The Array Constructor
2400Reduction JSCallReducer::ReduceArrayConstructor(Node* node) {
2401 DisallowHeapAccessIf disallow_heap_access(should_disallow_heap_access());
2402
2403 JSCallNode n(node);
2404 Node* target = n.target();
2405 CallParameters const& p = n.Parameters();
2406
2407 // Turn the {node} into a {JSCreateArray} call.
2408 size_t const arity = p.arity_without_implicit_args();
2409 node->RemoveInput(n.FeedbackVectorIndex());
2410 NodeProperties::ReplaceValueInput(node, target, 0);
2411 NodeProperties::ReplaceValueInput(node, target, 1);
2412 NodeProperties::ChangeOp(
2413 node, javascript()->CreateArray(arity, MaybeHandle<AllocationSite>()));
2414 return Changed(node);
2415}
2416
2417// ES6 section 19.3.1.1 Boolean ( value )
2418Reduction JSCallReducer::ReduceBooleanConstructor(Node* node) {
2419 // Replace the {node} with a proper {ToBoolean} operator.
2420 JSCallNode n(node);
2421 Node* value = n.ArgumentOrUndefined(0, jsgraph());
2422 value = graph()->NewNode(simplified()->ToBoolean(), value);
2423 ReplaceWithValue(node, value);
2424 return Replace(value);
2425}
2426
2427// ES section #sec-object-constructor
2428Reduction JSCallReducer::ReduceObjectConstructor(Node* node) {
2429 JSCallNode n(node);
2430 if (n.ArgumentCount() < 1) return NoChange();
2431 Node* value = n.Argument(0);
2432 Effect effect = n.effect();
2433
2434 // We can fold away the Object(x) call if |x| is definitely not a primitive.
2435 if (NodeProperties::CanBePrimitive(broker(), value, effect)) {
2436 if (!NodeProperties::CanBeNullOrUndefined(broker(), value, effect)) {
2437 // Turn the {node} into a {JSToObject} call if we know that
2438 // the {value} cannot be null or undefined.
2439 NodeProperties::ReplaceValueInputs(node, value);
2440 NodeProperties::ChangeOp(node, javascript()->ToObject());
2441 return Changed(node);
2442 }
2443 } else {
2444 ReplaceWithValue(node, value);
2445 return Replace(value);
2446 }
2447 return NoChange();
2448}
2449
2450// ES6 section 19.2.3.1 Function.prototype.apply ( thisArg, argArray )
2451Reduction JSCallReducer::ReduceFunctionPrototypeApply(Node* node) {
2452 DisallowHeapAccessIf no_heap_access(should_disallow_heap_access());
2453
2454 JSCallNode n(node);
2455 CallParameters const& p = n.Parameters();
2456 int arity = p.arity_without_implicit_args();
2457 ConvertReceiverMode convert_mode = ConvertReceiverMode::kAny;
2458 if (arity == 0) {
2459 // Neither thisArg nor argArray was provided.
2460 convert_mode = ConvertReceiverMode::kNullOrUndefined;
2461 node->ReplaceInput(n.TargetIndex(), n.receiver());
2462 node->ReplaceInput(n.ReceiverIndex(), jsgraph()->UndefinedConstant());
2463 } else if (arity == 1) {
2464 // The argArray was not provided, just remove the {target}.
2465 node->RemoveInput(n.TargetIndex());
2466 --arity;
2467 } else {
2468 Node* target = n.receiver();
2469 Node* this_argument = n.Argument(0);
2470 Node* arguments_list = n.Argument(1);
2471 Node* context = n.context();
2472 FrameState frame_state = n.frame_state();
2473 Effect effect = n.effect();
2474 Control control = n.control();
2475
2476 // If {arguments_list} cannot be null or undefined, we don't need
2477 // to expand this {node} to control-flow.
2478 if (!NodeProperties::CanBeNullOrUndefined(broker(), arguments_list,
2479 effect)) {
2480 // Massage the value inputs appropriately.
2481 node->ReplaceInput(n.TargetIndex(), target);
2482 node->ReplaceInput(n.ReceiverIndex(), this_argument);
2483 node->ReplaceInput(n.ArgumentIndex(0), arguments_list);
2484 while (arity-- > 1) node->RemoveInput(n.ArgumentIndex(1));
2485
2486 // Morph the {node} to a {JSCallWithArrayLike}.
2487 NodeProperties::ChangeOp(
2488 node, javascript()->CallWithArrayLike(
2489 p.frequency(), p.feedback(), p.speculation_mode(),
2490 CallFeedbackRelation::kUnrelated));
2491 return Changed(node).FollowedBy(ReduceJSCallWithArrayLike(node));
2492 } else {
2493 // Check whether {arguments_list} is null.
2494 Node* check_null =
2495 graph()->NewNode(simplified()->ReferenceEqual(), arguments_list,
2496 jsgraph()->NullConstant());
2497 control = graph()->NewNode(common()->Branch(BranchHint::kFalse),
2498 check_null, control);
2499 Node* if_null = graph()->NewNode(common()->IfTrue(), control);
2500 control = graph()->NewNode(common()->IfFalse(), control);
2501
2502 // Check whether {arguments_list} is undefined.
2503 Node* check_undefined =
2504 graph()->NewNode(simplified()->ReferenceEqual(), arguments_list,
2505 jsgraph()->UndefinedConstant());
2506 control = graph()->NewNode(common()->Branch(BranchHint::kFalse),
2507 check_undefined, control);
2508 Node* if_undefined = graph()->NewNode(common()->IfTrue(), control);
2509 control = graph()->NewNode(common()->IfFalse(), control);
2510
2511 // Lower to {JSCallWithArrayLike} if {arguments_list} is neither null
2512 // nor undefined.
2513 Node* effect0 = effect;
2514 Node* control0 = control;
2515 Node* value0 = effect0 = control0 = graph()->NewNode(
2516 javascript()->CallWithArrayLike(p.frequency(), p.feedback(),
2517 p.speculation_mode(),
2518 CallFeedbackRelation::kUnrelated),
2519 target, this_argument, arguments_list, n.feedback_vector(), context,
2520 frame_state, effect0, control0);
2521
2522 // Lower to {JSCall} if {arguments_list} is either null or undefined.
2523 Node* effect1 = effect;
2524 Node* control1 =
2525 graph()->NewNode(common()->Merge(2), if_null, if_undefined);
2526 Node* value1 = effect1 = control1 =
2527 graph()->NewNode(javascript()->Call(JSCallNode::ArityForArgc(0)),
2528 target, this_argument, n.feedback_vector(), context,
2529 frame_state, effect1, control1);
2530
2531 // Rewire potential exception edges.
2532 Node* if_exception = nullptr;
2533 if (NodeProperties::IsExceptionalCall(node, &if_exception)) {
2534 // Create appropriate {IfException} and {IfSuccess} nodes.
2535 Node* if_exception0 =
2536 graph()->NewNode(common()->IfException(), control0, effect0);
2537 control0 = graph()->NewNode(common()->IfSuccess(), control0);
2538 Node* if_exception1 =
2539 graph()->NewNode(common()->IfException(), control1, effect1);
2540 control1 = graph()->NewNode(common()->IfSuccess(), control1);
2541
2542 // Join the exception edges.
2543 Node* merge =
2544 graph()->NewNode(common()->Merge(2), if_exception0, if_exception1);
2545 Node* ephi = graph()->NewNode(common()->EffectPhi(2), if_exception0,
2546 if_exception1, merge);
2547 Node* phi =
2548 graph()->NewNode(common()->Phi(MachineRepresentation::kTagged, 2),
2549 if_exception0, if_exception1, merge);
2550 ReplaceWithValue(if_exception, phi, ephi, merge);
2551 }
2552
2553 // Join control paths.
2554 control = graph()->NewNode(common()->Merge(2), control0, control1);
2555 effect =
2556 graph()->NewNode(common()->EffectPhi(2), effect0, effect1, control);
2557 Node* value =
2558 graph()->NewNode(common()->Phi(MachineRepresentation::kTagged, 2),
2559 value0, value1, control);
2560 ReplaceWithValue(node, value, effect, control);
2561 return Replace(value);
2562 }
2563 }
2564 // Change {node} to the new {JSCall} operator.
2565 NodeProperties::ChangeOp(
2566 node, javascript()->Call(JSCallNode::ArityForArgc(arity), p.frequency(),
2567 p.feedback(), convert_mode, p.speculation_mode(),
2568 CallFeedbackRelation::kUnrelated));
2569 // Try to further reduce the JSCall {node}.
2570 return Changed(node).FollowedBy(ReduceJSCall(node));
2571}
2572
2573// ES section #sec-function.prototype.bind
2574Reduction JSCallReducer::ReduceFunctionPrototypeBind(Node* node) {
2575 DisallowHeapAccessIf no_heap_access(should_disallow_heap_access());
2576
2577 JSCallNode n(node);
2578 CallParameters const& p = n.Parameters();
2579 if (p.speculation_mode() == SpeculationMode::kDisallowSpeculation) {
2580 return NoChange();
2581 }
2582
2583 // Value inputs to the {node} are as follows:
2584 //
2585 // - target, which is Function.prototype.bind JSFunction
2586 // - receiver, which is the [[BoundTargetFunction]]
2587 // - bound_this (optional), which is the [[BoundThis]]
2588 // - and all the remaining value inputs are [[BoundArguments]]
2589 Node* receiver = n.receiver();
2590 Node* context = n.context();
2591 Effect effect = n.effect();
2592 Control control = n.control();
2593
2594 // Ensure that the {receiver} is known to be a JSBoundFunction or
2595 // a JSFunction with the same [[Prototype]], and all maps we've
2596 // seen for the {receiver} so far indicate that {receiver} is
2597 // definitely a constructor or not a constructor.
2598 MapInference inference(broker(), receiver, effect);
2599 if (!inference.HaveMaps()) return NoChange();
2600 MapHandles const& receiver_maps = inference.GetMaps();
2601
2602 MapRef first_receiver_map(broker(), receiver_maps[0]);
2603 bool const is_constructor = first_receiver_map.is_constructor();
2604
2605 if (should_disallow_heap_access() &&
2606 !first_receiver_map.serialized_prototype()) {
2607 TRACE_BROKER_MISSING(broker(),do { if (broker()->tracing_enabled()) StdoutStream{} <<
broker()->Trace() << "Missing " << "serialized prototype on map "
<< first_receiver_map << " (" << "../deps/v8/src/compiler/js-call-reducer.cc"
<< ":" << 2608 << ")" << std::endl; }
while (false)
2608 "serialized prototype on map " << first_receiver_map)do { if (broker()->tracing_enabled()) StdoutStream{} <<
broker()->Trace() << "Missing " << "serialized prototype on map "
<< first_receiver_map << " (" << "../deps/v8/src/compiler/js-call-reducer.cc"
<< ":" << 2608 << ")" << std::endl; }
while (false);
2609 return inference.NoChange();
2610 }
2611 ObjectRef const prototype = first_receiver_map.prototype();
2612 for (Handle<Map> const map : receiver_maps) {
2613 MapRef receiver_map(broker(), map);
2614
2615 if (should_disallow_heap_access() && !receiver_map.serialized_prototype()) {
2616 TRACE_BROKER_MISSING(broker(),do { if (broker()->tracing_enabled()) StdoutStream{} <<
broker()->Trace() << "Missing " << "serialized prototype on map "
<< receiver_map << " (" << "../deps/v8/src/compiler/js-call-reducer.cc"
<< ":" << 2617 << ")" << std::endl; }
while (false)
2617 "serialized prototype on map " << receiver_map)do { if (broker()->tracing_enabled()) StdoutStream{} <<
broker()->Trace() << "Missing " << "serialized prototype on map "
<< receiver_map << " (" << "../deps/v8/src/compiler/js-call-reducer.cc"
<< ":" << 2617 << ")" << std::endl; }
while (false);
2618 return inference.NoChange();
2619 }
2620
2621 // Check for consistency among the {receiver_maps}.
2622 STATIC_ASSERT(LAST_TYPE == LAST_FUNCTION_TYPE)static_assert(LAST_TYPE == LAST_FUNCTION_TYPE, "LAST_TYPE == LAST_FUNCTION_TYPE"
);
2623 if (!receiver_map.prototype().equals(prototype) ||
2624 receiver_map.is_constructor() != is_constructor ||
2625 receiver_map.instance_type() < FIRST_FUNCTION_TYPE) {
2626 return inference.NoChange();
2627 }
2628
2629 // Disallow binding of slow-mode functions. We need to figure out
2630 // whether the length and name property are in the original state.
2631 if (receiver_map.is_dictionary_map()) return inference.NoChange();
2632
2633 // Check whether the length and name properties are still present
2634 // as AccessorInfo objects. In that case, their values can be
2635 // recomputed even if the actual value of the object changes.
2636 // This mirrors the checks done in builtins-function-gen.cc at
2637 // runtime otherwise.
2638 int minimum_nof_descriptors = i::Max(JSFunction::kLengthDescriptorIndex,
2639 JSFunction::kNameDescriptorIndex) +
2640 1;
2641 if (receiver_map.NumberOfOwnDescriptors() < minimum_nof_descriptors) {
2642 return inference.NoChange();
2643 }
2644 const InternalIndex kLengthIndex(JSFunction::kLengthDescriptorIndex);
2645 const InternalIndex kNameIndex(JSFunction::kNameDescriptorIndex);
2646 if (!receiver_map.serialized_own_descriptor(kLengthIndex) ||
2647 !receiver_map.serialized_own_descriptor(kNameIndex)) {
2648 TRACE_BROKER_MISSING(broker(),do { if (broker()->tracing_enabled()) StdoutStream{} <<
broker()->Trace() << "Missing " << "serialized descriptors on map "
<< receiver_map << " (" << "../deps/v8/src/compiler/js-call-reducer.cc"
<< ":" << 2649 << ")" << std::endl; }
while (false)
2649 "serialized descriptors on map " << receiver_map)do { if (broker()->tracing_enabled()) StdoutStream{} <<
broker()->Trace() << "Missing " << "serialized descriptors on map "
<< receiver_map << " (" << "../deps/v8/src/compiler/js-call-reducer.cc"
<< ":" << 2649 << ")" << std::endl; }
while (false);
2650 return inference.NoChange();
2651 }
2652 ReadOnlyRoots roots(isolate());
2653 StringRef length_string(broker(), roots.length_string_handle());
2654 StringRef name_string(broker(), roots.name_string_handle());
2655
2656 base::Optional<ObjectRef> length_value(
2657 receiver_map.GetStrongValue(kLengthIndex));
2658 base::Optional<ObjectRef> name_value(
2659 receiver_map.GetStrongValue(kNameIndex));
2660 if (!length_value || !name_value) {
2661 TRACE_BROKER_MISSING(do { if (broker()->tracing_enabled()) StdoutStream{} <<
broker()->Trace() << "Missing " << "name or length descriptors on map "
<< receiver_map << " (" << "../deps/v8/src/compiler/js-call-reducer.cc"
<< ":" << 2662 << ")" << std::endl; }
while (false)
2662 broker(), "name or length descriptors on map " << receiver_map)do { if (broker()->tracing_enabled()) StdoutStream{} <<
broker()->Trace() << "Missing " << "name or length descriptors on map "
<< receiver_map << " (" << "../deps/v8/src/compiler/js-call-reducer.cc"
<< ":" << 2662 << ")" << std::endl; }
while (false);
2663 return inference.NoChange();
2664 }
2665 if (!receiver_map.GetPropertyKey(kLengthIndex).equals(length_string) ||
2666 !length_value->IsAccessorInfo() ||
2667 !receiver_map.GetPropertyKey(kNameIndex).equals(name_string) ||
2668 !name_value->IsAccessorInfo()) {
2669 return inference.NoChange();
2670 }
2671 }
2672
2673 // Choose the map for the resulting JSBoundFunction (but bail out in case of a
2674 // custom prototype).
2675 MapRef map = is_constructor
2676 ? native_context().bound_function_with_constructor_map()
2677 : native_context().bound_function_without_constructor_map();
2678 if (!map.prototype().equals(prototype)) return inference.NoChange();
2679
2680 inference.RelyOnMapsPreferStability(dependencies(), jsgraph(), &effect,
2681 control, p.feedback());
2682
2683 // Replace the {node} with a JSCreateBoundFunction.
2684 static constexpr int kBoundThis = 1;
2685 static constexpr int kReceiverContextEffectAndControl = 4;
2686 int const arity = n.ArgumentCount();
2687 int const arity_with_bound_this = std::max(arity, kBoundThis);
2688 int const input_count =
2689 arity_with_bound_this + kReceiverContextEffectAndControl;
2690 Node** inputs = graph()->zone()->NewArray<Node*>(input_count);
2691 int cursor = 0;
2692 inputs[cursor++] = receiver;
2693 inputs[cursor++] = n.ArgumentOrUndefined(0, jsgraph()); // bound_this.
2694 for (int i = 1; i < arity; ++i) {
2695 inputs[cursor++] = n.Argument(i);
2696 }
2697 inputs[cursor++] = context;
2698 inputs[cursor++] = effect;
2699 inputs[cursor++] = control;
2700 DCHECK_EQ(cursor, input_count)((void) 0);
2701 Node* value = effect =
2702 graph()->NewNode(javascript()->CreateBoundFunction(
2703 arity_with_bound_this - kBoundThis, map.object()),
2704 input_count, inputs);
2705 ReplaceWithValue(node, value, effect, control);
2706 return Replace(value);
2707}
2708
2709// ES6 section 19.2.3.3 Function.prototype.call (thisArg, ...args)
2710Reduction JSCallReducer::ReduceFunctionPrototypeCall(Node* node) {
2711 DisallowHeapAccessIf no_heap_access(should_disallow_heap_access());
2712
2713 JSCallNode n(node);
2714 CallParameters const& p = n.Parameters();
2715 Node* target = n.target();
2716 Effect effect = n.effect();
2717 Control control = n.control();
2718
2719 // Change context of {node} to the Function.prototype.call context,
2720 // to ensure any exception is thrown in the correct context.
2721 Node* context;
2722 HeapObjectMatcher m(target);
2723 if (m.HasValue()) {
2724 JSFunctionRef function = m.Ref(broker()).AsJSFunction();
2725 if (should_disallow_heap_access() && !function.serialized()) {
2726 TRACE_BROKER_MISSING(broker(), "Serialize call on function " << function)do { if (broker()->tracing_enabled()) StdoutStream{} <<
broker()->Trace() << "Missing " << "Serialize call on function "
<< function << " (" << "../deps/v8/src/compiler/js-call-reducer.cc"
<< ":" << 2726 << ")" << std::endl; }
while (false);
2727 return NoChange();
2728 }
2729 context = jsgraph()->Constant(function.context());
2730 } else {
2731 context = effect = graph()->NewNode(
2732 simplified()->LoadField(AccessBuilder::ForJSFunctionContext()), target,
2733 effect, control);
2734 }
2735 NodeProperties::ReplaceContextInput(node, context);
2736 NodeProperties::ReplaceEffectInput(node, effect);
2737
2738 // Remove the target from {node} and use the receiver as target instead, and
2739 // the thisArg becomes the new target. If thisArg was not provided, insert
2740 // undefined instead.
2741 int arity = p.arity_without_implicit_args();
2742 ConvertReceiverMode convert_mode;
2743 if (arity == 0) {
2744 // The thisArg was not provided, use undefined as receiver.
2745 convert_mode = ConvertReceiverMode::kNullOrUndefined;
2746 node->ReplaceInput(n.TargetIndex(), n.receiver());
2747 node->ReplaceInput(n.ReceiverIndex(), jsgraph()->UndefinedConstant());
2748 } else {
2749 // Just remove the target, which is the first value input.
2750 convert_mode = ConvertReceiverMode::kAny;
2751 node->RemoveInput(n.TargetIndex());
2752 --arity;
2753 }
2754 NodeProperties::ChangeOp(
2755 node, javascript()->Call(JSCallNode::ArityForArgc(arity), p.frequency(),
2756 p.feedback(), convert_mode, p.speculation_mode(),
2757 CallFeedbackRelation::kUnrelated));
2758 // Try to further reduce the JSCall {node}.
2759 return Changed(node).FollowedBy(ReduceJSCall(node));
2760}
2761
2762// ES6 section 19.2.3.6 Function.prototype [ @@hasInstance ] (V)
2763Reduction JSCallReducer::ReduceFunctionPrototypeHasInstance(Node* node) {
2764 JSCallNode n(node);
2765 Node* receiver = n.receiver();
2766 Node* object = n.ArgumentOrUndefined(0, jsgraph());
2767 Node* context = n.context();
2768 FrameState frame_state = n.frame_state();
2769 Effect effect = n.effect();
2770 Control control = n.control();
2771
2772 // TODO(turbofan): If JSOrdinaryToInstance raises an exception, the
2773 // stack trace doesn't contain the @@hasInstance call; we have the
2774 // corresponding bug in the baseline case. Some massaging of the frame
2775 // state would be necessary here.
2776
2777 // Morph this {node} into a JSOrdinaryHasInstance node.
2778 node->ReplaceInput(0, receiver);
2779 node->ReplaceInput(1, object);
2780 node->ReplaceInput(2, context);
2781 node->ReplaceInput(3, frame_state);
2782 node->ReplaceInput(4, effect);
2783 node->ReplaceInput(5, control);
2784 node->TrimInputCount(6);
2785 NodeProperties::ChangeOp(node, javascript()->OrdinaryHasInstance());
2786 return Changed(node);
2787}
2788
2789Reduction JSCallReducer::ReduceObjectGetPrototype(Node* node, Node* object) {
2790 Node* effect = NodeProperties::GetEffectInput(node);
2791
2792 // Try to determine the {object} map.
2793 MapInference inference(broker(), object, effect);
2794 if (!inference.HaveMaps()) return NoChange();
2795 MapHandles const& object_maps = inference.GetMaps();
2796
2797 MapRef candidate_map(broker(), object_maps[0]);
2798 if (should_disallow_heap_access() && !candidate_map.serialized_prototype()) {
2799 TRACE_BROKER_MISSING(broker(), "prototype for map " << candidate_map)do { if (broker()->tracing_enabled()) StdoutStream{} <<
broker()->Trace() << "Missing " << "prototype for map "
<< candidate_map << " (" << "../deps/v8/src/compiler/js-call-reducer.cc"
<< ":" << 2799 << ")" << std::endl; }
while (false);
2800 return inference.NoChange();
2801 }
2802 ObjectRef candidate_prototype = candidate_map.prototype();
2803
2804 // Check if we can constant-fold the {candidate_prototype}.
2805 for (size_t i = 0; i < object_maps.size(); ++i) {
2806 MapRef object_map(broker(), object_maps[i]);
2807 if (should_disallow_heap_access() && !object_map.serialized_prototype()) {
2808 TRACE_BROKER_MISSING(broker(), "prototype for map " << object_map)do { if (broker()->tracing_enabled()) StdoutStream{} <<
broker()->Trace() << "Missing " << "prototype for map "
<< object_map << " (" << "../deps/v8/src/compiler/js-call-reducer.cc"
<< ":" << 2808 << ")" << std::endl; }
while (false);
2809 return inference.NoChange();
2810 }
2811 if (IsSpecialReceiverInstanceType(object_map.instance_type()) ||
2812 !object_map.prototype().equals(candidate_prototype)) {
2813 // We exclude special receivers, like JSProxy or API objects that
2814 // might require access checks here; we also don't want to deal
2815 // with hidden prototypes at this point.
2816 return inference.NoChange();
2817 }
2818 // The above check also excludes maps for primitive values, which is
2819 // important because we are not applying [[ToObject]] here as expected.
2820 DCHECK(!object_map.IsPrimitiveMap() && object_map.IsJSReceiverMap())((void) 0);
2821 }
2822 if (!inference.RelyOnMapsViaStability(dependencies())) {
2823 return inference.NoChange();
2824 }
2825 Node* value = jsgraph()->Constant(candidate_prototype);
2826 ReplaceWithValue(node, value);
2827 return Replace(value);
2828}
2829
2830// ES6 section 19.1.2.11 Object.getPrototypeOf ( O )
2831Reduction JSCallReducer::ReduceObjectGetPrototypeOf(Node* node) {

2853// ES #sec-object.prototype.hasownproperty
2854Reduction JSCallReducer::ReduceObjectPrototypeHasOwnProperty(Node* node) {
2855 JSCallNode n(node);
2856 Node* receiver = n.receiver();
2857 Node* name = n.ArgumentOrUndefined(0, jsgraph());
2858 Effect effect = n.effect();
2859 Control control = n.control();
2860
2861 // We can optimize a call to Object.prototype.hasOwnProperty if it's being
2862 // used inside a fast-mode for..in, so for code like this:
2863 //
2864 // for (name in receiver) {
2865 // if (receiver.hasOwnProperty(name)) {
2866 // ...
2867 // }
2868 // }
2869 //
2870 // If the for..in is in fast-mode, we know that the {receiver} has {name}
2871 // as own property, otherwise the enumeration wouldn't include it. The graph
2872 // constructed by the BytecodeGraphBuilder in this case looks like this:
2873
2874 // receiver
2875 // ^ ^
2876 // | |
2877 // | +-+
2878 // | |
2879 // | JSToObject
2880 // | ^
2881 // | |
2882 // | JSForInNext
2883 // | ^
2884 // +----+ |
2885 // | |
2886 // JSCall[hasOwnProperty]
2887
2888 // We can constant-fold the {node} to True in this case, and insert
2889 // a (potentially redundant) map check to guard the fact that the
2890 // {receiver} map didn't change since the dominating JSForInNext. This
2891 // map check is only necessary when TurboFan cannot prove that there
2892 // is no observable side effect between the {JSForInNext} and the
2893 // {JSCall} to Object.prototype.hasOwnProperty.
2894 //
2895 // Also note that it's safe to look through the {JSToObject}, since the
2896 // Object.prototype.hasOwnProperty does an implicit ToObject anyway, and
2897 // these operations are not observable.
2898 if (name->opcode() == IrOpcode::kJSForInNext) {
2899 ForInMode const mode = ForInModeOf(name->op());
2900 if (mode != ForInMode::kGeneric) {
2901 Node* object = NodeProperties::GetValueInput(name, 0);
2902 Node* cache_type = NodeProperties::GetValueInput(name, 2);
2903 if (object->opcode() == IrOpcode::kJSToObject) {
2904 object = NodeProperties::GetValueInput(object, 0);
2905 }
2906 if (object == receiver) {
2907 // No need to repeat the map check if we can prove that there's no
2908 // observable side effect between {effect} and {name].
2909 if (!NodeProperties::NoObservableSideEffectBetween(effect, name)) {
2910 Node* receiver_map = effect =
2911 graph()->NewNode(simplified()->LoadField(AccessBuilder::ForMap()),
2912 receiver, effect, control);
2913 Node* check = graph()->NewNode(simplified()->ReferenceEqual(),
2914 receiver_map, cache_type);
2915 effect = graph()->NewNode(
2916 simplified()->CheckIf(DeoptimizeReason::kWrongMap), check, effect,
2917 control);
2918 }
2919 Node* value = jsgraph()->TrueConstant();
2920 ReplaceWithValue(node, value, effect, control);
2921 return Replace(value);
2922 }
2923 }
2924 }
2925
2926 return NoChange();
2927}
2928
2929// ES #sec-object.prototype.isprototypeof
2930Reduction JSCallReducer::ReduceObjectPrototypeIsPrototypeOf(Node* node) {
2931 DisallowHeapAccessIf no_heap_access(should_disallow_heap_access());
2932
2933 JSCallNode n(node);
2934 Node* receiver = n.receiver();
2935 Node* value = n.ArgumentOrUndefined(0, jsgraph());
2936 Effect effect = n.effect();
2937
2938 // Ensure that the {receiver} is known to be a JSReceiver (so that
2939 // the ToObject step of Object.prototype.isPrototypeOf is a no-op).
2940 MapInference inference(broker(), receiver, effect);
2941 if (!inference.HaveMaps() || !inference.AllOfInstanceTypesAreJSReceiver()) {
2942 return NoChange();
2943 }
2944
2945 // We don't check whether {value} is a proper JSReceiver here explicitly,
2946 // and don't explicitly rule out Primitive {value}s, since all of them
2947 // have null as their prototype, so the prototype chain walk inside the
2948 // JSHasInPrototypeChain operator immediately aborts and yields false.
2949 NodeProperties::ReplaceValueInput(node, value, n.TargetIndex());
2950 for (int i = node->op()->ValueInputCount(); i > 2; i--) {
2951 node->RemoveInput(2);
2952 }
2953 NodeProperties::ChangeOp(node, javascript()->HasInPrototypeChain());
2954 return Changed(node);
2955}
2956
2957// ES6 section 26.1.1 Reflect.apply ( target, thisArgument, argumentsList )
2958Reduction JSCallReducer::ReduceReflectApply(Node* node) {
2959 JSCallNode n(node);
2960 CallParameters const& p = n.Parameters();
2961 int arity = p.arity_without_implicit_args();
2962 // Massage value inputs appropriately.
2963 STATIC_ASSERT(n.ReceiverIndex() > n.TargetIndex())static_assert(n.ReceiverIndex() > n.TargetIndex(), "n.ReceiverIndex() > n.TargetIndex()"
);
2964 node->RemoveInput(n.ReceiverIndex());
2965 node->RemoveInput(n.TargetIndex());
2966 while (arity < 3) {
2967 node->InsertInput(graph()->zone(), arity++, jsgraph()->UndefinedConstant());
2968 }
2969 while (arity-- > 3) {
2970 node->RemoveInput(arity);
2971 }
2972 NodeProperties::ChangeOp(
2973 node, javascript()->CallWithArrayLike(p.frequency(), p.feedback(),
2974 p.speculation_mode(),
2975 CallFeedbackRelation::kUnrelated));
2976 return Changed(node).FollowedBy(ReduceJSCallWithArrayLike(node));
2977}

2979// ES6 section 26.1.2 Reflect.construct ( target, argumentsList [, newTarget] )
2980Reduction JSCallReducer::ReduceReflectConstruct(Node* node) {
2981 JSCallNode n(node);
2982 CallParameters const& p = n.Parameters();
2983 int arity = p.arity_without_implicit_args();
2984 // Massage value inputs appropriately.
2985 Node* arg_target = n.ArgumentOrUndefined(0, jsgraph());
2986 Node* arg_argument_list = n.ArgumentOrUndefined(1, jsgraph());
2987 Node* arg_new_target = n.ArgumentOr(2, arg_target);
2988
2989 STATIC_ASSERT(n.ReceiverIndex() > n.TargetIndex())static_assert(n.ReceiverIndex() > n.TargetIndex(), "n.ReceiverIndex() > n.TargetIndex()"
);
2990 node->RemoveInput(n.ReceiverIndex());
2991 node->RemoveInput(n.TargetIndex());
2992
2993 // TODO(jgruber): This pattern essentially ensures that we have the correct
2994 // number of inputs for a given argument count. Wrap it in a helper function.
2995 STATIC_ASSERT(JSConstructNode::FirstArgumentIndex() == 2)static_assert(JSConstructNode::FirstArgumentIndex() == 2, "JSConstructNode::FirstArgumentIndex() == 2"
);
2996 while (arity < 3) {
2997 node->InsertInput(graph()->zone(), arity++, jsgraph()->UndefinedConstant());
2998 }
2999 while (arity-- > 3) {
3000 node->RemoveInput(arity);
3001 }
3002
3003 STATIC_ASSERT(JSConstructNode::TargetIndex() == 0)static_assert(JSConstructNode::TargetIndex() == 0, "JSConstructNode::TargetIndex() == 0"
);
3004 STATIC_ASSERT(JSConstructNode::NewTargetIndex() == 1)static_assert(JSConstructNode::NewTargetIndex() == 1, "JSConstructNode::NewTargetIndex() == 1"
);
3005 STATIC_ASSERT(JSConstructNode::kFeedbackVectorIsLastInput)static_assert(JSConstructNode::kFeedbackVectorIsLastInput, "JSConstructNode::kFeedbackVectorIsLastInput"
);
3006 node->ReplaceInput(JSConstructNode::TargetIndex(), arg_target);
3007 node->ReplaceInput(JSConstructNode::NewTargetIndex(), arg_new_target);
3008 node->ReplaceInput(JSConstructNode::ArgumentIndex(0), arg_argument_list);
3009
3010 NodeProperties::ChangeOp(
3011 node, javascript()->ConstructWithArrayLike(p.frequency(), p.feedback()));
3012 return Changed(node).FollowedBy(ReduceJSConstructWithArrayLike(node));
3013}

3022// ES6 section #sec-object.create Object.create(proto, properties)
3023Reduction JSCallReducer::ReduceObjectCreate(Node* node) {
3024 JSCallNode n(node);
3025 Node* properties = n.ArgumentOrUndefined(1, jsgraph());
3026 if (properties != jsgraph()->UndefinedConstant()) return NoChange();
3027
3028 Node* context = n.context();
3029 FrameState frame_state = n.frame_state();
3030 Effect effect = n.effect();
3031 Control control = n.control();
3032 Node* prototype = n.ArgumentOrUndefined(0, jsgraph());
3033 node->ReplaceInput(0, prototype);
3034 node->ReplaceInput(1, context);
3035 node->ReplaceInput(2, frame_state);
3036 node->ReplaceInput(3, effect);
3037 node->ReplaceInput(4, control);
3038 node->TrimInputCount(5);
3039 NodeProperties::ChangeOp(node, javascript()->CreateObject());
3040 return Changed(node);
3041}
3042
3043// ES section #sec-reflect.get
3044Reduction JSCallReducer::ReduceReflectGet(Node* node) {
3045 JSCallNode n(node);
3046 CallParameters const& p = n.Parameters();
3047 int arity = p.arity_without_implicit_args();
3048 if (arity != 2) return NoChange();
3049 Node* target = n.Argument(0);
3050 Node* key = n.Argument(1);
3051 Node* context = n.context();
3052 FrameState frame_state = n.frame_state();
3053 Effect effect = n.effect();
3054 Control control = n.control();
3055
3056 // Check whether {target} is a JSReceiver.
3057 Node* check = graph()->NewNode(simplified()->ObjectIsReceiver(), target);
3058 Node* branch =
3059 graph()->NewNode(common()->Branch(BranchHint::kTrue), check, control);
3060
3061 // Throw an appropriate TypeError if the {target} is not a JSReceiver.
3062 Node* if_false = graph()->NewNode(common()->IfFalse(), branch);
3063 Node* efalse = effect;
3064 {
3065 if_false = efalse = graph()->NewNode(
3066 javascript()->CallRuntime(Runtime::kThrowTypeError, 2),
3067 jsgraph()->Constant(
3068 static_cast<int>(MessageTemplate::kCalledOnNonObject)),
3069 jsgraph()->HeapConstant(factory()->ReflectGet_string()), context,
3070 frame_state, efalse, if_false);
3071 }
3072
3073 // Otherwise just use the existing GetPropertyStub.
3074 Node* if_true = graph()->NewNode(common()->IfTrue(), branch);
3075 Node* etrue = effect;
3076 Node* vtrue;
3077 {
3078 Callable callable =
3079 Builtins::CallableFor(isolate(), Builtins::kGetProperty);
3080 auto call_descriptor = Linkage::GetStubCallDescriptor(
3081 graph()->zone(), callable.descriptor(),
3082 callable.descriptor().GetStackParameterCount(),
3083 CallDescriptor::kNeedsFrameState, Operator::kNoProperties);
3084 Node* stub_code = jsgraph()->HeapConstant(callable.code());
3085 vtrue = etrue = if_true =
3086 graph()->NewNode(common()->Call(call_descriptor), stub_code, target,
3087 key, context, frame_state, etrue, if_true);
3088 }
3089
3090 // Rewire potential exception edges.
3091 Node* on_exception = nullptr;
3092 if (NodeProperties::IsExceptionalCall(node, &on_exception)) {
3093 // Create appropriate {IfException} and {IfSuccess} nodes.
3094 Node* extrue = graph()->NewNode(common()->IfException(), etrue, if_true);
3095 if_true = graph()->NewNode(common()->IfSuccess(), if_true);
3096 Node* exfalse = graph()->NewNode(common()->IfException(), efalse, if_false);
3097 if_false = graph()->NewNode(common()->IfSuccess(), if_false);
3098
3099 // Join the exception edges.
3100 Node* merge = graph()->NewNode(common()->Merge(2), extrue, exfalse);
3101 Node* ephi =
3102 graph()->NewNode(common()->EffectPhi(2), extrue, exfalse, merge);
3103 Node* phi =
3104 graph()->NewNode(common()->Phi(MachineRepresentation::kTagged, 2),
3105 extrue, exfalse, merge);
3106 ReplaceWithValue(on_exception, phi, ephi, merge);
3107 }
3108
3109 // Connect the throwing path to end.
3110 if_false = graph()->NewNode(common()->Throw(), efalse, if_false);
3111 NodeProperties::MergeControlToEnd(graph(), common(), if_false);
3112
3113 // Continue on the regular path.
3114 ReplaceWithValue(node, vtrue, etrue, if_true);
3115 return Changed(vtrue);
3116}
3117
3118// ES section #sec-reflect.has
3119Reduction JSCallReducer::ReduceReflectHas(Node* node) {
3120 JSCallNode n(node);
3121 Node* target = n.ArgumentOrUndefined(0, jsgraph());
3122 Node* key = n.ArgumentOrUndefined(1, jsgraph());
3123 Node* context = n.context();
3124 Effect effect = n.effect();
3125 Control control = n.control();
3126 FrameState frame_state = n.frame_state();
3127
3128 // Check whether {target} is a JSReceiver.
3129 Node* check = graph()->NewNode(simplified()->ObjectIsReceiver(), target);
3130 Node* branch =
3131 graph()->NewNode(common()->Branch(BranchHint::kTrue), check, control);
3132
3133 // Throw an appropriate TypeError if the {target} is not a JSReceiver.
3134 Node* if_false = graph()->NewNode(common()->IfFalse(), branch);
3135 Node* efalse = effect;
3136 {
3137 if_false = efalse = graph()->NewNode(
3138 javascript()->CallRuntime(Runtime::kThrowTypeError, 2),
3139 jsgraph()->Constant(
3140 static_cast<int>(MessageTemplate::kCalledOnNonObject)),
3141 jsgraph()->HeapConstant(factory()->ReflectHas_string()), context,
3142 frame_state, efalse, if_false);
3143 }
3144
3145 // Otherwise just use the existing {JSHasProperty} logic.
3146 Node* if_true = graph()->NewNode(common()->IfTrue(), branch);
3147 Node* etrue = effect;
3148 Node* vtrue;
3149 {
3150 // TODO(magardn): collect feedback so this can be optimized
3151 vtrue = etrue = if_true = graph()->NewNode(
3152 javascript()->HasProperty(FeedbackSource()), target, key,
3153 jsgraph()->UndefinedConstant(), context, frame_state, etrue, if_true);
3154 }
3155
3156 // Rewire potential exception edges.
3157 Node* on_exception = nullptr;
3158 if (NodeProperties::IsExceptionalCall(node, &on_exception)) {
3159 // Create appropriate {IfException} and {IfSuccess} nodes.
3160 Node* extrue = graph()->NewNode(common()->IfException(), etrue, if_true);
3161 if_true = graph()->NewNode(common()->IfSuccess(), if_true);
3162 Node* exfalse = graph()->NewNode(common()->IfException(), efalse, if_false);
3163 if_false = graph()->NewNode(common()->IfSuccess(), if_false);
3164
3165 // Join the exception edges.
3166 Node* merge = graph()->NewNode(common()->Merge(2), extrue, exfalse);
3167 Node* ephi =
3168 graph()->NewNode(common()->EffectPhi(2), extrue, exfalse, merge);
3169 Node* phi =
3170 graph()->NewNode(common()->Phi(MachineRepresentation::kTagged, 2),
3171 extrue, exfalse, merge);
3172 ReplaceWithValue(on_exception, phi, ephi, merge);
3173 }
3174
3175 // Connect the throwing path to end.
3176 if_false = graph()->NewNode(common()->Throw(), efalse, if_false);
3177 NodeProperties::MergeControlToEnd(graph(), common(), if_false);
3178
3179 // Continue on the regular path.
3180 ReplaceWithValue(node, vtrue, etrue, if_true);
3181 return Changed(vtrue);
3182}

3184namespace {
3185bool CanInlineArrayIteratingBuiltin(JSHeapBroker* broker,
3186 MapHandles const& receiver_maps,
3187 ElementsKind* kind_return) {
3188 DCHECK_NE(0, receiver_maps.size())((void) 0);
3189 *kind_return = MapRef(broker, receiver_maps[0]).elements_kind();
3190 for (auto receiver_map : receiver_maps) {
3191 MapRef map(broker, receiver_map);
3192 if (!map.supports_fast_array_iteration() ||
3193 !UnionElementsKindUptoSize(kind_return, map.elements_kind())) {
3194 return false;
3195 }
3196 }
3197 return true;
3198}
3199
3200bool CanInlineArrayResizingBuiltin(JSHeapBroker* broker,
3201 MapHandles const& receiver_maps,
3202 std::vector<ElementsKind>* kinds,
3203 bool builtin_is_push = false) {
3204 DCHECK_NE(0, receiver_maps.size())((void) 0);
3205 for (auto receiver_map : receiver_maps) {
3206 MapRef map(broker, receiver_map);
3207 if (!map.supports_fast_array_resize()) return false;
3208 // TODO(turbofan): We should also handle fast holey double elements once
3209 // we got the hole NaN mess sorted out in TurboFan/V8.
3210 if (map.elements_kind() == HOLEY_DOUBLE_ELEMENTS && !builtin_is_push) {
3211 return false;
3212 }
3213 ElementsKind current_kind = map.elements_kind();
3214 auto kind_ptr = kinds->data();
3215 size_t i;
3216 for (i = 0; i < kinds->size(); i++, kind_ptr++) {
3217 if (UnionElementsKindUptoPackedness(kind_ptr, current_kind)) {
3218 break;
3219 }
3220 }
3221 if (i == kinds->size()) kinds->push_back(current_kind);
3222 }
3223 return true;
3224}
3225
3226// Wraps common setup code for iterating array builtins.
3227class IteratingArrayBuiltinHelper {
3228 public:
3229 IteratingArrayBuiltinHelper(Node* node, JSHeapBroker* broker,
3230 JSGraph* jsgraph,
3231 CompilationDependencies* dependencies)
3232 : receiver_(NodeProperties::GetValueInput(node, 1)),
3233 effect_(NodeProperties::GetEffectInput(node)),
3234 control_(NodeProperties::GetControlInput(node)),
3235 inference_(broker, receiver_, effect_) {
3236 if (!FLAG_turbo_inline_array_builtins) return;
3237
3238 DCHECK_EQ(IrOpcode::kJSCall, node->opcode())((void) 0);
3239 const CallParameters& p = CallParametersOf(node->op());
3240 if (p.speculation_mode() == SpeculationMode::kDisallowSpeculation) {
3241 return;
3242 }
3243
3244 // Try to determine the {receiver} map.
3245 if (!inference_.HaveMaps()) return;
3246 MapHandles const& receiver_maps = inference_.GetMaps();
3247
3248 if (!CanInlineArrayIteratingBuiltin(broker, receiver_maps,
3249 &elements_kind_)) {
3250 return;
3251 }
3252
3253 // TODO(jgruber): May only be needed for holey elements kinds.
3254 if (!dependencies->DependOnNoElementsProtector()) UNREACHABLE()V8_Fatal("unreachable code");
3255 has_stability_dependency_ = inference_.RelyOnMapsPreferStability(
3256 dependencies, jsgraph, &effect_, control_, p.feedback());
3257
3258 can_reduce_ = true;
3259 }
3260
3261 bool can_reduce() const { return can_reduce_; }
3262 bool has_stability_dependency() const { return has_stability_dependency_; }
3263 Effect effect() const { return effect_; }
3264 Control control() const { return control_; }
3265 MapInference* inference() { return &inference_; }
3266 ElementsKind elements_kind() const { return elements_kind_; }
3267
3268 private:
3269 bool can_reduce_ = false;
3270 bool has_stability_dependency_ = false;
3271 Node* receiver_;
3272 Effect effect_;
3273 Control control_;
3274 MapInference inference_;
3275 ElementsKind elements_kind_;
3276};
3277
3278} // namespace

3280Reduction JSCallReducer::ReduceArrayForEach(
3281 Node* node, const SharedFunctionInfoRef& shared) {
3282 DisallowHeapAccessIf disallow_heap_access(should_disallow_heap_access());
3283 IteratingArrayBuiltinHelper h(node, broker(), jsgraph(), dependencies());
3284 if (!h.can_reduce()) return h.inference()->NoChange();
3285
3286 IteratingArrayBuiltinReducerAssembler a(jsgraph(), temp_zone(), node);
3287 a.InitializeEffectControl(h.effect(), h.control());
3288 TNode<Object> subgraph = a.ReduceArrayPrototypeForEach(
3289 h.inference(), h.has_stability_dependency(), h.elements_kind(), shared);
3290 return ReplaceWithSubgraph(&a, subgraph);
3291}
