3450
3451Reduction JSCallReducer::ReduceCallApiFunction(
3452 Node* node, const SharedFunctionInfoRef& shared) {
3453 DisallowHeapAccessIf no_heap_access(should_disallow_heap_access());
3454
3455 JSCallNode n(node);
3456 CallParameters const& p = n.Parameters();
3457 int const argc = p.arity_without_implicit_args();
3458 Node* target = n.target();
3459 Node* global_proxy =
3460 jsgraph()->Constant(native_context().global_proxy_object());
3461 Node* receiver = (p.convert_mode() == ConvertReceiverMode::kNullOrUndefined)
3462 ? global_proxy
3463 : n.receiver();
3464 Node* holder;
3465 Node* context = n.context();
3466 Effect effect = n.effect();
3467 Control control = n.control();
3468 FrameState frame_state = n.frame_state();
3469
3470 if (!shared.function_template_info().has_value()) {
3471 TRACE_BROKER_MISSING(do { if (broker()->tracing_enabled()) StdoutStream{} <<
broker()->Trace() << "Missing " << "FunctionTemplateInfo for function with SFI "
<< shared << " (" << "../deps/v8/src/compiler/js-call-reducer.cc"
<< ":" << 3472 << ")" << std::endl; }
while (false)
3472 broker(), "FunctionTemplateInfo for function with SFI " << shared)do { if (broker()->tracing_enabled()) StdoutStream{} <<
broker()->Trace() << "Missing " << "FunctionTemplateInfo for function with SFI "
<< shared << " (" << "../deps/v8/src/compiler/js-call-reducer.cc"
<< ":" << 3472 << ")" << std::endl; }
while (false);
3473 return NoChange();
3474 }
3475
3476 // See if we can optimize this API call to {shared}.
3477 FunctionTemplateInfoRef function_template_info(
3478 shared.function_template_info().value());
3479
3480 if (!function_template_info.has_call_code()) return NoChange();
3481
3482 if (function_template_info.accept_any_receiver() &&
3483 function_template_info.is_signature_undefined()) {
3484 // We might be able to
3485 // optimize the API call depending on the {function_template_info}.
3486 // If the API function accepts any kind of {receiver}, we only need to
3487 // ensure that the {receiver} is actually a JSReceiver at this point,
3488 // and also pass that as the {holder}. There are two independent bits
3489 // here:
3490 //
3491 // a. When the "accept any receiver" bit is set, it means we don't
3492 // need to perform access checks, even if the {receiver}'s map
3493 // has the "needs access check" bit set.
3494 // b. When the {function_template_info} has no signature, we don't
3495 // need to do the compatible receiver check, since all receivers
3496 // are considered compatible at that point, and the {receiver}
3497 // will be pass as the {holder}.
3498 //
3499 receiver = holder = effect =
3500 graph()->NewNode(simplified()->ConvertReceiver(p.convert_mode()),
3501 receiver, global_proxy, effect, control);
3502 } else {
3503 // Try to infer the {receiver} maps from the graph.
3504 MapInference inference(broker(), receiver, effect);
3505 if (inference.HaveMaps()) {
3506 MapHandles const& receiver_maps = inference.GetMaps();
3507 MapRef first_receiver_map(broker(), receiver_maps[0]);
3508
3509 // See if we can constant-fold the compatible receiver checks.
3510 HolderLookupResult api_holder =
3511 function_template_info.LookupHolderOfExpectedType(first_receiver_map);
3512 if (api_holder.lookup == CallOptimization::kHolderNotFound) {
3513 return inference.NoChange();
3514 }
3515
3516 // Check that all {receiver_maps} are actually JSReceiver maps and
3517 // that the {function_template_info} accepts them without access
3518 // checks (even if "access check needed" is set for {receiver}).
3519 //
3520 // Note that we don't need to know the concrete {receiver} maps here,
3521 // meaning it's fine if the {receiver_maps} are unreliable, and we also
3522 // don't need to install any stability dependencies, since the only
3523 // relevant information regarding the {receiver} is the Map::constructor
3524 // field on the root map (which is different from the JavaScript exposed
3525 // "constructor" property) and that field cannot change.
3526 //
3527 // So if we know that {receiver} had a certain constructor at some point
3528 // in the past (i.e. it had a certain map), then this constructor is going
3529 // to be the same later, since this information cannot change with map
3530 // transitions.
3531 //
3532 // The same is true for the instance type, e.g. we still know that the
3533 // instance type is JSObject even if that information is unreliable, and
3534 // the "access check needed" bit, which also cannot change later.
3535 CHECK(first_receiver_map.IsJSReceiverMap())do { if ((__builtin_expect(!!(!(first_receiver_map.IsJSReceiverMap
())), 0))) { V8_Fatal("Check failed: %s.", "first_receiver_map.IsJSReceiverMap()"
); } } while (false);
3536 CHECK(!first_receiver_map.is_access_check_needed() ||do { if ((__builtin_expect(!!(!(!first_receiver_map.is_access_check_needed
() || function_template_info.accept_any_receiver())), 0))) { V8_Fatal
("Check failed: %s.", "!first_receiver_map.is_access_check_needed() || function_template_info.accept_any_receiver()"
); } } while (false)
3537 function_template_info.accept_any_receiver())do { if ((__builtin_expect(!!(!(!first_receiver_map.is_access_check_needed
() || function_template_info.accept_any_receiver())), 0))) { V8_Fatal
("Check failed: %s.", "!first_receiver_map.is_access_check_needed() || function_template_info.accept_any_receiver()"
); } } while (false);
3538
3539 for (size_t i = 1; i < receiver_maps.size(); ++i) {
3540 MapRef receiver_map(broker(), receiver_maps[i]);
3541 HolderLookupResult holder_i =
3542 function_template_info.LookupHolderOfExpectedType(receiver_map);
3543
3544 if (api_holder.lookup != holder_i.lookup) return inference.NoChange();
3545 DCHECK(holder_i.lookup == CallOptimization::kHolderFound ||((void) 0)
3546 holder_i.lookup == CallOptimization::kHolderIsReceiver)((void) 0);
3547 if (holder_i.lookup == CallOptimization::kHolderFound) {
3548 DCHECK(api_holder.holder.has_value() && holder_i.holder.has_value())((void) 0);
3549 if (!api_holder.holder->equals(*holder_i.holder)) {
3550 return inference.NoChange();
3551 }
3552 }
3553
3554 CHECK(receiver_map.IsJSReceiverMap())do { if ((__builtin_expect(!!(!(receiver_map.IsJSReceiverMap(
))), 0))) { V8_Fatal("Check failed: %s.", "receiver_map.IsJSReceiverMap()"
); } } while (false);
3555 CHECK(!receiver_map.is_access_check_needed() ||do { if ((__builtin_expect(!!(!(!receiver_map.is_access_check_needed
() || function_template_info.accept_any_receiver())), 0))) { V8_Fatal
("Check failed: %s.", "!receiver_map.is_access_check_needed() || function_template_info.accept_any_receiver()"
); } } while (false)
3556 function_template_info.accept_any_receiver())do { if ((__builtin_expect(!!(!(!receiver_map.is_access_check_needed
() || function_template_info.accept_any_receiver())), 0))) { V8_Fatal
("Check failed: %s.", "!receiver_map.is_access_check_needed() || function_template_info.accept_any_receiver()"
); } } while (false);
3557 }
3558
3559 if (p.speculation_mode() == SpeculationMode::kDisallowSpeculation &&
3560 !inference.RelyOnMapsViaStability(dependencies())) {
3561 // We were not able to make the receiver maps reliable without map
3562 // checks but doing map checks would lead to deopt loops, so give up.
3563 return inference.NoChange();
3564 }
3565
3566 // TODO(neis): The maps were used in a way that does not actually require
3567 // map checks or stability dependencies.
3568 inference.RelyOnMapsPreferStability(dependencies(), jsgraph(), &effect,
3569 control, p.feedback());
3570
3571 // Determine the appropriate holder for the {lookup}.
3572 holder = api_holder.lookup == CallOptimization::kHolderFound
3573 ? jsgraph()->Constant(*api_holder.holder)
3574 : receiver;
3575 } else {
3576 // We don't have enough information to eliminate the access check
3577 // and/or the compatible receiver check, so use the generic builtin
3578 // that does those checks dynamically. This is still significantly
3579 // faster than the generic call sequence.
3580 Builtins::Name builtin_name;
3581 if (function_template_info.accept_any_receiver()) {
3582 builtin_name = Builtins::kCallFunctionTemplate_CheckCompatibleReceiver;
3583 } else if (function_template_info.is_signature_undefined()) {
3584 builtin_name = Builtins::kCallFunctionTemplate_CheckAccess;
3585 } else {
3586 builtin_name =
3587 Builtins::kCallFunctionTemplate_CheckAccessAndCompatibleReceiver;
3588 }
3589
3590 // The CallFunctionTemplate builtin requires the {receiver} to be
3591 // an actual JSReceiver, so make sure we do the proper conversion
3592 // first if necessary.
3593 receiver = holder = effect =
Although the value stored to 'holder' is used in the enclosing expression, the value is never actually read from 'holder'
3594 graph()->NewNode(simplified()->ConvertReceiver(p.convert_mode()),
3595 receiver, global_proxy, effect, control);
3596
3597 Callable callable = Builtins::CallableFor(isolate(), builtin_name);
3598 auto call_descriptor = Linkage::GetStubCallDescriptor(
3599 graph()->zone(), callable.descriptor(),
3600 argc + 1 /* implicit receiver */, CallDescriptor::kNeedsFrameState);
3601 node->RemoveInput(n.FeedbackVectorIndex());
3602 node->InsertInput(graph()->zone(), 0,
3603 jsgraph()->HeapConstant(callable.code()));
3604 node->ReplaceInput(1, jsgraph()->Constant(function_template_info));
3605 node->InsertInput(graph()->zone(), 2, jsgraph()->Constant(argc));
3606 node->ReplaceInput(3, receiver); // Update receiver input.
3607 node->ReplaceInput(6 + argc, effect); // Update effect input.
3608 NodeProperties::ChangeOp(node, common()->Call(call_descriptor));
3609 return Changed(node);
3610 }
3611 }
3612
3613 // TODO(turbofan): Consider introducing a JSCallApiCallback operator for
3614 // this and lower it during JSGenericLowering, and unify this with the
3615 // JSNativeContextSpecialization::InlineApiCall method a bit.
3616 if (!function_template_info.call_code().has_value()) {
3617 TRACE_BROKER_MISSING(broker(), "call code for function template info "do { if (broker()->tracing_enabled()) StdoutStream{} <<
broker()->Trace() << "Missing " << "call code for function template info "
<< function_template_info << " (" << "../deps/v8/src/compiler/js-call-reducer.cc"
<< ":" << 3618 << ")" << std::endl; }
while (false)
3618 << function_template_info)do { if (broker()->tracing_enabled()) StdoutStream{} <<
broker()->Trace() << "Missing " << "call code for function template info "
<< function_template_info << " (" << "../deps/v8/src/compiler/js-call-reducer.cc"
<< ":" << 3618 << ")" << std::endl; }
while (false);
3619 return NoChange();
3620 }
3621
3622 Address c_function = function_template_info.c_function();
3623
3624 if (FLAG_turbo_fast_api_calls && c_function != kNullAddress) {
3625 const CFunctionInfo* c_signature = function_template_info.c_signature();
3626 FastApiCallReducerAssembler a(jsgraph(), graph()->zone(), node, c_function,
3627 c_signature, function_template_info, receiver,
3628 holder, shared, target, argc, effect);
3629 Node* fast_call_subgraph = a.ReduceFastApiCall();
3630 ReplaceWithSubgraph(&a, fast_call_subgraph);
3631
3632 return Replace(fast_call_subgraph);
3633 }
3634
3635 CallHandlerInfoRef call_handler_info = *function_template_info.call_code();
3636 Callable call_api_callback = CodeFactory::CallApiCallback(isolate());
3637 CallInterfaceDescriptor cid = call_api_callback.descriptor();
3638 auto call_descriptor =
3639 Linkage::GetStubCallDescriptor(graph()->zone(), cid, argc + 1 /*
3640 implicit receiver */, CallDescriptor::kNeedsFrameState);
3641 ApiFunction api_function(call_handler_info.callback());
3642 ExternalReference function_reference = ExternalReference::Create(
3643 &api_function, ExternalReference::DIRECT_API_CALL);
3644
3645 Node* continuation_frame_state = CreateGenericLazyDeoptContinuationFrameState(
3646 jsgraph(), shared, target, context, receiver, frame_state);
3647
3648 node->RemoveInput(n.FeedbackVectorIndex());
3649 node->InsertInput(graph()->zone(), 0,
3650 jsgraph()->HeapConstant(call_api_callback.code()));
3651 node->ReplaceInput(1, jsgraph()->ExternalConstant(function_reference));
3652 node->InsertInput(graph()->zone(), 2, jsgraph()->Constant(argc));
3653 node->InsertInput(graph()->zone(), 3,
3654 jsgraph()->Constant(call_handler_info.data()));
3655 node->InsertInput(graph()->zone(), 4, holder);
3656 node->ReplaceInput(5, receiver); // Update receiver input.
3657 // 6 + argc is context input.
3658 node->ReplaceInput(6 + argc + 1, continuation_frame_state);
3659 node->ReplaceInput(6 + argc + 2, effect);
3660 NodeProperties::ChangeOp(node, common()->Call(call_descriptor));
3661 return Changed(node);
3662}
3663
3664namespace {
3665
3666// Check whether elements aren't mutated; we play it extremely safe here by
3667// explicitly checking that {node} is only used by {LoadField} or
3668// {LoadElement}.
3669bool IsSafeArgumentsElements(Node* node) {
3670 for (Edge const edge : node->use_edges()) {
3671 if (!NodeProperties::IsValueEdge(edge)) continue;
3672 if (edge.from()->opcode() != IrOpcode::kLoadField &&
3673 edge.from()->opcode() != IrOpcode::kLoadElement) {
3674 return false;
3675 }
3676 }
3677 return true;
3678}
3679
3680#ifdef DEBUG
3681bool IsCallOrConstructWithArrayLike(Node* node) {
3682 return node->opcode() == IrOpcode::kJSCallWithArrayLike ||
3683 node->opcode() == IrOpcode::kJSConstructWithArrayLike;
3684}
3685#endif
3686
3687bool IsCallOrConstructWithSpread(Node* node) {
3688 return node->opcode() == IrOpcode::kJSCallWithSpread ||
3689 node->opcode() == IrOpcode::kJSConstructWithSpread;
3690}
3691
3692bool IsCallWithArrayLikeOrSpread(Node* node) {
3693 return node->opcode() == IrOpcode::kJSCallWithArrayLike ||
3694 node->opcode() == IrOpcode::kJSCallWithSpread;
3695}
3696
3697} // namespace
3698
3699Reduction JSCallReducer::ReduceCallOrConstructWithArrayLikeOrSpread(
3700 Node* node, int arraylike_or_spread_index, CallFrequency const& frequency,
3701 FeedbackSource const& feedback, SpeculationMode speculation_mode,
3702 CallFeedbackRelation feedback_relation) {
3703 DCHECK(IsCallOrConstructWithArrayLike(node) ||((void) 0)
3704 IsCallOrConstructWithSpread(node))((void) 0);
3705 DCHECK_IMPLIES(speculation_mode == SpeculationMode::kAllowSpeculation,((void) 0)
3706 feedback.IsValid())((void) 0);
3707
3708 Node* arguments_list =
3709 NodeProperties::GetValueInput(node, arraylike_or_spread_index);
3710 if (arguments_list->opcode() != IrOpcode::kJSCreateArguments) {
3711 return NoChange();
3712 }
3713
3714 // Check if {node} is the only value user of {arguments_list} (except for
3715 // value uses in frame states). If not, we give up for now.
3716 for (Edge edge : arguments_list->use_edges()) {
3717 if (!NodeProperties::IsValueEdge(edge)) continue;
3718 Node* const user = edge.from();
3719 switch (user->opcode()) {
3720 case IrOpcode::kCheckMaps:
3721 case IrOpcode::kFrameState:
3722 case IrOpcode::kStateValues:
3723 case IrOpcode::kReferenceEqual:
3724 case IrOpcode::kReturn:
3725 // Ignore safe uses that definitely don't mess with the arguments.
3726 continue;
3727 case IrOpcode::kLoadField: {
3728 DCHECK_EQ(arguments_list, user->InputAt(0))((void) 0);
3729 FieldAccess const& access = FieldAccessOf(user->op());
3730 if (access.offset == JSArray::kLengthOffset) {
3731 // Ignore uses for arguments#length.
3732 STATIC_ASSERT(static_assert(static_cast<int>(JSArray::kLengthOffset) ==
static_cast<int>(JSStrictArgumentsObject::kLengthOffset
), "static_cast<int>(JSArray::kLengthOffset) == static_cast<int>(JSStrictArgumentsObject::kLengthOffset)"
)
3733 static_cast<int>(JSArray::kLengthOffset) ==static_assert(static_cast<int>(JSArray::kLengthOffset) ==
static_cast<int>(JSStrictArgumentsObject::kLengthOffset
), "static_cast<int>(JSArray::kLengthOffset) == static_cast<int>(JSStrictArgumentsObject::kLengthOffset)"
)
3734 static_cast<int>(JSStrictArgumentsObject::kLengthOffset))static_assert(static_cast<int>(JSArray::kLengthOffset) ==
static_cast<int>(JSStrictArgumentsObject::kLengthOffset
), "static_cast<int>(JSArray::kLengthOffset) == static_cast<int>(JSStrictArgumentsObject::kLengthOffset)"
);
3735 STATIC_ASSERT(static_assert(static_cast<int>(JSArray::kLengthOffset) ==
static_cast<int>(JSSloppyArgumentsObject::kLengthOffset
), "static_cast<int>(JSArray::kLengthOffset) == static_cast<int>(JSSloppyArgumentsObject::kLengthOffset)"
)
3736 static_cast<int>(JSArray::kLengthOffset) ==static_assert(static_cast<int>(JSArray::kLengthOffset) ==
static_cast<int>(JSSloppyArgumentsObject::kLengthOffset
), "static_cast<int>(JSArray::kLengthOffset) == static_cast<int>(JSSloppyArgumentsObject::kLengthOffset)"
)
3737 static_cast<int>(JSSloppyArgumentsObject::kLengthOffset))static_assert(static_cast<int>(JSArray::kLengthOffset) ==
static_cast<int>(JSSloppyArgumentsObject::kLengthOffset
), "static_cast<int>(JSArray::kLengthOffset) == static_cast<int>(JSSloppyArgumentsObject::kLengthOffset)"
);
3738 continue;
3739 } else if (access.offset == JSObject::kElementsOffset) {
3740 // Ignore safe uses for arguments#elements.
3741 if (IsSafeArgumentsElements(user)) continue;
3742 }
3743 break;
3744 }
3745 case IrOpcode::kJSCallWithArrayLike: {
3746 // Ignore uses as argumentsList input to calls with array like.
3747 JSCallWithArrayLikeNode n(user);
3748 if (n.Argument(0) == arguments_list) continue;
3749 break;
3750 }
3751 case IrOpcode::kJSConstructWithArrayLike: {
3752 // Ignore uses as argumentsList input to calls with array like.
3753 JSConstructWithArrayLikeNode n(user);
3754 if (n.Argument(0) == arguments_list) continue;
3755 break;
3756 }
3757 case IrOpcode::kJSCallWithSpread: {
3758 // Ignore uses as spread input to calls with spread.
3759 JSCallWithSpreadNode n(user);
3760 if (n.LastArgument() == arguments_list) continue;
3761 break;
3762 }
3763 case IrOpcode::kJSConstructWithSpread: {
3764 // Ignore uses as spread input to construct with spread.
3765 JSConstructWithSpreadNode n(user);
3766 if (n.LastArgument() == arguments_list) continue;
3767 break;
3768 }
3769 default:
3770 break;
3771 }
3772 // We cannot currently reduce the {node} to something better than what
3773 // it already is, but we might be able to do something about the {node}
3774 // later, so put it on the waitlist and try again during finalization.
3775 waitlist_.insert(node);
3776 return NoChange();
3777 }
3778
3779 // Get to the actual frame state from which to extract the arguments;
3780 // we can only optimize this in case the {node} was already inlined into
3781 // some other function (and same for the {arguments_list}).
3782 CreateArgumentsType const type = CreateArgumentsTypeOf(arguments_list->op());
3783 Node* frame_state = NodeProperties::GetFrameStateInput(arguments_list);
3784 FrameStateInfo state_info = FrameStateInfoOf(frame_state->op());
3785 int start_index = 0;
3786
3787 int formal_parameter_count;
3788 {
3789 Handle<SharedFunctionInfo> shared;
3790 if (!state_info.shared_info().ToHandle(&shared)) return NoChange();
3791 formal_parameter_count = SharedFunctionInfoRef(broker(), shared)
3792 .internal_formal_parameter_count();
3793 }
3794
3795 if (type == CreateArgumentsType::kMappedArguments) {
3796 // Mapped arguments (sloppy mode) that are aliased can only be handled
3797 // here if there's no side-effect between the {node} and the {arg_array}.
3798 // TODO(turbofan): Further relax this constraint.
3799 if (formal_parameter_count != 0) {
3800 Node* effect = NodeProperties::GetEffectInput(node);
3801 if (!NodeProperties::NoObservableSideEffectBetween(effect,
3802 arguments_list)) {
3803 return NoChange();
3804 }
3805 }
3806 } else if (type == CreateArgumentsType::kRestParameter) {
3807 start_index = formal_parameter_count;
3808 }
3809
3810 // TODO(jgruber,v8:8888): Attempt to remove this restriction. The reason it
3811 // currently exists is because we cannot create code dependencies in NCI code.
3812 if (broker()->is_native_context_independent()) return NoChange();
3813
3814 // For call/construct with spread, we need to also install a code
3815 // dependency on the array iterator lookup protector cell to ensure
3816 // that no one messed with the %ArrayIteratorPrototype%.next method.
3817 if (IsCallOrConstructWithSpread(node)) {
3818 if (!dependencies()->DependOnArrayIteratorProtector()) return NoChange();
3819 }
3820
3821 // Remove the {arguments_list} input from the {node}.
3822 node->RemoveInput(arraylike_or_spread_index);
3823
3824 // After removing the arraylike or spread object, the argument count is:
3825 int argc =
3826 arraylike_or_spread_index - JSCallOrConstructNode::FirstArgumentIndex();
3827 // Check if are spreading to inlined arguments or to the arguments of
3828 // the outermost function.
3829 Node* outer_state = frame_state->InputAt(kFrameStateOuterStateInput);
3830 if (outer_state->opcode() != IrOpcode::kFrameState) {
3831 Operator const* op;
3832 if (IsCallWithArrayLikeOrSpread(node)) {
3833 static constexpr int kTargetAndReceiver = 2;
3834 op = javascript()->CallForwardVarargs(argc + kTargetAndReceiver,
3835 start_index);
3836 } else {
3837 static constexpr int kTargetAndNewTarget = 2;
3838 op = javascript()->ConstructForwardVarargs(argc + kTargetAndNewTarget,
3839 start_index);
3840 }
3841 node->RemoveInput(JSCallOrConstructNode::FeedbackVectorIndexForArgc(argc));
3842 NodeProperties::ChangeOp(node, op);
3843 return Changed(node);
3844 }
3845 // Get to the actual frame state from which to extract the arguments;
3846 // we can only optimize this in case the {node} was already inlined into
3847 // some other function (and same for the {arg_array}).
3848 FrameStateInfo outer_info = FrameStateInfoOf(outer_state->op());
3849 if (outer_info.type() == FrameStateType::kArgumentsAdaptor) {
3850 // Need to take the parameters from the arguments adaptor.
3851 frame_state = outer_state;
3852 }
3853 // Add the actual parameters to the {node}, skipping the receiver.
3854 Node* const parameters = frame_state->InputAt(kFrameStateParametersInput);
3855 for (int i = start_index + 1; i < parameters->InputCount(); ++i) {
3856 node->InsertInput(graph()->zone(),
3857 JSCallOrConstructNode::ArgumentIndex(argc++),
3858 parameters->InputAt(i));
3859 }
3860
3861 if (IsCallWithArrayLikeOrSpread(node)) {
3862 NodeProperties::ChangeOp(
3863 node,
3864 javascript()->Call(JSCallNode::ArityForArgc(argc), frequency, feedback,
3865 ConvertReceiverMode::kAny, speculation_mode,
3866 CallFeedbackRelation::kUnrelated));
3867 return Changed(node).FollowedBy(ReduceJSCall(node));
3868 } else {
3869 NodeProperties::ChangeOp(
3870 node, javascript()->Construct(JSConstructNode::ArityForArgc(argc),
3871 frequency, feedback));
3872
3873 JSConstructNode n(node);
3874 Node* new_target = n.new_target();
3875 FrameState frame_state = n.frame_state();
3876 Node* context = n.context();
3877 Effect effect = n.effect();
3878 Control control = n.control();
3879
3880 // Check whether the given new target value is a constructor function. The
3881 // replacement {JSConstruct} operator only checks the passed target value
3882 // but relies on the new target value to be implicitly valid.
3883 Node* check =
3884 graph()->NewNode(simplified()->ObjectIsConstructor(), new_target);
3885 Node* check_branch =
3886 graph()->NewNode(common()->Branch(BranchHint::kTrue), check, control);
3887 Node* check_fail = graph()->NewNode(common()->IfFalse(), check_branch);
3888 Node* check_throw = check_fail = graph()->NewNode(
3889 javascript()->CallRuntime(Runtime::kThrowTypeError, 2),
3890 jsgraph()->Constant(static_cast<int>(MessageTemplate::kNotConstructor)),
3891 new_target, context, frame_state, effect, check_fail);
3892 control = graph()->NewNode(common()->IfTrue(), check_branch);
3893 NodeProperties::ReplaceControlInput(node, control);
3894
3895 // Rewire potential exception edges.
3896 Node* on_exception = nullptr;
3897 if (NodeProperties::IsExceptionalCall(node, &on_exception)) {
3898 // Create appropriate {IfException} and {IfSuccess} nodes.
3899 Node* if_exception =
3900 graph()->NewNode(common()->IfException(), check_throw, check_fail);
3901 check_fail = graph()->NewNode(common()->IfSuccess(), check_fail);
3902
3903 // Join the exception edges.
3904 Node* merge =
3905 graph()->NewNode(common()->Merge(2), if_exception, on_exception);
3906 Node* ephi = graph()->NewNode(common()->EffectPhi(2), if_exception,
3907 on_exception, merge);
3908 Node* phi =
3909 graph()->NewNode(common()->Phi(MachineRepresentation::kTagged, 2),
3910 if_exception, on_exception, merge);
3911 ReplaceWithValue(on_exception, phi, ephi, merge);
3912 merge->ReplaceInput(1, on_exception);
3913 ephi->ReplaceInput(1, on_exception);
3914 phi->ReplaceInput(1, on_exception);
3915 }
3916
3917 // The above %ThrowTypeError runtime call is an unconditional throw,
3918 // making it impossible to return a successful completion in this case. We
3919 // simply connect the successful completion to the graph end.
3920 Node* throw_node =
3921 graph()->NewNode(common()->Throw(), check_throw, check_fail);
3922 NodeProperties::MergeControlToEnd(graph(), common(), throw_node);
3923
3924 return Changed(node).FollowedBy(ReduceJSConstruct(node));
3925 }
3926}
3927
3928namespace {
3929
3930bool ShouldUseCallICFeedback(Node* node) {
3931 HeapObjectMatcher m(node);
3932 if (m.HasValue() || m.IsCheckClosure() || m.IsJSCreateClosure()) {
3933 // Don't use CallIC feedback when we know the function
3934 // being called, i.e. either know the closure itself or
3935 // at least the SharedFunctionInfo.
3936 return false;
3937 } else if (m.IsPhi()) {
3938 // Protect against endless loops here.
3939 Node* control = NodeProperties::GetControlInput(node);
3940 if (control->opcode() == IrOpcode::kLoop) return false;
3941 // Check if {node} is a Phi of nodes which shouldn't
3942 // use CallIC feedback (not looking through loops).
3943 int const value_input_count = m.node()->op()->ValueInputCount();
3944 for (int n = 0; n < value_input_count; ++n) {
3945 if (ShouldUseCallICFeedback(node->InputAt(n))) return true;
3946 }
3947 return false;
3948 }
3949 return true;
3950}
3951
3952} // namespace
3953
3954bool JSCallReducer::IsBuiltinOrApiFunction(JSFunctionRef function) const {
3955 if (should_disallow_heap_access() && !function.serialized()) {
3956 TRACE_BROKER_MISSING(broker(), "data for function " << function)do { if (broker()->tracing_enabled()) StdoutStream{} <<
broker()->Trace() << "Missing " << "data for function "
<< function << " (" << "../deps/v8/src/compiler/js-call-reducer.cc"
<< ":" << 3956 << ")" << std::endl; }
while (false);
3957 return false;
3958 }
3959
3960 // TODO(neis): Add a way to check if function template info isn't serialized
3961 // and add a warning in such cases. Currently we can't tell if function
3962 // template info doesn't exist or wasn't serialized.
3963 return function.shared().HasBuiltinId() ||
3964 function.shared().function_template_info().has_value();
3965}
3966
3967Reduction JSCallReducer::ReduceJSCall(Node* node) {
3968 JSCallNode n(node);
3969 CallParameters const& p = n.Parameters();
3970 Node* target = n.target();
3971 Effect effect = n.effect();
3972 Control control = n.control();
3973 int arity = p.arity_without_implicit_args();
3974
3975 // Try to specialize JSCall {node}s with constant {target}s.
3976 HeapObjectMatcher m(target);
3977 if (m.HasValue()) {
3978 ObjectRef target_ref = m.Ref(broker());
3979 if (target_ref.IsJSFunction()) {
3980 JSFunctionRef function = target_ref.AsJSFunction();
3981 if (should_disallow_heap_access() && !function.serialized()) {
3982 TRACE_BROKER_MISSING(broker(), "data for function " << function)do { if (broker()->tracing_enabled()) StdoutStream{} <<
broker()->Trace() << "Missing " << "data for function "
<< function << " (" << "../deps/v8/src/compiler/js-call-reducer.cc"
<< ":" << 3982 << ")" << std::endl; }
while (false);
3983 return NoChange();
3984 }
3985
3986 // Don't inline cross native context.
3987 if (!function.native_context().equals(native_context())) {
3988 return NoChange();
3989 }
3990
3991 return ReduceJSCall(node, function.shared());
3992 } else if (target_ref.IsJSBoundFunction()) {
3993 JSBoundFunctionRef function = target_ref.AsJSBoundFunction();
3994 if (should_disallow_heap_access() && !function.serialized()) {
3995 TRACE_BROKER_MISSING(broker(), "data for function " << function)do { if (broker()->tracing_enabled()) StdoutStream{} <<
broker()->Trace() << "Missing " << "data for function "
<< function << " (" << "../deps/v8/src/compiler/js-call-reducer.cc"
<< ":" << 3995 << ")" << std::endl; }
while (false);
3996 return NoChange();
3997 }
3998
3999 ObjectRef bound_this = function.bound_this();
4000 ConvertReceiverMode const convert_mode =
4001 bound_this.IsNullOrUndefined()
4002 ? ConvertReceiverMode::kNullOrUndefined
4003 : ConvertReceiverMode::kNotNullOrUndefined;
4004
4005 // Patch {node} to use [[BoundTargetFunction]] and [[BoundThis]].
4006 NodeProperties::ReplaceValueInput(
4007 node, jsgraph()->Constant(function.bound_target_function()),
4008 JSCallNode::TargetIndex());
4009 NodeProperties::ReplaceValueInput(node, jsgraph()->Constant(bound_this),
4010 JSCallNode::ReceiverIndex());
4011
4012 // Insert the [[BoundArguments]] for {node}.
4013 FixedArrayRef bound_arguments = function.bound_arguments();
4014 for (int i = 0; i < bound_arguments.length(); ++i) {
4015 node->InsertInput(graph()->zone(), i + 2,
4016 jsgraph()->Constant(bound_arguments.get(i)));
4017 arity++;
4018 }
4019
4020 NodeProperties::ChangeOp(
4021 node,
4022 javascript()->Call(JSCallNode::ArityForArgc(arity), p.frequency(),
4023 p.feedback(), convert_mode, p.speculation_mode(),
4024 CallFeedbackRelation::kUnrelated));
4025
4026 // Try to further reduce the JSCall {node}.
4027 return Changed(node).FollowedBy(ReduceJSCall(node));
4028 }
4029
4030 // Don't mess with other {node}s that have a constant {target}.
4031 // TODO(bmeurer): Also support proxies here.
4032 return NoChange();
4033 }
4034
4035 // If {target} is the result of a JSCreateClosure operation, we can
4036 // just immediately try to inline based on the SharedFunctionInfo,
4037 // since TurboFan generally doesn't inline cross-context, and hence
4038 // the {target} must have the same native context as the call site.
4039 // Same if the {target} is the result of a CheckClosure operation.
4040 if (target->opcode() == IrOpcode::kJSCreateClosure) {
4041 CreateClosureParameters const& p = JSCreateClosureNode{target}.Parameters();
4042 return ReduceJSCall(node, SharedFunctionInfoRef(broker(), p.shared_info()));
4043 } else if (target->opcode() == IrOpcode::kCheckClosure) {
4044 FeedbackCellRef cell(broker(), FeedbackCellOf(target->op()));
4045 return ReduceJSCall(node,
4046 cell.value().AsFeedbackVector().shared_function_info());
4047 }
4048
4049 // If {target} is the result of a JSCreateBoundFunction operation,
4050 // we can just fold the construction and call the bound target
4051 // function directly instead.
4052 if (target->opcode() == IrOpcode::kJSCreateBoundFunction) {
4053 Node* bound_target_function = NodeProperties::GetValueInput(target, 0);
4054 Node* bound_this = NodeProperties::GetValueInput(target, 1);
4055 int const bound_arguments_length =
4056 static_cast<int>(CreateBoundFunctionParametersOf(target->op()).arity());
4057
4058 // Patch the {node} to use [[BoundTargetFunction]] and [[BoundThis]].
4059 NodeProperties::ReplaceValueInput(node, bound_target_function,
4060 n.TargetIndex());
4061 NodeProperties::ReplaceValueInput(node, bound_this, n.ReceiverIndex());
4062
4063 // Insert the [[BoundArguments]] for {node}.
4064 for (int i = 0; i < bound_arguments_length; ++i) {
4065 Node* value = NodeProperties::GetValueInput(target, 2 + i);
4066 node->InsertInput(graph()->zone(), n.ArgumentIndex(i), value);
4067 arity++;
4068 }
4069
4070 // Update the JSCall operator on {node}.
4071 ConvertReceiverMode const convert_mode =
4072 NodeProperties::CanBeNullOrUndefined(broker(), bound_this, effect)
4073 ? ConvertReceiverMode::kAny
4074 : ConvertReceiverMode::kNotNullOrUndefined;
4075 NodeProperties::ChangeOp(
4076 node,
4077 javascript()->Call(JSCallNode::ArityForArgc(arity), p.frequency(),
4078 p.feedback(), convert_mode, p.speculation_mode(),
4079 CallFeedbackRelation::kUnrelated));
4080
4081 // Try to further reduce the JSCall {node}.
4082 return Changed(node).FollowedBy(ReduceJSCall(node));
4083 }
4084
4085 if (!ShouldUseCallICFeedback(target) ||
4086 p.feedback_relation() != CallFeedbackRelation::kRelated ||
4087 !p.feedback().IsValid()) {
4088 return NoChange();
4089 }
4090
4091 ProcessedFeedback const& feedback =
4092 broker()->GetFeedbackForCall(p.feedback());
4093 if (feedback.IsInsufficient()) {
4094 return ReduceForInsufficientFeedback(
4095 node, DeoptimizeReason::kInsufficientTypeFeedbackForCall);
4096 }
4097
4098 base::Optional<HeapObjectRef> feedback_target = feedback.AsCall().target();
4099 if (feedback_target.has_value() && feedback_target->map().is_callable()) {
4100 Node* target_function = jsgraph()->Constant(*feedback_target);
4101
4102 if (FLAG_turboprop) {
4103 if (!feedback_target->IsJSFunction()) return NoChange();
4104 if (!IsBuiltinOrApiFunction(feedback_target->AsJSFunction())) {
4105 return NoChange();
4106 }
4107 }
4108
4109 // Check that the {target} is still the {target_function}.
4110 Node* check = graph()->NewNode(simplified()->ReferenceEqual(), target,
4111 target_function);
4112 effect = graph()->NewNode(
4113 simplified()->CheckIf(DeoptimizeReason::kWrongCallTarget), check,
4114 effect, control);
4115
4116 // Specialize the JSCall node to the {target_function}.
4117 NodeProperties::ReplaceValueInput(node, target_function, n.TargetIndex());
4118 NodeProperties::ReplaceEffectInput(node, effect);
4119
4120 // Try to further reduce the JSCall {node}.
4121 return Changed(node).FollowedBy(ReduceJSCall(node));
4122 } else if (feedback_target.has_value() && feedback_target->IsFeedbackCell()) {
4123 FeedbackCellRef feedback_cell(
4124 broker(), feedback_target.value().AsFeedbackCell().object());
4125 if (feedback_cell.value().IsFeedbackVector()) {
4126 // Check that {target} is a closure with given {feedback_cell},
4127 // which uniquely identifies a given function inside a native context.
4128 FeedbackVectorRef feedback_vector =
4129 feedback_cell.value().AsFeedbackVector();
4130 if (!feedback_vector.serialized()) {
4131 TRACE_BROKER_MISSING(do { if (broker()->tracing_enabled()) StdoutStream{} <<
broker()->Trace() << "Missing " << "feedback vector, not serialized: "
<< feedback_vector << " (" << "../deps/v8/src/compiler/js-call-reducer.cc"
<< ":" << 4132 << ")" << std::endl; }
while (false)
4132 broker(), "feedback vector, not serialized: " << feedback_vector)do { if (broker()->tracing_enabled()) StdoutStream{} <<
broker()->Trace() << "Missing " << "feedback vector, not serialized: "
<< feedback_vector << " (" << "../deps/v8/src/compiler/js-call-reducer.cc"
<< ":" << 4132 << ")" << std::endl; }
while (false);
4133 return NoChange();
4134 }
4135
4136 if (FLAG_turboprop &&
4137 !feedback_vector.shared_function_info().HasBuiltinId()) {
4138 return NoChange();
4139 }
4140
4141 Node* target_closure = effect =
4142 graph()->NewNode(simplified()->CheckClosure(feedback_cell.object()),
4143 target, effect, control);
4144
4145 // Specialize the JSCall node to the {target_closure}.
4146 NodeProperties::ReplaceValueInput(node, target_closure, n.TargetIndex());
4147 NodeProperties::ReplaceEffectInput(node, effect);
4148
4149 // Try to further reduce the JSCall {node}.
4150 return Changed(node).FollowedBy(ReduceJSCall(node));
4151 }
4152 }
4153 return NoChange();
4154}
4155
4156Reduction JSCallReducer::ReduceJSCall(Node* node,
4157 const SharedFunctionInfoRef& shared) {
4158 JSCallNode n(node);
4159 Node* target = n.target();
4160
4161 // Do not reduce calls to functions with break points.
4162 if (shared.HasBreakInfo()) return NoChange();
4163
4164 // Raise a TypeError if the {target} is a "classConstructor".
4165 if (IsClassConstructor(shared.kind())) {
4166 NodeProperties::ReplaceValueInputs(node, target);
4167 NodeProperties::ChangeOp(
4168 node, javascript()->CallRuntime(
4169 Runtime::kThrowConstructorNonCallableError, 1));
4170 return Changed(node);
4171 }
4172
4173 // Check for known builtin functions.
4174
4175 int builtin_id =
4176 shared.HasBuiltinId() ? shared.builtin_id() : Builtins::kNoBuiltinId;
4177 switch (builtin_id) {
4178 case Builtins::kArrayConstructor:
4179 return ReduceArrayConstructor(node);
4180 case Builtins::kBooleanConstructor:
4181 return ReduceBooleanConstructor(node);
4182 case Builtins::kFunctionPrototypeApply:
4183 return ReduceFunctionPrototypeApply(node);
4184 case Builtins::kFastFunctionPrototypeBind:
4185 return ReduceFunctionPrototypeBind(node);
4186 case Builtins::kFunctionPrototypeCall:
4187 return ReduceFunctionPrototypeCall(node);
4188 case Builtins::kFunctionPrototypeHasInstance:
4189 return ReduceFunctionPrototypeHasInstance(node);
4190 case Builtins::kObjectConstructor:
4191 return ReduceObjectConstructor(node);
4192 case Builtins::kObjectCreate:
4193 return ReduceObjectCreate(node);
4194 case Builtins::kObjectGetPrototypeOf:
4195 return ReduceObjectGetPrototypeOf(node);
4196 case Builtins::kObjectIs:
4197 return ReduceObjectIs(node);
4198 case Builtins::kObjectPrototypeGetProto:
4199 return ReduceObjectPrototypeGetProto(node);
4200 case Builtins::kObjectPrototypeHasOwnProperty:
4201 return ReduceObjectPrototypeHasOwnProperty(node);
4202 case Builtins::kObjectPrototypeIsPrototypeOf:
4203 return ReduceObjectPrototypeIsPrototypeOf(node);
4204 case Builtins::kReflectApply:
4205 return ReduceReflectApply(node);
4206 case Builtins::kReflectConstruct:
4207 return ReduceReflectConstruct(node);
4208 case Builtins::kReflectGet:
4209 return ReduceReflectGet(node);
4210 case Builtins::kReflectGetPrototypeOf:
4211 return ReduceReflectGetPrototypeOf(node);
4212 case Builtins::kReflectHas:
4213 return ReduceReflectHas(node);
4214 case Builtins::kArrayForEach:
4215 return ReduceArrayForEach(node, shared);
4216 case Builtins::kArrayMap:
4217 return ReduceArrayMap(node, shared);
4218 case Builtins::kArrayFilter:
4219 return ReduceArrayFilter(node, shared);
4220 case Builtins::kArrayReduce:
4221 return ReduceArrayReduce(node, shared);
4222 case Builtins::kArrayReduceRight:
4223 return ReduceArrayReduceRight(node, shared);
4224 case Builtins::kArrayPrototypeFind:
4225 return ReduceArrayFind(node, shared);
4226 case Builtins::kArrayPrototypeFindIndex:
4227 return ReduceArrayFindIndex(node, shared);
4228 case Builtins::kArrayEvery:
4229 return ReduceArrayEvery(node, shared);
4230 case Builtins::kArrayIndexOf:
4231 return ReduceArrayIndexOf(node);
4232 case Builtins::kArrayIncludes:
4233 return ReduceArrayIncludes(node);

4235 return ReduceArraySome(node, shared);

4249 IterationKind::kKeys);
4250 case Builtins::kArrayPrototypeValues:
4251 return ReduceArrayIterator(node, ArrayIteratorKind::kArrayLike,
4252 IterationKind::kValues);
4253 case Builtins::kArrayIteratorPrototypeNext:
4254 return ReduceArrayIteratorPrototypeNext(node);
4255 case Builtins::kArrayIsArray:

4386 case Builtins::kMathClz32:

4390 case Builtins::kMathMax:

4392 jsgraph()->Constant(-V8_INFINITYstd::numeric_limits<double>::infinity()));
4393 case Builtins::kMathMin:

4395 jsgraph()->Constant(V8_INFINITYstd::numeric_limits<double>::infinity()));
4396 case Builtins::kNumberIsFinite:

4398 case Builtins::kNumberIsInteger:

4400 case Builtins::kNumberIsSafeInteger:

4442 case Builtins::kStringFromCharCode:

4531
4532Reduction JSCallReducer::ReduceJSConstruct(Node* node) {
4533 JSConstructNode n(node);
4534 ConstructParameters const& p = n.Parameters();
4535 int arity = p.arity_without_implicit_args();
4536 Node* target = n.target();
4537 Node* new_target = n.new_target();
4538 Effect effect = n.effect();
4539 Control control = n.control();
4540
4541 if (p.feedback().IsValid()) {
4542 ProcessedFeedback const& feedback =
4543 broker()->GetFeedbackForCall(p.feedback());
4544 if (feedback.IsInsufficient()) {
4545 return ReduceForInsufficientFeedback(
4546 node, DeoptimizeReason::kInsufficientTypeFeedbackForConstruct);
4547 }
4548
4549 base::Optional<HeapObjectRef> feedback_target = feedback.AsCall().target();
4550 if (feedback_target.has_value() && feedback_target->IsAllocationSite()) {
4551 // The feedback is an AllocationSite, which means we have called the
4552 // Array function and collected transition (and pretenuring) feedback
4553 // for the resulting arrays. This has to be kept in sync with the
4554 // implementation in Ignition.
4555
4556 Node* array_function =
4557 jsgraph()->Constant(native_context().array_function());
4558
4559 // Check that the {target} is still the {array_function}.
4560 Node* check = graph()->NewNode(simplified()->ReferenceEqual(), target,
4561 array_function);
4562 effect = graph()->NewNode(
4563 simplified()->CheckIf(DeoptimizeReason::kWrongCallTarget), check,
4564 effect, control);
4565
4566 // Turn the {node} into a {JSCreateArray} call.
4567 NodeProperties::ReplaceEffectInput(node, effect);
4568 STATIC_ASSERT(JSConstructNode::NewTargetIndex() == 1)static_assert(JSConstructNode::NewTargetIndex() == 1, "JSConstructNode::NewTargetIndex() == 1"
);
4569 node->ReplaceInput(n.NewTargetIndex(), array_function);
4570 node->RemoveInput(n.FeedbackVectorIndex());
4571 NodeProperties::ChangeOp(
4572 node, javascript()->CreateArray(
4573 arity, feedback_target->AsAllocationSite().object()));
4574 return Changed(node);
4575 } else if (feedback_target.has_value() &&
4576 !HeapObjectMatcher(new_target).HasValue() &&
4577 feedback_target->map().is_constructor()) {
4578 Node* new_target_feedback = jsgraph()->Constant(*feedback_target);
4579
4580 // Check that the {new_target} is still the {new_target_feedback}.
4581 Node* check = graph()->NewNode(simplified()->ReferenceEqual(), new_target,
4582 new_target_feedback);
4583 effect = graph()->NewNode(
4584 simplified()->CheckIf(DeoptimizeReason::kWrongCallTarget), check,
4585 effect, control);
4586
4587 // Specialize the JSConstruct node to the {new_target_feedback}.
4588 node->ReplaceInput(n.NewTargetIndex(), new_target_feedback);
4589 NodeProperties::ReplaceEffectInput(node, effect);
4590 if (target == new_target) {
4591 node->ReplaceInput(n.TargetIndex(), new_target_feedback);
4592 }
4593
4594 // Try to further reduce the JSConstruct {node}.
4595 return Changed(node).FollowedBy(ReduceJSConstruct(node));
4596 }
4597 }
4598
4599 // Try to specialize JSConstruct {node}s with constant {target}s.
4600 HeapObjectMatcher m(target);
4601 if (m.HasValue()) {
4602 HeapObjectRef target_ref = m.Ref(broker());
4603
4604 // Raise a TypeError if the {target} is not a constructor.
4605 if (!target_ref.map().is_constructor()) {
4606 NodeProperties::ReplaceValueInputs(node, target);
4607 NodeProperties::ChangeOp(node,
4608 javascript()->CallRuntime(
4609 Runtime::kThrowConstructedNonConstructable));
4610 return Changed(node);
4611 }
4612
4613 if (target_ref.IsJSFunction()) {
4614 JSFunctionRef function = target_ref.AsJSFunction();
4615 if (should_disallow_heap_access() && !function.serialized()) {
4616 TRACE_BROKER_MISSING(broker(),do { if (broker()->tracing_enabled()) StdoutStream{} <<
broker()->Trace() << "Missing " << "function, not serialized: "
<< function << " (" << "../deps/v8/src/compiler/js-call-reducer.cc"
<< ":" << 4617 << ")" << std::endl; }
while (false)
4617 "function, not serialized: " << function)do { if (broker()->tracing_enabled()) StdoutStream{} <<
broker()->Trace() << "Missing " << "function, not serialized: "
<< function << " (" << "../deps/v8/src/compiler/js-call-reducer.cc"
<< ":" << 4617 << ")" << std::endl; }
while (false);
4618 return NoChange();
4619 }
4620
4621 // Do not reduce constructors with break points.
4622 if (function.shared().HasBreakInfo()) return NoChange();
4623
4624 // Don't inline cross native context.
4625 if (!function.native_context().equals(native_context())) {
4626 return NoChange();
4627 }
4628
4629 // Check for known builtin functions.
4630 int builtin_id = function.shared().HasBuiltinId()
4631 ? function.shared().builtin_id()
4632 : Builtins::kNoBuiltinId;
4633 switch (builtin_id) {
4634 case Builtins::kArrayConstructor: {
4635 // TODO(bmeurer): Deal with Array subclasses here.
4636 // Turn the {node} into a {JSCreateArray} call.
4637 STATIC_ASSERT(JSConstructNode::NewTargetIndex() == 1)static_assert(JSConstructNode::NewTargetIndex() == 1, "JSConstructNode::NewTargetIndex() == 1"
);
4638 node->ReplaceInput(n.NewTargetIndex(), new_target);
4639 node->RemoveInput(n.FeedbackVectorIndex());
4640 NodeProperties::ChangeOp(
4641 node, javascript()->CreateArray(arity, Handle<AllocationSite>()));
4642 return Changed(node);
4643 }
4644 case Builtins::kObjectConstructor: {
4645 // If no value is passed, we can immediately lower to a simple
4646 // JSCreate and don't need to do any massaging of the {node}.
4647 if (arity == 0) {
4648 node->RemoveInput(n.FeedbackVectorIndex());
4649 NodeProperties::ChangeOp(node, javascript()->Create());
4650 return Changed(node);
4651 }
4652
4653 // If {target} is not the same as {new_target} (i.e. the Object
4654 // constructor), {value} will be ignored and therefore we can lower
4655 // to {JSCreate}. See https://tc39.es/ecma262/#sec-object-value.
4656 HeapObjectMatcher mnew_target(new_target);
4657 if (mnew_target.HasValue() &&
4658 !mnew_target.Ref(broker()).equals(function)) {
4659 // Drop the value inputs.
4660 node->RemoveInput(n.FeedbackVectorIndex());
4661 for (int i = n.ArgumentCount() - 1; i >= 0; i--) {
4662 node->RemoveInput(n.ArgumentIndex(i));
4663 }
4664 NodeProperties::ChangeOp(node, javascript()->Create());
4665 return Changed(node);
4666 }
4667 break;
4668 }
4669 case Builtins::kPromiseConstructor:
4670 return ReducePromiseConstructor(node);
4671 case Builtins::kTypedArrayConstructor:
4672 return ReduceTypedArrayConstructor(node, function.shared());
4673 default:
4674 break;
4675 }
4676 } else if (target_ref.IsJSBoundFunction()) {
4677 JSBoundFunctionRef function = target_ref.AsJSBoundFunction();
4678 if (should_disallow_heap_access() && !function.serialized()) {
4679 TRACE_BROKER_MISSING(broker(),do { if (broker()->tracing_enabled()) StdoutStream{} <<
broker()->Trace() << "Missing " << "function, not serialized: "
<< function << " (" << "../deps/v8/src/compiler/js-call-reducer.cc"
<< ":" << 4680 << ")" << std::endl; }
while (false)
4680 "function, not serialized: " << function)do { if (broker()->tracing_enabled()) StdoutStream{} <<
broker()->Trace() << "Missing " << "function, not serialized: "
<< function << " (" << "../deps/v8/src/compiler/js-call-reducer.cc"
<< ":" << 4680 << ")" << std::endl; }
while (false);
4681 return NoChange();
4682 }
4683
4684 ObjectRef bound_target_function = function.bound_target_function();
4685 FixedArrayRef bound_arguments = function.bound_arguments();
4686
4687 // Patch {node} to use [[BoundTargetFunction]].
4688 node->ReplaceInput(n.TargetIndex(),
4689 jsgraph()->Constant(bound_target_function));
4690
4691 // Patch {node} to use [[BoundTargetFunction]]
4692 // as new.target if {new_target} equals {target}.
4693 node->ReplaceInput(
4694 n.NewTargetIndex(),
4695 graph()->NewNode(common()->Select(MachineRepresentation::kTagged),
4696 graph()->NewNode(simplified()->ReferenceEqual(),
4697 target, new_target),
4698 jsgraph()->Constant(bound_target_function),
4699 new_target));
4700
4701 // Insert the [[BoundArguments]] for {node}.
4702 for (int i = 0; i < bound_arguments.length(); ++i) {
4703 node->InsertInput(graph()->zone(), n.ArgumentIndex(i),
4704 jsgraph()->Constant(bound_arguments.get(i)));
4705 arity++;
4706 }
4707
4708 // Update the JSConstruct operator on {node}.
4709 NodeProperties::ChangeOp(
4710 node, javascript()->Construct(JSConstructNode::ArityForArgc(arity),
4711 p.frequency(), FeedbackSource()));
4712
4713 // Try to further reduce the JSConstruct {node}.
4714 return Changed(node).FollowedBy(ReduceJSConstruct(node));
4715 }
4716
4717 // TODO(bmeurer): Also support optimizing proxies here.
4718 }
4719
4720 // If {target} is the result of a JSCreateBoundFunction operation,
4721 // we can just fold the construction and construct the bound target
4722 // function directly instead.
4723 if (target->opcode() == IrOpcode::kJSCreateBoundFunction) {
4724 Node* bound_target_function = NodeProperties::GetValueInput(target, 0);
4725 int const bound_arguments_length =
4726 static_cast<int>(CreateBoundFunctionParametersOf(target->op()).arity());
4727
4728 // Patch the {node} to use [[BoundTargetFunction]].
4729 node->ReplaceInput(n.TargetIndex(), bound_target_function);
4730
4731 // Patch {node} to use [[BoundTargetFunction]]
4732 // as new.target if {new_target} equals {target}.
4733 node->ReplaceInput(
4734 n.NewTargetIndex(),
4735 graph()->NewNode(common()->Select(MachineRepresentation::kTagged),
4736 graph()->NewNode(simplified()->ReferenceEqual(),
4737 target, new_target),
4738 bound_target_function, new_target));
4739
4740 // Insert the [[BoundArguments]] for {node}.
4741 for (int i = 0; i < bound_arguments_length; ++i) {
4742 Node* value = NodeProperties::GetValueInput(target, 2 + i);
4743 node->InsertInput(graph()->zone(), n.ArgumentIndex(i), value);
4744 arity++;
4745 }
4746
4747 // Update the JSConstruct operator on {node}.
4748 NodeProperties::ChangeOp(
4749 node, javascript()->Construct(JSConstructNode::ArityForArgc(arity),
4750 p.frequency(), FeedbackSource()));
4751
4752 // Try to further reduce the JSConstruct {node}.
4753 return Changed(node).FollowedBy(ReduceJSConstruct(node));
4754 }
4755
4756 return NoChange();
4757}
4758
4759// ES #sec-string.prototype.indexof
4760Reduction JSCallReducer::ReduceStringPrototypeIndexOf(Node* node) {
4761 JSCallNode n(node);
4762 CallParameters const& p = n.Parameters();
4763 if (p.speculation_mode() == SpeculationMode::kDisallowSpeculation) {
4764 return NoChange();
4765 }
4766
4767 Effect effect = n.effect();
4768 Control control = n.control();
4769 if (n.ArgumentCount() > 0) {
4770 Node* receiver = n.receiver();
4771 Node* new_receiver = effect = graph()->NewNode(
4772 simplified()->CheckString(p.feedback()), receiver, effect, control);
4773
4774 Node* search_string = n.Argument(0);
4775 Node* new_search_string = effect =
4776 graph()->NewNode(simplified()->CheckString(p.feedback()), search_string,
4777 effect, control);
4778
4779 Node* new_position = jsgraph()->ZeroConstant();
4780 if (n.ArgumentCount() > 1) {
4781 Node* position = n.Argument(1);
4782 new_position = effect = graph()->NewNode(
4783 simplified()->CheckSmi(p.feedback()), position, effect, control);
4784 }
4785
4786 NodeProperties::ReplaceEffectInput(node, effect);
4787 RelaxEffectsAndControls(node);
4788 node->ReplaceInput(0, new_receiver);
4789 node->ReplaceInput(1, new_search_string);
4790 node->ReplaceInput(2, new_position);
4791 node->TrimInputCount(3);
4792 NodeProperties::ChangeOp(node, simplified()->StringIndexOf());
4793 return Changed(node);
4794 }
4795 return NoChange();
4796}

4798// ES #sec-string.prototype.substring
4799Reduction JSCallReducer::ReduceStringPrototypeSubstring(Node* node) {
4800 JSCallNode n(node);
4801 CallParameters const& p = n.Parameters();
4802 if (n.ArgumentCount() < 1) return NoChange();
4803 if (p.speculation_mode() == SpeculationMode::kDisallowSpeculation) {
4804 return NoChange();
4805 }
4806
4807 JSCallReducerAssembler a(jsgraph(), temp_zone(), node);
4808 Node* subgraph = a.ReduceStringPrototypeSubstring();
4809 return ReplaceWithSubgraph(&a, subgraph);
4810}

4816 if (n.ArgumentCount() < 1) return NoChange();
4817 if (p.speculation_mode() == SpeculationMode::kDisallowSpeculation) {
4818 return NoChange();
4819 }

4825
4826// ES #sec-string.prototype.substr
4827Reduction JSCallReducer::ReduceStringPrototypeSubstr(Node* node) {
4828 JSCallNode n(node);
4829 CallParameters const& p = n.Parameters();
4830 if (n.ArgumentCount() < 1) return NoChange();
4831 if (p.speculation_mode() == SpeculationMode::kDisallowSpeculation) {
4832 return NoChange();
4833 }
4834
4835 Effect effect = n.effect();
4836 Control control = n.control();
4837 Node* receiver = n.receiver();
4838 Node* start = n.Argument(0);
4839 Node* end = n.ArgumentOrUndefined(1, jsgraph());
4840
4841 receiver = effect = graph()->NewNode(simplified()->CheckString(p.feedback()),
4842 receiver, effect, control);
4843
4844 start = effect = graph()->NewNode(simplified()->CheckSmi(p.feedback()), start,
4845 effect, control);
4846
4847 Node* length = graph()->NewNode(simplified()->StringLength(), receiver);
4848
4849 // Replace {end} argument with {length} if it is undefined.
4850 {
4851 Node* check = graph()->NewNode(simplified()->ReferenceEqual(), end,
4852 jsgraph()->UndefinedConstant());
4853 Node* branch =
4854 graph()->NewNode(common()->Branch(BranchHint::kFalse), check, control);
4855
4856 Node* if_true = graph()->NewNode(common()->IfTrue(), branch);
4857 Node* etrue = effect;
4858 Node* vtrue = length;
4859
4860 Node* if_false = graph()->NewNode(common()->IfFalse(), branch);
4861 Node* efalse = effect;
4862 Node* vfalse = efalse = graph()->NewNode(
4863 simplified()->CheckSmi(p.feedback()), end, efalse, if_false);
4864
4865 control = graph()->NewNode(common()->Merge(2), if_true, if_false);
4866 effect = graph()->NewNode(common()->EffectPhi(2), etrue, efalse, control);
4867 end = graph()->NewNode(common()->Phi(MachineRepresentation::kTagged, 2),
4868 vtrue, vfalse, control);
4869 }
4870
4871 Node* initStart = graph()->NewNode(
4872 common()->Select(MachineRepresentation::kTagged, BranchHint::kFalse),
4873 graph()->NewNode(simplified()->NumberLessThan(), start,
4874 jsgraph()->ZeroConstant()),
4875 graph()->NewNode(
4876 simplified()->NumberMax(),
4877 graph()->NewNode(simplified()->NumberAdd(), length, start),
4878 jsgraph()->ZeroConstant()),
4879 start);
4880 // The select above guarantees that initStart is non-negative, but
4881 // our typer can't figure that out yet.
4882 initStart = effect = graph()->NewNode(
4883 common()->TypeGuard(Type::UnsignedSmall()), initStart, effect, control);
4884
4885 Node* resultLength = graph()->NewNode(
4886 simplified()->NumberMin(),
4887 graph()->NewNode(simplified()->NumberMax(), end,
4888 jsgraph()->ZeroConstant()),
4889 graph()->NewNode(simplified()->NumberSubtract(), length, initStart));
4890
4891 // The the select below uses {resultLength} only if {resultLength > 0},
4892 // but our typer can't figure that out yet.
4893 Node* to = effect = graph()->NewNode(
4894 common()->TypeGuard(Type::UnsignedSmall()),
4895 graph()->NewNode(simplified()->NumberAdd(), initStart, resultLength),
4896 effect, control);
4897
4898 Node* result_string = nullptr;
4899 // Return empty string if {from} is smaller than {to}.
4900 {
4901 Node* check = graph()->NewNode(simplified()->NumberLessThan(),
4902 jsgraph()->ZeroConstant(), resultLength);
4903
4904 Node* branch =
4905 graph()->NewNode(common()->Branch(BranchHint::kTrue), check, control);
4906
4907 Node* if_true = graph()->NewNode(common()->IfTrue(), branch);
4908 Node* etrue = effect;
4909 Node* vtrue = etrue =
4910 graph()->NewNode(simplified()->StringSubstring(), receiver, initStart,
4911 to, etrue, if_true);
4912
4913 Node* if_false = graph()->NewNode(common()->IfFalse(), branch);
4914 Node* efalse = effect;
4915 Node* vfalse = jsgraph()->EmptyStringConstant();
4916
4917 control = graph()->NewNode(common()->Merge(2), if_true, if_false);
4918 effect = graph()->NewNode(common()->EffectPhi(2), etrue, efalse, control);
4919 result_string =
4920 graph()->NewNode(common()->Phi(MachineRepresentation::kTagged, 2),
4921 vtrue, vfalse, control);
4922 }
4923
4924 ReplaceWithValue(node, result_string, effect, control);
4925 return Replace(result_string);
4926}

4928Reduction JSCallReducer::ReduceJSConstructWithArrayLike(Node* node) {
4929 JSConstructWithArrayLikeNode n(node);
4930 ConstructParameters const& p = n.Parameters();
4931 const int arraylike_index = n.LastArgumentIndex();
4932 DCHECK_EQ(n.ArgumentCount(), 1)((void) 0); // The arraylike object.
4933 return ReduceCallOrConstructWithArrayLikeOrSpread(
4934 node, arraylike_index, p.frequency(), p.feedback(),
4935 SpeculationMode::kDisallowSpeculation, CallFeedbackRelation::kRelated);

4937
4938Reduction JSCallReducer::ReduceJSConstructWithSpread(Node* node) {
4939 JSConstructWithSpreadNode n(node);
4940 ConstructParameters const& p = n.Parameters();
4941 const int spread_index = n.LastArgumentIndex();
4942 DCHECK_GE(n.ArgumentCount(), 1)((void) 0); // At least the spread.
4943 return ReduceCallOrConstructWithArrayLikeOrSpread(
4944 node, spread_index, p.frequency(), p.feedback(),
4945 SpeculationMode::kDisallowSpeculation, CallFeedbackRelation::kRelated);
4946}
4947
4948Reduction JSCallReducer::ReduceReturnReceiver(Node* node) {
4949 JSCallNode n(node);
4950 Node* receiver = n.receiver();
4951 ReplaceWithValue(node, receiver);
4952 return Replace(receiver);
4953}
4954
4955Reduction JSCallReducer::ReduceForInsufficientFeedback(
4956 Node* node, DeoptimizeReason reason) {
4957 DCHECK(node->opcode() == IrOpcode::kJSCall ||((void) 0)
4958 node->opcode() == IrOpcode::kJSConstruct)((void) 0);
4959 if (!(flags() & kBailoutOnUninitialized)) return NoChange();
4960 // TODO(mythria): May be add additional flags to specify if we need to deopt
4961 // on calls / construct rather than checking for TurboProp here. We may need
4962 // it for NativeContextIndependent code too.
4963 if (FLAG_turboprop) return NoChange();
4964
4965 Node* effect = NodeProperties::GetEffectInput(node);
4966 Node* control = NodeProperties::GetControlInput(node);
4967 Node* frame_state =
4968 NodeProperties::FindFrameStateBefore(node, jsgraph()->Dead());
4969 Node* deoptimize = graph()->NewNode(
4970 common()->Deoptimize(DeoptimizeKind::kSoft, reason, FeedbackSource()),
4971 frame_state, effect, control);
4972 // TODO(bmeurer): This should be on the AdvancedReducer somehow.
4973 NodeProperties::MergeControlToEnd(graph(), common(), deoptimize);
4974 Revisit(graph()->end());
4975 node->TrimInputCount(0);
4976 NodeProperties::ChangeOp(node, common()->Dead());
4977 return Changed(node);
4978}
4979
4980Node* JSCallReducer::LoadReceiverElementsKind(Node* receiver, Effect* effect,
4981 Control control) {
4982 Node* effect_node = *effect;
4983 Node* receiver_map = effect_node =
4984 graph()->NewNode(simplified()->LoadField(AccessBuilder::ForMap()),
4985 receiver, effect_node, control);
4986 Node* receiver_bit_field2 = effect_node = graph()->NewNode(
4987 simplified()->LoadField(AccessBuilder::ForMapBitField2()), receiver_map,
4988 effect_node, control);
4989 Node* receiver_elements_kind = graph()->NewNode(
4990 simplified()->NumberShiftRightLogical(),
4991 graph()->NewNode(
4992 simplified()->NumberBitwiseAnd(), receiver_bit_field2,
4993 jsgraph()->Constant(Map::Bits2::ElementsKindBits::kMask)),
4994 jsgraph()->Constant(Map::Bits2::ElementsKindBits::kShift));
4995 *effect = effect_node;
4996 return receiver_elements_kind;
4997}
4998
4999void JSCallReducer::CheckIfElementsKind(Node* receiver_elements_kind,
5000 ElementsKind kind, Node* control,
5001 Node** if_true, Node** if_false) {
5002 Node* is_packed_kind =
5003 graph()->NewNode(simplified()->NumberEqual(), receiver_elements_kind,
5004 jsgraph()->Constant(GetPackedElementsKind(kind)));
5005 Node* packed_branch =
5006 graph()->NewNode(common()->Branch(), is_packed_kind, control);
5007 Node* if_packed = graph()->NewNode(common()->IfTrue(), packed_branch);
5008
5009 if (IsHoleyElementsKind(kind)) {
5010 Node* if_not_packed = graph()->NewNode(common()->IfFalse(), packed_branch);
5011 Node* is_holey_kind =
5012 graph()->NewNode(simplified()->NumberEqual(), receiver_elements_kind,
5013 jsgraph()->Constant(GetHoleyElementsKind(kind)));
5014 Node* holey_branch =
5015 graph()->NewNode(common()->Branch(), is_holey_kind, if_not_packed);
5016 Node* if_holey = graph()->NewNode(common()->IfTrue(), holey_branch);
5017
5018 Node* if_not_packed_not_holey =
5019 graph()->NewNode(common()->IfFalse(), holey_branch);
5020
5021 *if_true = graph()->NewNode(common()->Merge(2), if_packed, if_holey);
5022 *if_false = if_not_packed_not_holey;
5023 } else {
5024 *if_true = if_packed;
5025 *if_false = graph()->NewNode(common()->IfFalse(), packed_branch);
5026 }
5027}
5028
5029// ES6 section 22.1.3.18 Array.prototype.push ( )
5030Reduction JSCallReducer::ReduceArrayPrototypePush(Node* node) {
5031 DisallowHeapAccessIf disallow_heap_access(should_disallow_heap_access());
5032
5033 JSCallNode n(node);
5034 CallParameters const& p = n.Parameters();
5035 if (p.speculation_mode() == SpeculationMode::kDisallowSpeculation) {
5036 return NoChange();
5037 }
5038
5039 int const num_values = n.ArgumentCount();
5040 Node* receiver = n.receiver();
5041 Effect effect = n.effect();
5042 Control control = n.control();
5043
5044 MapInference inference(broker(), receiver, effect);
5045 if (!inference.HaveMaps()) return NoChange();
5046 MapHandles const& receiver_maps = inference.GetMaps();
5047
5048 std::vector<ElementsKind> kinds;
5049 if (!CanInlineArrayResizingBuiltin(broker(), receiver_maps, &kinds, true)) {
5050 return inference.NoChange();
5051 }
5052 if (!dependencies()->DependOnNoElementsProtector()) UNREACHABLE()V8_Fatal("unreachable code");
5053 inference.RelyOnMapsPreferStability(dependencies(), jsgraph(), &effect,
5054 control, p.feedback());
5055
5056 std::vector<Node*> controls_to_merge;
5057 std::vector<Node*> effects_to_merge;
5058 std::vector<Node*> values_to_merge;
5059 Node* return_value = jsgraph()->UndefinedConstant();
5060
5061 Node* receiver_elements_kind =
5062 LoadReceiverElementsKind(receiver, &effect, control);
5063 Node* next_control = control;
5064 Node* next_effect = effect;
5065 for (size_t i = 0; i < kinds.size(); i++) {
5066 ElementsKind kind = kinds[i];
5067 control = next_control;
5068 effect = next_effect;
5069 // We do not need branch for the last elements kind.
5070 if (i != kinds.size() - 1) {
5071 Node* control_node = control;
5072 CheckIfElementsKind(receiver_elements_kind, kind, control_node,
5073 &control_node, &next_control);
5074 control = control_node;
5075 }
5076
5077 // Collect the value inputs to push.
5078 std::vector<Node*> values(num_values);
5079 for (int i = 0; i < num_values; ++i) {
5080 values[i] = n.Argument(i);
5081 }
5082
5083 for (auto& value : values) {
5084 if (IsSmiElementsKind(kind)) {
5085 value = effect = graph()->NewNode(simplified()->CheckSmi(p.feedback()),
5086 value, effect, control);
5087 } else if (IsDoubleElementsKind(kind)) {
5088 value = effect = graph()->NewNode(
5089 simplified()->CheckNumber(p.feedback()), value, effect, control);
5090 // Make sure we do not store signaling NaNs into double arrays.
5091 value = graph()->NewNode(simplified()->NumberSilenceNaN(), value);
5092 }
5093 }
5094
5095 // Load the "length" property of the {receiver}.
5096 Node* length = effect = graph()->NewNode(
5097 simplified()->LoadField(AccessBuilder::ForJSArrayLength(kind)),
5098 receiver, effect, control);
5099 return_value = length;
5100
5101 // Check if we have any {values} to push.
5102 if (num_values > 0) {
5103 // Compute the resulting "length" of the {receiver}.
5104 Node* new_length = return_value = graph()->NewNode(
5105 simplified()->NumberAdd(), length, jsgraph()->Constant(num_values));
5106
5107 // Load the elements backing store of the {receiver}.
5108 Node* elements = effect = graph()->NewNode(
5109 simplified()->LoadField(AccessBuilder::ForJSObjectElements()),
5110 receiver, effect, control);
5111 Node* elements_length = effect = graph()->NewNode(
5112 simplified()->LoadField(AccessBuilder::ForFixedArrayLength()),
5113 elements, effect, control);
5114
5115 GrowFastElementsMode mode =
5116 IsDoubleElementsKind(kind)
5117 ? GrowFastElementsMode::kDoubleElements
5118 : GrowFastElementsMode::kSmiOrObjectElements;
5119 elements = effect = graph()->NewNode(
5120 simplified()->MaybeGrowFastElements(mode, p.feedback()), receiver,
5121 elements,
5122 graph()->NewNode(simplified()->NumberAdd(), length,
5123 jsgraph()->Constant(num_values - 1)),
5124 elements_length, effect, control);
5125
5126 // Update the JSArray::length field. Since this is observable,
5127 // there must be no other check after this.
5128 effect = graph()->NewNode(
5129 simplified()->StoreField(AccessBuilder::ForJSArrayLength(kind)),
5130 receiver, new_length, effect, control);
5131
5132 // Append the {values} to the {elements}.
5133 for (int i = 0; i < num_values; ++i) {
5134 Node* value = values[i];
5135 Node* index = graph()->NewNode(simplified()->NumberAdd(), length,
5136 jsgraph()->Constant(i));
5137 effect =
5138 graph()->NewNode(simplified()->StoreElement(
5139 AccessBuilder::ForFixedArrayElement(kind)),
5140 elements, index, value, effect, control);
5141 }
5142 }
5143
5144 controls_to_merge.push_back(control);
5145 effects_to_merge.push_back(effect);
5146 values_to_merge.push_back(return_value);
5147 }
5148
5149 if (controls_to_merge.size() > 1) {
5150 int const count = static_cast<int>(controls_to_merge.size());
5151
5152 control = graph()->NewNode(common()->Merge(count), count,
5153 &controls_to_merge.front());
5154 effects_to_merge.push_back(control);
5155 effect = graph()->NewNode(common()->EffectPhi(count), count + 1,
5156 &effects_to_merge.front());
5157 values_to_merge.push_back(control);
5158 return_value =
5159 graph()->NewNode(common()->Phi(MachineRepresentation::kTagged, count),
5160 count + 1, &values_to_merge.front());
5161 }
5162
5163 ReplaceWithValue(node, return_value, effect, control);
5164 return Replace(return_value);
5165}
5166
5167// ES6 section 22.1.3.17 Array.prototype.pop ( )
5168Reduction JSCallReducer::ReduceArrayPrototypePop(Node* node) {
5169 DisallowHeapAccessIf disallow_heap_access(should_disallow_heap_access());
5170
5171 JSCallNode n(node);
5172 CallParameters const& p = n.Parameters();
5173 if (p.speculation_mode() == SpeculationMode::kDisallowSpeculation) {
5174 return NoChange();
5175 }
5176
5177 Effect effect = n.effect();
5178 Control control = n.control();
5179 Node* receiver = n.receiver();
5180
5181 MapInference inference(broker(), receiver, effect);
5182 if (!inference.HaveMaps()) return NoChange();
5183 MapHandles const& receiver_maps = inference.GetMaps();
5184
5185 std::vector<ElementsKind> kinds;
5186 if (!CanInlineArrayResizingBuiltin(broker(), receiver_maps, &kinds)) {
5187 return inference.NoChange();
5188 }
5189 if (!dependencies()->DependOnNoElementsProtector()) UNREACHABLE()V8_Fatal("unreachable code");
5190 inference.RelyOnMapsPreferStability(dependencies(), jsgraph(), &effect,
5191 control, p.feedback());
5192
5193 std::vector<Node*> controls_to_merge;
5194 std::vector<Node*> effects_to_merge;
5195 std::vector<Node*> values_to_merge;
5196 Node* value = jsgraph()->UndefinedConstant();
5197
5198 Node* receiver_elements_kind =
5199 LoadReceiverElementsKind(receiver, &effect, control);
5200 Node* next_control = control;
5201 Node* next_effect = effect;
5202 for (size_t i = 0; i < kinds.size(); i++) {
5203 ElementsKind kind = kinds[i];
5204 control = next_control;
5205 effect = next_effect;
5206 // We do not need branch for the last elements kind.
5207 if (i != kinds.size() - 1) {
5208 Node* control_node = control;
5209 CheckIfElementsKind(receiver_elements_kind, kind, control_node,
5210 &control_node, &next_control);
5211 control = control_node;
5212 }
5213
5214 // Load the "length" property of the {receiver}.
5215 Node* length = effect = graph()->NewNode(
5216 simplified()->LoadField(AccessBuilder::ForJSArrayLength(kind)),
5217 receiver, effect, control);
5218
5219 // Check if the {receiver} has any elements.
5220 Node* check = graph()->NewNode(simplified()->NumberEqual(), length,
5221 jsgraph()->ZeroConstant());
5222 Node* branch =
5223 graph()->NewNode(common()->Branch(BranchHint::kFalse), check, control);
5224
5225 Node* if_true = graph()->NewNode(common()->IfTrue(), branch);
5226 Node* etrue = effect;
5227 Node* vtrue = jsgraph()->UndefinedConstant();
5228
5229 Node* if_false = graph()->NewNode(common()->IfFalse(), branch);
5230 Node* efalse = effect;
5231 Node* vfalse;
5232 {
5233 // TODO(tebbi): We should trim the backing store if the capacity is too
5234 // big, as implemented in elements.cc:ElementsAccessorBase::SetLengthImpl.
5235
5236 // Load the elements backing store from the {receiver}.
5237 Node* elements = efalse = graph()->NewNode(
5238 simplified()->LoadField(AccessBuilder::ForJSObjectElements()),
5239 receiver, efalse, if_false);
5240
5241 // Ensure that we aren't popping from a copy-on-write backing store.
5242 if (IsSmiOrObjectElementsKind(kind)) {
5243 elements = efalse =
5244 graph()->NewNode(simplified()->EnsureWritableFastElements(),
5245 receiver, elements, efalse, if_false);
5246 }
5247
5248 // Compute the new {length}.
5249 length = graph()->NewNode(simplified()->NumberSubtract(), length,
5250 jsgraph()->OneConstant());
5251
5252 // Store the new {length} to the {receiver}.
5253 efalse = graph()->NewNode(
5254 simplified()->StoreField(AccessBuilder::ForJSArrayLength(kind)),
5255 receiver, length, efalse, if_false);
5256
5257 // Load the last entry from the {elements}.
5258 vfalse = efalse = graph()->NewNode(
5259 simplified()->LoadElement(AccessBuilder::ForFixedArrayElement(kind)),
5260 elements, length, efalse, if_false);
5261
5262 // Store a hole to the element we just removed from the {receiver}.
5263 efalse = graph()->NewNode(
5264 simplified()->StoreElement(
5265 AccessBuilder::ForFixedArrayElement(GetHoleyElementsKind(kind))),
5266 elements, length, jsgraph()->TheHoleConstant(), efalse, if_false);
5267 }
5268
5269 control = graph()->NewNode(common()->Merge(2), if_true, if_false);
5270 effect = graph()->NewNode(common()->EffectPhi(2), etrue, efalse, control);
5271 value = graph()->NewNode(common()->Phi(MachineRepresentation::kTagged, 2),
5272 vtrue, vfalse, control);
5273
5274 // Convert the hole to undefined. Do this last, so that we can optimize
5275 // conversion operator via some smart strength reduction in many cases.
5276 if (IsHoleyElementsKind(kind)) {
5277 value =
5278 graph()->NewNode(simplified()->ConvertTaggedHoleToUndefined(), value);
5279 }
5280
5281 controls_to_merge.push_back(control);
5282 effects_to_merge.push_back(effect);
5283 values_to_merge.push_back(value);
5284 }
5285
5286 if (controls_to_merge.size() > 1) {
5287 int const count = static_cast<int>(controls_to_merge.size());
5288
5289 control = graph()->NewNode(common()->Merge(count), count,
5290 &controls_to_merge.front());
5291 effects_to_merge.push_back(control);
5292 effect = graph()->NewNode(common()->EffectPhi(count), count + 1,
5293 &effects_to_merge.front());
5294 values_to_merge.push_back(control);
5295 value =
5296 graph()->NewNode(common()->Phi(MachineRepresentation::kTagged, count),
5297 count + 1, &values_to_merge.front());
5298 }
5299
5300 ReplaceWithValue(node, value, effect, control);
5301 return Replace(value);
5302}
