5304// ES6 section 22.1.3.22 Array.prototype.shift ( )
5305Reduction JSCallReducer::ReduceArrayPrototypeShift(Node* node) {
5306 DisallowHeapAccessIf disallow_heap_access(should_disallow_heap_access());
5307
5308 JSCallNode n(node);
5309 CallParameters const& p = n.Parameters();
5310 if (p.speculation_mode() == SpeculationMode::kDisallowSpeculation) {
5311 return NoChange();
5312 }
5313
5314 Node* target = n.target();
5315 Node* receiver = n.receiver();
5316 Node* context = n.context();
5317 FrameState frame_state = n.frame_state();
5318 Effect effect = n.effect();
5319 Control control = n.control();
5320
5321 MapInference inference(broker(), receiver, effect);
5322 if (!inference.HaveMaps()) return NoChange();
5323 MapHandles const& receiver_maps = inference.GetMaps();
5324
5325 std::vector<ElementsKind> kinds;
5326 if (!CanInlineArrayResizingBuiltin(broker(), receiver_maps, &kinds)) {
5327 return inference.NoChange();
5328 }
5329 if (!dependencies()->DependOnNoElementsProtector()) UNREACHABLE()V8_Fatal("unreachable code");
5330 inference.RelyOnMapsPreferStability(dependencies(), jsgraph(), &effect,
5331 control, p.feedback());
5332
5333 std::vector<Node*> controls_to_merge;
5334 std::vector<Node*> effects_to_merge;
5335 std::vector<Node*> values_to_merge;
5336 Node* value = jsgraph()->UndefinedConstant();
5337
5338 Node* receiver_elements_kind =
5339 LoadReceiverElementsKind(receiver, &effect, control);
5340 Node* next_control = control;
5341 Node* next_effect = effect;
5342 for (size_t i = 0; i < kinds.size(); i++) {
5343 ElementsKind kind = kinds[i];
5344 control = next_control;
5345 effect = next_effect;
5346 // We do not need branch for the last elements kind.
5347 if (i != kinds.size() - 1) {
5348 Node* control_node = control;
5349 CheckIfElementsKind(receiver_elements_kind, kind, control_node,
5350 &control_node, &next_control);
5351 control = control_node;
5352 }
5353
5354 // Load length of the {receiver}.
5355 Node* length = effect = graph()->NewNode(
5356 simplified()->LoadField(AccessBuilder::ForJSArrayLength(kind)),
5357 receiver, effect, control);
5358
5359 // Return undefined if {receiver} has no elements.
5360 Node* check0 = graph()->NewNode(simplified()->NumberEqual(), length,
5361 jsgraph()->ZeroConstant());
5362 Node* branch0 =
5363 graph()->NewNode(common()->Branch(BranchHint::kFalse), check0, control);
5364
5365 Node* if_true0 = graph()->NewNode(common()->IfTrue(), branch0);
5366 Node* etrue0 = effect;
5367 Node* vtrue0 = jsgraph()->UndefinedConstant();
5368
5369 Node* if_false0 = graph()->NewNode(common()->IfFalse(), branch0);
5370 Node* efalse0 = effect;
5371 Node* vfalse0;
5372 {
5373 // Check if we should take the fast-path.
5374 Node* check1 =
5375 graph()->NewNode(simplified()->NumberLessThanOrEqual(), length,
5376 jsgraph()->Constant(JSArray::kMaxCopyElements));
5377 Node* branch1 = graph()->NewNode(common()->Branch(BranchHint::kTrue),
5378 check1, if_false0);
5379
5380 Node* if_true1 = graph()->NewNode(common()->IfTrue(), branch1);
5381 Node* etrue1 = efalse0;
5382 Node* vtrue1;
5383 {
5384 Node* elements = etrue1 = graph()->NewNode(
5385 simplified()->LoadField(AccessBuilder::ForJSObjectElements()),
5386 receiver, etrue1, if_true1);
5387
5388 // Load the first element here, which we return below.
5389 vtrue1 = etrue1 = graph()->NewNode(
5390 simplified()->LoadElement(
5391 AccessBuilder::ForFixedArrayElement(kind)),
5392 elements, jsgraph()->ZeroConstant(), etrue1, if_true1);
5393
5394 // Ensure that we aren't shifting a copy-on-write backing store.
5395 if (IsSmiOrObjectElementsKind(kind)) {
5396 elements = etrue1 =
5397 graph()->NewNode(simplified()->EnsureWritableFastElements(),
5398 receiver, elements, etrue1, if_true1);
5399 }
5400
5401 // Shift the remaining {elements} by one towards the start.
5402 Node* loop = graph()->NewNode(common()->Loop(2), if_true1, if_true1);
5403 Node* eloop =
5404 graph()->NewNode(common()->EffectPhi(2), etrue1, etrue1, loop);
5405 Node* terminate = graph()->NewNode(common()->Terminate(), eloop, loop);
5406 NodeProperties::MergeControlToEnd(graph(), common(), terminate);
5407 Node* index = graph()->NewNode(
5408 common()->Phi(MachineRepresentation::kTagged, 2),
5409 jsgraph()->OneConstant(),
5410 jsgraph()->Constant(JSArray::kMaxCopyElements - 1), loop);
5411
5412 {
5413 Node* check2 =
5414 graph()->NewNode(simplified()->NumberLessThan(), index, length);
5415 Node* branch2 = graph()->NewNode(common()->Branch(), check2, loop);
5416
5417 if_true1 = graph()->NewNode(common()->IfFalse(), branch2);
5418 etrue1 = eloop;
5419
5420 Node* control = graph()->NewNode(common()->IfTrue(), branch2);
5421 Node* effect = etrue1;
5422
5423 ElementAccess const access =
5424 AccessBuilder::ForFixedArrayElement(kind);
5425 Node* value = effect =
5426 graph()->NewNode(simplified()->LoadElement(access), elements,
5427 index, effect, control);
5428 effect = graph()->NewNode(
5429 simplified()->StoreElement(access), elements,
5430 graph()->NewNode(simplified()->NumberSubtract(), index,
5431 jsgraph()->OneConstant()),
5432 value, effect, control);
5433
5434 loop->ReplaceInput(1, control);
5435 eloop->ReplaceInput(1, effect);
5436 index->ReplaceInput(1,
5437 graph()->NewNode(simplified()->NumberAdd(), index,
5438 jsgraph()->OneConstant()));
5439 }
5440
5441 // Compute the new {length}.
5442 length = graph()->NewNode(simplified()->NumberSubtract(), length,
5443 jsgraph()->OneConstant());
5444
5445 // Store the new {length} to the {receiver}.
5446 etrue1 = graph()->NewNode(
5447 simplified()->StoreField(AccessBuilder::ForJSArrayLength(kind)),
5448 receiver, length, etrue1, if_true1);
5449
5450 // Store a hole to the element we just removed from the {receiver}.
5451 etrue1 = graph()->NewNode(
5452 simplified()->StoreElement(AccessBuilder::ForFixedArrayElement(
5453 GetHoleyElementsKind(kind))),
5454 elements, length, jsgraph()->TheHoleConstant(), etrue1, if_true1);
5455 }
5456
5457 Node* if_false1 = graph()->NewNode(common()->IfFalse(), branch1);
5458 Node* efalse1 = efalse0;
5459 Node* vfalse1;
5460 {
5461 // Call the generic C++ implementation.
5462 const int builtin_index = Builtins::kArrayShift;
5463 auto call_descriptor = Linkage::GetCEntryStubCallDescriptor(
5464 graph()->zone(), 1, BuiltinArguments::kNumExtraArgsWithReceiver,
5465 Builtins::name(builtin_index), node->op()->properties(),
5466 CallDescriptor::kNeedsFrameState);
5467 Node* stub_code = jsgraph()->CEntryStubConstant(1, kDontSaveFPRegs,
5468 kArgvOnStack, true);
5469 Address builtin_entry = Builtins::CppEntryOf(builtin_index);
5470 Node* entry = jsgraph()->ExternalConstant(
5471 ExternalReference::Create(builtin_entry));
5472 Node* argc =
5473 jsgraph()->Constant(BuiltinArguments::kNumExtraArgsWithReceiver);
5474 if_false1 = efalse1 = vfalse1 =
5475 graph()->NewNode(common()->Call(call_descriptor), stub_code,
5476 receiver, jsgraph()->PaddingConstant(), argc,
5477 target, jsgraph()->UndefinedConstant(), entry,
5478 argc, context, frame_state, efalse1, if_false1);
5479 }
5480
5481 if_false0 = graph()->NewNode(common()->Merge(2), if_true1, if_false1);
5482 efalse0 =
5483 graph()->NewNode(common()->EffectPhi(2), etrue1, efalse1, if_false0);
5484 vfalse0 =
5485 graph()->NewNode(common()->Phi(MachineRepresentation::kTagged, 2),
5486 vtrue1, vfalse1, if_false0);
5487 }
5488
5489 control = graph()->NewNode(common()->Merge(2), if_true0, if_false0);
5490 effect = graph()->NewNode(common()->EffectPhi(2), etrue0, efalse0, control);
5491 value = graph()->NewNode(common()->Phi(MachineRepresentation::kTagged, 2),
5492 vtrue0, vfalse0, control);
5493
5494 // Convert the hole to undefined. Do this last, so that we can optimize
5495 // conversion operator via some smart strength reduction in many cases.
5496 if (IsHoleyElementsKind(kind)) {
5497 value =
5498 graph()->NewNode(simplified()->ConvertTaggedHoleToUndefined(), value);
5499 }
5500
5501 controls_to_merge.push_back(control);
5502 effects_to_merge.push_back(effect);
5503 values_to_merge.push_back(value);
5504 }
5505
5506 if (controls_to_merge.size() > 1) {
5507 int const count = static_cast<int>(controls_to_merge.size());
5508
5509 control = graph()->NewNode(common()->Merge(count), count,
5510 &controls_to_merge.front());
5511 effects_to_merge.push_back(control);
5512 effect = graph()->NewNode(common()->EffectPhi(count), count + 1,
5513 &effects_to_merge.front());
5514 values_to_merge.push_back(control);
5515 value =
5516 graph()->NewNode(common()->Phi(MachineRepresentation::kTagged, count),
5517 count + 1, &values_to_merge.front());
5518 }
5519
5520 ReplaceWithValue(node, value, effect, control);
5521 return Replace(value);
5522}
5523
5524// ES6 section 22.1.3.23 Array.prototype.slice ( )
5525Reduction JSCallReducer::ReduceArrayPrototypeSlice(Node* node) {
5526 DisallowHeapAccessIf disallow_heap_access(should_disallow_heap_access());
5527
5528 if (!FLAG_turbo_inline_array_builtins) return NoChange();
5529 JSCallNode n(node);
5530 CallParameters const& p = n.Parameters();
5531 if (p.speculation_mode() == SpeculationMode::kDisallowSpeculation) {
5532 return NoChange();
5533 }
5534
5535 Node* receiver = n.receiver();
5536 Node* start = n.ArgumentOr(0, jsgraph()->ZeroConstant());
5537 Node* end = n.ArgumentOrUndefined(1, jsgraph());
5538 Node* context = n.context();
5539 Effect effect = n.effect();
5540 Control control = n.control();
5541
5542 // Optimize for the case where we simply clone the {receiver},
5543 // i.e. when the {start} is zero and the {end} is undefined
5544 // (meaning it will be set to {receiver}s "length" property).
5545 if (!NumberMatcher(start).Is(0) ||
5546 !HeapObjectMatcher(end).Is(factory()->undefined_value())) {
5547 return NoChange();
5548 }
5549
5550 MapInference inference(broker(), receiver, effect);
5551 if (!inference.HaveMaps()) return NoChange();
5552 MapHandles const& receiver_maps = inference.GetMaps();
5553
5554 // Check that the maps are of JSArray (and more).
5555 // TODO(turbofan): Consider adding special case for the common pattern
5556 // `slice.call(arguments)`, for example jQuery makes heavy use of that.
5557 bool can_be_holey = false;
5558 for (Handle<Map> map : receiver_maps) {
5559 MapRef receiver_map(broker(), map);
5560 if (!receiver_map.supports_fast_array_iteration())
5561 return inference.NoChange();
5562 if (IsHoleyElementsKind(receiver_map.elements_kind())) {
5563 can_be_holey = true;
5564 }
5565 }
5566
5567 if (!dependencies()->DependOnArraySpeciesProtector())
5568 return inference.NoChange();
5569 if (can_be_holey) {
5570 if (!dependencies()->DependOnNoElementsProtector()) UNREACHABLE()V8_Fatal("unreachable code");
5571 }
5572 inference.RelyOnMapsPreferStability(dependencies(), jsgraph(), &effect,
5573 control, p.feedback());
5574
5575 // TODO(turbofan): We can do even better here, either adding a CloneArray
5576 // simplified operator, whose output type indicates that it's an Array,
5577 // saving subsequent checks, or yet better, by introducing new operators
5578 // CopySmiOrObjectElements / CopyDoubleElements and inlining the JSArray
5579 // allocation in here. That way we'd even get escape analysis and scalar
5580 // replacement to help in some cases.
5581 Callable callable =
5582 Builtins::CallableFor(isolate(), Builtins::kCloneFastJSArray);
5583 auto call_descriptor = Linkage::GetStubCallDescriptor(
5584 graph()->zone(), callable.descriptor(),
5585 callable.descriptor().GetStackParameterCount(), CallDescriptor::kNoFlags,
5586 Operator::kNoThrow | Operator::kNoDeopt);
5587
5588 // Calls to Builtins::kCloneFastJSArray produce COW arrays
5589 // if the original array is COW
5590 Node* clone = effect = graph()->NewNode(
5591 common()->Call(call_descriptor), jsgraph()->HeapConstant(callable.code()),
5592 receiver, context, effect, control);
5593
5594 ReplaceWithValue(node, clone, effect, control);
5595 return Replace(clone);
5596}
5597
5598// ES6 section 22.1.2.2 Array.isArray ( arg )
5599Reduction JSCallReducer::ReduceArrayIsArray(Node* node) {
5600 DisallowHeapAccessIf disallow_heap_access(should_disallow_heap_access());
5601
5602 // We certainly know that undefined is not an array.
5603 JSCallNode n(node);
5604 if (n.ArgumentCount() < 1) {
5605 Node* value = jsgraph()->FalseConstant();
5606 ReplaceWithValue(node, value);
5607 return Replace(value);
5608 }
5609
5610 Effect effect = n.effect();
5611 Control control = n.control();
5612 Node* context = n.context();
5613 FrameState frame_state = n.frame_state();
5614 Node* object = n.Argument(0);
5615 node->ReplaceInput(0, object);
5616 node->ReplaceInput(1, context);
5617 node->ReplaceInput(2, frame_state);
5618 node->ReplaceInput(3, effect);
5619 node->ReplaceInput(4, control);
5620 node->TrimInputCount(5);
5621 NodeProperties::ChangeOp(node, javascript()->ObjectIsArray());
5622 return Changed(node);
5623}
5624
5625Reduction JSCallReducer::ReduceArrayIterator(Node* node,
5626 ArrayIteratorKind array_kind,
5627 IterationKind iteration_kind) {
5628 DisallowHeapAccessIf disallow_heap_access(should_disallow_heap_access());
5629
5630 JSCallNode n(node);
5631 Node* receiver = n.receiver();
5632 Node* context = n.context();
5633 Effect effect = n.effect();
5634 Control control = n.control();
5635
5636 // Check if we know that {receiver} is a valid JSReceiver.
5637 MapInference inference(broker(), receiver, effect);
5638 if (!inference.HaveMaps() || !inference.AllOfInstanceTypesAreJSReceiver()) {
5639 return NoChange();
5640 }
5641
5642 // TypedArray iteration is stricter: it throws if the receiver is not a typed
5643 // array. So don't bother optimizing in that case.
5644 if (array_kind == ArrayIteratorKind::kTypedArray &&
5645 !inference.AllOfInstanceTypesAre(InstanceType::JS_TYPED_ARRAY_TYPE)) {
5646 return NoChange();
5647 }
5648
5649 if (array_kind == ArrayIteratorKind::kTypedArray) {
5650 // Make sure we deopt when the JSArrayBuffer is detached.
5651 if (!dependencies()->DependOnArrayBufferDetachingProtector()) {
5652 CallParameters const& p = CallParametersOf(node->op());
5653 if (p.speculation_mode() == SpeculationMode::kDisallowSpeculation) {
5654 return NoChange();
5655 }
5656 Node* buffer = effect = graph()->NewNode(
5657 simplified()->LoadField(AccessBuilder::ForJSArrayBufferViewBuffer()),
5658 receiver, effect, control);
5659 Node* buffer_bit_field = effect = graph()->NewNode(
5660 simplified()->LoadField(AccessBuilder::ForJSArrayBufferBitField()),
5661 buffer, effect, control);
5662 Node* check = graph()->NewNode(
5663 simplified()->NumberEqual(),
5664 graph()->NewNode(
5665 simplified()->NumberBitwiseAnd(), buffer_bit_field,
5666 jsgraph()->Constant(JSArrayBuffer::WasDetachedBit::kMask)),
5667 jsgraph()->ZeroConstant());
5668 effect = graph()->NewNode(
5669 simplified()->CheckIf(DeoptimizeReason::kArrayBufferWasDetached,
5670 p.feedback()),
5671 check, effect, control);
5672 }
5673 }
5674
5675 // Morph the {node} into a JSCreateArrayIterator with the given {kind}.
5676 RelaxControls(node);
5677 node->ReplaceInput(0, receiver);
5678 node->ReplaceInput(1, context);
5679 node->ReplaceInput(2, effect);
5680 node->ReplaceInput(3, control);
5681 node->TrimInputCount(4);
5682 NodeProperties::ChangeOp(node,
5683 javascript()->CreateArrayIterator(iteration_kind));
5684 return Changed(node);
5685}
5686
5687// ES #sec-%arrayiteratorprototype%.next
5688Reduction JSCallReducer::ReduceArrayIteratorPrototypeNext(Node* node) {
5689 DisallowHeapAccessIf disallow_heap_access(should_disallow_heap_access());
5690
5691 JSCallNode n(node);
5692 CallParameters const& p = n.Parameters();
5693 Node* iterator = n.receiver();
5694 Node* context = n.context();
5695 Effect effect = n.effect();
5696 Control control = n.control();
5697
5698 if (p.speculation_mode() == SpeculationMode::kDisallowSpeculation) {
5699 return NoChange();
5700 }
5701
5702 if (iterator->opcode() != IrOpcode::kJSCreateArrayIterator) return NoChange();
5703
5704 IterationKind const iteration_kind =
5705 CreateArrayIteratorParametersOf(iterator->op()).kind();
5706 Node* iterated_object = NodeProperties::GetValueInput(iterator, 0);
5707 Node* iterator_effect = NodeProperties::GetEffectInput(iterator);
5708
5709 MapInference inference(broker(), iterated_object, iterator_effect);
5710 if (!inference.HaveMaps()) return NoChange();
5711 MapHandles const& iterated_object_maps = inference.GetMaps();
5712
5713 // Check that various {iterated_object_maps} have compatible elements kinds.
5714 ElementsKind elements_kind =
5715 MapRef(broker(), iterated_object_maps[0]).elements_kind();
5716 if (IsTypedArrayElementsKind(elements_kind)) {
5717 // TurboFan doesn't support loading from BigInt typed arrays yet.
5718 if (elements_kind == BIGUINT64_ELEMENTS ||
5719 elements_kind == BIGINT64_ELEMENTS) {
5720 return inference.NoChange();
5721 }
5722 for (Handle<Map> map : iterated_object_maps) {
5723 MapRef iterated_object_map(broker(), map);
5724 if (iterated_object_map.elements_kind() != elements_kind) {
5725 return inference.NoChange();
5726 }
5727 }
5728 } else {
5729 if (!CanInlineArrayIteratingBuiltin(broker(), iterated_object_maps,
5730 &elements_kind)) {
5731 return inference.NoChange();
5732 }
5733 }
5734
5735 if (IsHoleyElementsKind(elements_kind)) {
5736 if (!dependencies()->DependOnNoElementsProtector()) UNREACHABLE()V8_Fatal("unreachable code");
5737 }
5738 // Since the map inference was done relative to {iterator_effect} rather than
5739 // {effect}, we need to guard the use of the map(s) even when the inference
5740 // was reliable.
5741 inference.InsertMapChecks(jsgraph(), &effect, control, p.feedback());
5742
5743 if (IsTypedArrayElementsKind(elements_kind)) {
5744 // See if we can skip the detaching check.
5745 if (!dependencies()->DependOnArrayBufferDetachingProtector()) {
5746 // Bail out if the {iterated_object}s JSArrayBuffer was detached.
5747 Node* buffer = effect = graph()->NewNode(
5748 simplified()->LoadField(AccessBuilder::ForJSArrayBufferViewBuffer()),
5749 iterated_object, effect, control);
5750 Node* buffer_bit_field = effect = graph()->NewNode(
5751 simplified()->LoadField(AccessBuilder::ForJSArrayBufferBitField()),
5752 buffer, effect, control);
5753 Node* check = graph()->NewNode(
5754 simplified()->NumberEqual(),
5755 graph()->NewNode(
5756 simplified()->NumberBitwiseAnd(), buffer_bit_field,
5757 jsgraph()->Constant(JSArrayBuffer::WasDetachedBit::kMask)),
5758 jsgraph()->ZeroConstant());
5759 effect = graph()->NewNode(
5760 simplified()->CheckIf(DeoptimizeReason::kArrayBufferWasDetached,
5761 p.feedback()),
5762 check, effect, control);
5763 }
5764 }
5765
5766 // Load the [[NextIndex]] from the {iterator} and leverage the fact
5767 // that we definitely know that it's in Unsigned32 range since the
5768 // {iterated_object} is either a JSArray or a JSTypedArray. For the
5769 // latter case we even know that it's a Smi in UnsignedSmall range.
5770 FieldAccess index_access = AccessBuilder::ForJSArrayIteratorNextIndex();
5771 if (IsTypedArrayElementsKind(elements_kind)) {
5772 index_access.type = TypeCache::Get()->kJSTypedArrayLengthType;
5773 } else {
5774 index_access.type = TypeCache::Get()->kJSArrayLengthType;
5775 }
5776 Node* index = effect = graph()->NewNode(simplified()->LoadField(index_access),
5777 iterator, effect, control);
5778
5779 // Load the elements of the {iterated_object}. While it feels
5780 // counter-intuitive to place the elements pointer load before
5781 // the condition below, as it might not be needed (if the {index}
5782 // is out of bounds for the {iterated_object}), it's better this
5783 // way as it allows the LoadElimination to eliminate redundant
5784 // reloads of the elements pointer.
5785 Node* elements = effect = graph()->NewNode(
5786 simplified()->LoadField(AccessBuilder::ForJSObjectElements()),
5787 iterated_object, effect, control);
5788
5789 // Load the length of the {iterated_object}. Due to the map checks we
5790 // already know something about the length here, which we can leverage
5791 // to generate Word32 operations below without additional checking.
5792 FieldAccess length_access =
5793 IsTypedArrayElementsKind(elements_kind)
5794 ? AccessBuilder::ForJSTypedArrayLength()
5795 : AccessBuilder::ForJSArrayLength(elements_kind);
5796 Node* length = effect = graph()->NewNode(
5797 simplified()->LoadField(length_access), iterated_object, effect, control);
5798
5799 // Check whether {index} is within the valid range for the {iterated_object}.
5800 Node* check = graph()->NewNode(simplified()->NumberLessThan(), index, length);
5801 Node* branch =
5802 graph()->NewNode(common()->Branch(BranchHint::kNone), check, control);
5803
5804 Node* done_true;
5805 Node* value_true;
5806 Node* etrue = effect;
5807 Node* if_true = graph()->NewNode(common()->IfTrue(), branch);
5808 {
5809 // We know that the {index} is range of the {length} now.
5810 index = etrue = graph()->NewNode(
5811 common()->TypeGuard(
5812 Type::Range(0.0, length_access.type.Max() - 1.0, graph()->zone())),
5813 index, etrue, if_true);
5814
5815 done_true = jsgraph()->FalseConstant();
5816 if (iteration_kind == IterationKind::kKeys) {
5817 // Just return the {index}.
5818 value_true = index;
5819 } else {
5820 DCHECK(iteration_kind == IterationKind::kEntries ||((void) 0)
5821 iteration_kind == IterationKind::kValues)((void) 0);
5822
5823 if (IsTypedArrayElementsKind(elements_kind)) {
5824 Node* base_ptr = etrue =
5825 graph()->NewNode(simplified()->LoadField(
5826 AccessBuilder::ForJSTypedArrayBasePointer()),
5827 iterated_object, etrue, if_true);
5828 Node* external_ptr = etrue = graph()->NewNode(
5829 simplified()->LoadField(
5830 AccessBuilder::ForJSTypedArrayExternalPointer()),
5831 iterated_object, etrue, if_true);
5832
5833 ExternalArrayType array_type = kExternalInt8Array;
5834 switch (elements_kind) {
5835#define TYPED_ARRAY_CASE(Type, type, TYPE, ctype) \
5836 case TYPE##_ELEMENTS: \
5837 array_type = kExternal##Type##Array; \
5838 break;
5839 TYPED_ARRAYS(TYPED_ARRAY_CASE)TYPED_ARRAY_CASE(Uint8, uint8, UINT8, uint8_t) TYPED_ARRAY_CASE
(Int8, int8, INT8, int8_t) TYPED_ARRAY_CASE(Uint16, uint16, UINT16
, uint16_t) TYPED_ARRAY_CASE(Int16, int16, INT16, int16_t) TYPED_ARRAY_CASE
(Uint32, uint32, UINT32, uint32_t) TYPED_ARRAY_CASE(Int32, int32
, INT32, int32_t) TYPED_ARRAY_CASE(Float32, float32, FLOAT32,
float) TYPED_ARRAY_CASE(Float64, float64, FLOAT64, double) TYPED_ARRAY_CASE
(Uint8Clamped, uint8_clamped, UINT8_CLAMPED, uint8_t) TYPED_ARRAY_CASE
(BigUint64, biguint64, BIGUINT64, uint64_t) TYPED_ARRAY_CASE(
BigInt64, bigint64, BIGINT64, int64_t)
5840 default:
5841 UNREACHABLE()V8_Fatal("unreachable code");
5842#undef TYPED_ARRAY_CASE
5843 }
5844
5845 Node* buffer = etrue =
5846 graph()->NewNode(simplified()->LoadField(
5847 AccessBuilder::ForJSArrayBufferViewBuffer()),
5848 iterated_object, etrue, if_true);
5849
5850 value_true = etrue =
5851 graph()->NewNode(simplified()->LoadTypedElement(array_type), buffer,
5852 base_ptr, external_ptr, index, etrue, if_true);
5853 } else {
5854 value_true = etrue = graph()->NewNode(
5855 simplified()->LoadElement(
5856 AccessBuilder::ForFixedArrayElement(elements_kind)),
5857 elements, index, etrue, if_true);
5858
5859 // Convert hole to undefined if needed.
5860 if (elements_kind == HOLEY_ELEMENTS ||
5861 elements_kind == HOLEY_SMI_ELEMENTS) {
5862 value_true = graph()->NewNode(
5863 simplified()->ConvertTaggedHoleToUndefined(), value_true);
5864 } else if (elements_kind == HOLEY_DOUBLE_ELEMENTS) {
5865 // TODO(6587): avoid deopt if not all uses of value are truncated.
5866 CheckFloat64HoleMode mode = CheckFloat64HoleMode::kAllowReturnHole;
5867 value_true = etrue = graph()->NewNode(
5868 simplified()->CheckFloat64Hole(mode, p.feedback()), value_true,
5869 etrue, if_true);
5870 }
5871 }
5872
5873 if (iteration_kind == IterationKind::kEntries) {
5874 // Allocate elements for key/value pair
5875 value_true = etrue =
5876 graph()->NewNode(javascript()->CreateKeyValueArray(), index,
5877 value_true, context, etrue);
5878 } else {
5879 DCHECK_EQ(IterationKind::kValues, iteration_kind)((void) 0);
5880 }
5881 }
5882
5883 // Increment the [[NextIndex]] field in the {iterator}. The TypeGuards
5884 // above guarantee that the {next_index} is in the UnsignedSmall range.
5885 Node* next_index = graph()->NewNode(simplified()->NumberAdd(), index,
5886 jsgraph()->OneConstant());
5887 etrue = graph()->NewNode(simplified()->StoreField(index_access), iterator,
5888 next_index, etrue, if_true);
5889 }
5890
5891 Node* done_false;
5892 Node* value_false;
5893 Node* efalse = effect;
5894 Node* if_false = graph()->NewNode(common()->IfFalse(), branch);
5895 {
5896 // iterator.[[NextIndex]] >= array.length, stop iterating.
5897 done_false = jsgraph()->TrueConstant();
5898 value_false = jsgraph()->UndefinedConstant();
5899
5900 if (!IsTypedArrayElementsKind(elements_kind)) {
5901 // Mark the {iterator} as exhausted by setting the [[NextIndex]] to a
5902 // value that will never pass the length check again (aka the maximum
5903 // value possible for the specific iterated object). Note that this is
5904 // different from what the specification says, which is changing the
5905 // [[IteratedObject]] field to undefined, but that makes it difficult
5906 // to eliminate the map checks and "length" accesses in for..of loops.
5907 //
5908 // This is not necessary for JSTypedArray's, since the length of those
5909 // cannot change later and so if we were ever out of bounds for them
5910 // we will stay out-of-bounds forever.
5911 Node* end_index = jsgraph()->Constant(index_access.type.Max());
5912 efalse = graph()->NewNode(simplified()->StoreField(index_access),
5913 iterator, end_index, efalse, if_false);
5914 }
5915 }
5916
5917 control = graph()->NewNode(common()->Merge(2), if_true, if_false);
5918 effect = graph()->NewNode(common()->EffectPhi(2), etrue, efalse, control);
5919 Node* value =
5920 graph()->NewNode(common()->Phi(MachineRepresentation::kTagged, 2),
5921 value_true, value_false, control);
5922 Node* done =
5923 graph()->NewNode(common()->Phi(MachineRepresentation::kTagged, 2),
5924 done_true, done_false, control);
5925
5926 // Create IteratorResult object.
5927 value = effect = graph()->NewNode(javascript()->CreateIterResultObject(),
5928 value, done, context, effect);
5929 ReplaceWithValue(node, value, effect, control);
5930 return Replace(value);
5931}
5932
5933// ES6 section 21.1.3.2 String.prototype.charCodeAt ( pos )
5934// ES6 section 21.1.3.3 String.prototype.codePointAt ( pos )
5935Reduction JSCallReducer::ReduceStringPrototypeStringAt(
5936 const Operator* string_access_operator, Node* node) {
5937 DCHECK(string_access_operator->opcode() == IrOpcode::kStringCharCodeAt ||((void) 0)
5938 string_access_operator->opcode() == IrOpcode::kStringCodePointAt)((void) 0);
5939 JSCallNode n(node);
5940 CallParameters const& p = n.Parameters();
5941 if (p.speculation_mode() == SpeculationMode::kDisallowSpeculation) {
5942 return NoChange();
5943 }
5944
5945 Node* receiver = n.receiver();
5946 Node* index = n.ArgumentOr(0, jsgraph()->ZeroConstant());
5947 Effect effect = n.effect();
5948 Control control = n.control();
5949
5950 // Ensure that the {receiver} is actually a String.
5951 receiver = effect = graph()->NewNode(simplified()->CheckString(p.feedback()),
5952 receiver, effect, control);
5953
5954 // Determine the {receiver} length.
5955 Node* receiver_length =
5956 graph()->NewNode(simplified()->StringLength(), receiver);
5957
5958 // Check that the {index} is within range.
5959 index = effect = graph()->NewNode(simplified()->CheckBounds(p.feedback()),
5960 index, receiver_length, effect, control);
5961
5962 // Return the character from the {receiver} as single character string.
5963 Node* masked_index = graph()->NewNode(simplified()->PoisonIndex(), index);
5964 Node* value = effect = graph()->NewNode(string_access_operator, receiver,
5965 masked_index, effect, control);
5966
5967 ReplaceWithValue(node, value, effect, control);
5968 return Replace(value);
5969}
5970
5971// ES section 21.1.3.20
5972// String.prototype.startsWith ( searchString [ , position ] )
5973Reduction JSCallReducer::ReduceStringPrototypeStartsWith(Node* node) {
5974 JSCallNode n(node);
5975 CallParameters const& p = n.Parameters();
5976 if (p.speculation_mode() == SpeculationMode::kDisallowSpeculation) {
5977 return NoChange();
5978 }
5979
5980 Node* receiver = n.receiver();
5981 Effect effect = n.effect();
5982 Control control = n.control();
5983
5984 if (n.ArgumentCount() < 1) {
5985 effect = graph()->NewNode(simplified()->CheckString(p.feedback()), receiver,
5986 effect, control);
5987
5988 Node* value = jsgraph()->FalseConstant();
5989 ReplaceWithValue(node, value, effect, control);
5990 return Replace(value);
5991 }
5992
5993 Node* search_string = n.Argument(0);
5994 Node* position = n.ArgumentOr(1, jsgraph()->ZeroConstant());
5995
5996 HeapObjectMatcher m(search_string);
5997 if (m.HasValue()) {
5998 ObjectRef target_ref = m.Ref(broker());
5999 if (target_ref.IsString()) {
6000 StringRef str = target_ref.AsString();
6001 if (str.length() == 1) {
6002 receiver = effect = graph()->NewNode(
6003 simplified()->CheckString(p.feedback()), receiver, effect, control);
6004
6005 position = effect = graph()->NewNode(
6006 simplified()->CheckSmi(p.feedback()), position, effect, control);
6007
6008 Node* string_length =
6009 graph()->NewNode(simplified()->StringLength(), receiver);
6010 Node* unsigned_position = graph()->NewNode(
6011 simplified()->NumberMax(), position, jsgraph()->ZeroConstant());
6012
6013 Node* check = graph()->NewNode(simplified()->NumberLessThan(),
6014 unsigned_position, string_length);
6015 Node* branch = graph()->NewNode(common()->Branch(BranchHint::kNone),
6016 check, control);
6017
6018 Node* if_false = graph()->NewNode(common()->IfFalse(), branch);
6019 Node* efalse = effect;
6020 Node* vfalse = jsgraph()->FalseConstant();
6021
6022 Node* if_true = graph()->NewNode(common()->IfTrue(), branch);
6023 Node* etrue = effect;
6024 Node* vtrue;
6025 {
6026 Node* masked_position =
6027 graph()->NewNode(simplified()->PoisonIndex(), unsigned_position);
6028 Node* string_first = etrue =
6029 graph()->NewNode(simplified()->StringCharCodeAt(), receiver,
6030 masked_position, etrue, if_true);
6031
6032 Node* search_first = jsgraph()->Constant(str.GetFirstChar());
6033 vtrue = graph()->NewNode(simplified()->NumberEqual(), string_first,
6034 search_first);
6035 }
6036
6037 control = graph()->NewNode(common()->Merge(2), if_true, if_false);
6038 Node* value =
6039 graph()->NewNode(common()->Phi(MachineRepresentation::kTagged, 2),
6040 vtrue, vfalse, control);
6041 effect =
6042 graph()->NewNode(common()->EffectPhi(2), etrue, efalse, control);
6043
6044 ReplaceWithValue(node, value, effect, control);
6045 return Replace(value);
6046 }
6047 }
6048 }
6049
6050 return NoChange();
6051}
6052
6053// ES section 21.1.3.1 String.prototype.charAt ( pos )
6054Reduction JSCallReducer::ReduceStringPrototypeCharAt(Node* node) {
6055 JSCallNode n(node);
6056 CallParameters const& p = n.Parameters();
6057 if (p.speculation_mode() == SpeculationMode::kDisallowSpeculation) {
6058 return NoChange();
6059 }
6060
6061 Node* receiver = n.receiver();
6062 Node* index = n.ArgumentOr(0, jsgraph()->ZeroConstant());
6063 Effect effect = n.effect();
6064 Control control = n.control();
6065
6066 // Ensure that the {receiver} is actually a String.
6067 receiver = effect = graph()->NewNode(simplified()->CheckString(p.feedback()),
6068 receiver, effect, control);
6069
6070 // Determine the {receiver} length.
6071 Node* receiver_length =
6072 graph()->NewNode(simplified()->StringLength(), receiver);
6073
6074 // Check that the {index} is within range.
6075 index = effect = graph()->NewNode(simplified()->CheckBounds(p.feedback()),
6076 index, receiver_length, effect, control);
6077
6078 // Return the character from the {receiver} as single character string.
6079 Node* masked_index = graph()->NewNode(simplified()->PoisonIndex(), index);
6080 Node* value = effect =
6081 graph()->NewNode(simplified()->StringCharCodeAt(), receiver, masked_index,
6082 effect, control);
6083 value = graph()->NewNode(simplified()->StringFromSingleCharCode(), value);
6084
6085 ReplaceWithValue(node, value, effect, control);
6086 return Replace(value);
6087}

6091Reduction JSCallReducer::ReduceStringPrototypeToLowerCaseIntl(Node* node) {
6092 JSCallNode n(node);
6093 CallParameters const& p = n.Parameters();
6094 if (p.speculation_mode() == SpeculationMode::kDisallowSpeculation) {
6095 return NoChange();
6096 }
6097 Effect effect = n.effect();
6098 Control control = n.control();
6099
6100 Node* receiver = effect = graph()->NewNode(
6101 simplified()->CheckString(p.feedback()), n.receiver(), effect, control);
6102
6103 NodeProperties::ReplaceEffectInput(node, effect);
6104 RelaxEffectsAndControls(node);
6105 node->ReplaceInput(0, receiver);
6106 node->TrimInputCount(1);
6107 NodeProperties::ChangeOp(node, simplified()->StringToLowerCaseIntl());
6108 NodeProperties::SetType(node, Type::String());
6109 return Changed(node);

6111
6112Reduction JSCallReducer::ReduceStringPrototypeToUpperCaseIntl(Node* node) {
6113 JSCallNode n(node);
6114 CallParameters const& p = n.Parameters();
6115 if (p.speculation_mode() == SpeculationMode::kDisallowSpeculation) {
6116 return NoChange();
6117 }
6118 Effect effect = n.effect();
6119 Control control = n.control();
6120
6121 Node* receiver = effect = graph()->NewNode(
6122 simplified()->CheckString(p.feedback()), n.receiver(), effect, control);
6123
6124 NodeProperties::ReplaceEffectInput(node, effect);
6125 RelaxEffectsAndControls(node);
6126 node->ReplaceInput(0, receiver);
6127 node->TrimInputCount(1);
6128 NodeProperties::ChangeOp(node, simplified()->StringToUpperCaseIntl());
6129 NodeProperties::SetType(node, Type::String());
6130 return Changed(node);
6131}
6132
6133#endif // V8_INTL_SUPPORT

6136Reduction JSCallReducer::ReduceStringFromCharCode(Node* node) {
6137 JSCallNode n(node);
6138 CallParameters const& p = n.Parameters();
6139 if (p.speculation_mode() == SpeculationMode::kDisallowSpeculation) {
6140 return NoChange();
6141 }
6142 if (n.ArgumentCount() == 1) {
6143 Effect effect = n.effect();
6144 Control control = n.control();
6145 Node* input = n.Argument(0);
6146
6147 input = effect = graph()->NewNode(
6148 simplified()->SpeculativeToNumber(NumberOperationHint::kNumberOrOddball,
6149 p.feedback()),
6150 input, effect, control);
6151
6152 Node* value =
6153 graph()->NewNode(simplified()->StringFromSingleCharCode(), input);
6154 ReplaceWithValue(node, value, effect);
6155 return Replace(value);

6157 return NoChange();

6184Reduction JSCallReducer::ReduceStringPrototypeIterator(Node* node) {
6185 // TODO(jgruber): We could reduce here when generating native context
6186 // independent code, if LowerJSCreateStringIterator were implemented in
6187 // generic lowering.
6188 if (broker()->is_native_context_independent()) return NoChange();
6189 JSCallNode n(node);
6190 CallParameters const& p = n.Parameters();
6191 if (p.speculation_mode() == SpeculationMode::kDisallowSpeculation) {
6192 return NoChange();
6193 }
6194 Node* effect = NodeProperties::GetEffectInput(node);
6195 Node* control = NodeProperties::GetControlInput(node);
6196 Node* receiver = effect = graph()->NewNode(
6197 simplified()->CheckString(p.feedback()), n.receiver(), effect, control);
6198 Node* iterator = effect =
6199 graph()->NewNode(javascript()->CreateStringIterator(), receiver,
6200 jsgraph()->NoContextConstant(), effect);
6201 ReplaceWithValue(node, iterator, effect, control);
6202 return Replace(iterator);

6204
6205Reduction JSCallReducer::ReduceStringIteratorPrototypeNext(Node* node) {
6206 JSCallNode n(node);
6207 Node* receiver = n.receiver();
6208 Effect effect = n.effect();
6209 Control control = n.control();
6210 Node* context = n.context();
6211
6212 MapInference inference(broker(), receiver, effect);
6213 if (!inference.HaveMaps() ||
6214 !inference.AllOfInstanceTypesAre(JS_STRING_ITERATOR_TYPE)) {
6215 return NoChange();
6216 }
6217
6218 Node* string = effect = graph()->NewNode(
6219 simplified()->LoadField(AccessBuilder::ForJSStringIteratorString()),
6220 receiver, effect, control);
6221 Node* index = effect = graph()->NewNode(
6222 simplified()->LoadField(AccessBuilder::ForJSStringIteratorIndex()),
6223 receiver, effect, control);
6224 Node* length = graph()->NewNode(simplified()->StringLength(), string);
6225
6226 // branch0: if (index < length)
6227 Node* check0 =
6228 graph()->NewNode(simplified()->NumberLessThan(), index, length);
6229 Node* branch0 =
6230 graph()->NewNode(common()->Branch(BranchHint::kNone), check0, control);
6231
6232 Node* etrue0 = effect;
6233 Node* if_true0 = graph()->NewNode(common()->IfTrue(), branch0);
6234 Node* done_true;
6235 Node* vtrue0;
6236 {
6237 done_true = jsgraph()->FalseConstant();
6238 vtrue0 = etrue0 = graph()->NewNode(simplified()->StringFromCodePointAt(),
6239 string, index, etrue0, if_true0);
6240
6241 // Update iterator.[[NextIndex]]
6242 Node* char_length = graph()->NewNode(simplified()->StringLength(), vtrue0);
6243 index = graph()->NewNode(simplified()->NumberAdd(), index, char_length);
6244 etrue0 = graph()->NewNode(
6245 simplified()->StoreField(AccessBuilder::ForJSStringIteratorIndex()),
6246 receiver, index, etrue0, if_true0);
6247 }
6248
6249 Node* if_false0 = graph()->NewNode(common()->IfFalse(), branch0);
6250 Node* done_false;
6251 Node* vfalse0;
6252 {
6253 vfalse0 = jsgraph()->UndefinedConstant();
6254 done_false = jsgraph()->TrueConstant();
6255 }
6256
6257 control = graph()->NewNode(common()->Merge(2), if_true0, if_false0);
6258 effect = graph()->NewNode(common()->EffectPhi(2), etrue0, effect, control);
6259 Node* value =
6260 graph()->NewNode(common()->Phi(MachineRepresentation::kTagged, 2), vtrue0,
6261 vfalse0, control);
6262 Node* done =
6263 graph()->NewNode(common()->Phi(MachineRepresentation::kTagged, 2),
6264 done_true, done_false, control);
6265
6266 value = effect = graph()->NewNode(javascript()->CreateIterResultObject(),
6267 value, done, context, effect);
6268
6269 ReplaceWithValue(node, value, effect, control);
6270 return Replace(value);
6271}

6273// ES #sec-string.prototype.concat
6274Reduction JSCallReducer::ReduceStringPrototypeConcat(Node* node) {
6275 JSCallNode n(node);
6276 CallParameters const& p = n.Parameters();
6277 const int parameter_count = n.ArgumentCount();
6278 if (parameter_count > 1) return NoChange();
6279 if (p.speculation_mode() == SpeculationMode::kDisallowSpeculation) {
6280 return NoChange();
6281 }
6282
6283 Effect effect = n.effect();
6284 Control control = n.control();
6285 Node* receiver = effect = graph()->NewNode(
6286 simplified()->CheckString(p.feedback()), n.receiver(), effect, control);
6287
6288 if (parameter_count == 0) {
6289 ReplaceWithValue(node, receiver, effect, control);
6290 return Replace(receiver);
6291 }
6292
6293 Node* argument = effect = graph()->NewNode(
6294 simplified()->CheckString(p.feedback()), n.Argument(0), effect, control);
6295 Node* receiver_length =
6296 graph()->NewNode(simplified()->StringLength(), receiver);
6297 Node* argument_length =
6298 graph()->NewNode(simplified()->StringLength(), argument);
6299 Node* length = graph()->NewNode(simplified()->NumberAdd(), receiver_length,
6300 argument_length);
6301 length = effect = graph()->NewNode(
6302 simplified()->CheckBounds(p.feedback()), length,
6303 jsgraph()->Constant(String::kMaxLength + 1), effect, control);
6304
6305 Node* value = graph()->NewNode(simplified()->StringConcat(), length, receiver,
6306 argument);
6307
6308 ReplaceWithValue(node, value, effect, control);
6309 return Replace(value);
6310}
6311
6312Reduction JSCallReducer::ReducePromiseConstructor(Node* node) {
6313 // TODO(jgruber): We could reduce here when generating native context
6314 // independent code, if LowerJSCreatePromise were implemented in generic
6315 // lowering.
6316 if (broker()->is_native_context_independent()) return NoChange();
6317
6318 DisallowHeapAccessIf no_heap_access(should_disallow_heap_access());
6319 PromiseBuiltinReducerAssembler a(jsgraph(), temp_zone(), node, broker());
6320
6321 // We only inline when we have the executor.
6322 if (a.ConstructArity() < 1) return NoChange();
6323 // Only handle builtins Promises, not subclasses.
6324 if (a.TargetInput() != a.NewTargetInput()) return NoChange();
6325 if (!dependencies()->DependOnPromiseHookProtector()) return NoChange();
6326
6327 TNode<Object> subgraph = a.ReducePromiseConstructor(native_context());
6328 return ReplaceWithSubgraph(&a, subgraph);
6329}
6330
6331bool JSCallReducer::DoPromiseChecks(MapInference* inference) {
6332 if (!inference->HaveMaps()) return false;
6333 MapHandles const& receiver_maps = inference->GetMaps();
6334
6335 // Check whether all {receiver_maps} are JSPromise maps and
6336 // have the initial Promise.prototype as their [[Prototype]].
6337 for (Handle<Map> map : receiver_maps) {
6338 MapRef receiver_map(broker(), map);
6339 if (!receiver_map.IsJSPromiseMap()) return false;
6340 if (should_disallow_heap_access() && !receiver_map.serialized_prototype()) {
6341 TRACE_BROKER_MISSING(broker(), "prototype for map " << receiver_map)do { if (broker()->tracing_enabled()) StdoutStream{} <<
broker()->Trace() << "Missing " << "prototype for map "
<< receiver_map << " (" << "../deps/v8/src/compiler/js-call-reducer.cc"
<< ":" << 6341 << ")" << std::endl; }
while (false);
6342 return false;
6343 }
6344 if (!receiver_map.prototype().equals(
6345 native_context().promise_prototype())) {
6346 return false;
6347 }
6348 }
6349
6350 return true;
6351}
6352
6353// ES section #sec-promise.prototype.catch
6354Reduction JSCallReducer::ReducePromisePrototypeCatch(Node* node) {
6355 JSCallNode n(node);
6356 CallParameters const& p = n.Parameters();
6357 if (p.speculation_mode() == SpeculationMode::kDisallowSpeculation) {
6358 return NoChange();
6359 }
6360 int arity = p.arity_without_implicit_args();
6361 Node* receiver = n.receiver();
6362 Effect effect = n.effect();
6363 Control control = n.control();
6364
6365 MapInference inference(broker(), receiver, effect);
6366 if (!DoPromiseChecks(&inference)) return inference.NoChange();
6367
6368 if (!dependencies()->DependOnPromiseThenProtector()) {
6369 return inference.NoChange();
6370 }
6371 inference.RelyOnMapsPreferStability(dependencies(), jsgraph(), &effect,
6372 control, p.feedback());
6373
6374 // Massage the {node} to call "then" instead by first removing all inputs
6375 // following the onRejected parameter, and then filling up the parameters
6376 // to two inputs from the left with undefined.
6377 Node* target = jsgraph()->Constant(native_context().promise_then());
6378 NodeProperties::ReplaceValueInput(node, target, 0);
6379 NodeProperties::ReplaceEffectInput(node, effect);
6380 for (; arity > 1; --arity) node->RemoveInput(3);
6381 for (; arity < 2; ++arity) {
6382 node->InsertInput(graph()->zone(), 2, jsgraph()->UndefinedConstant());
6383 }
6384 NodeProperties::ChangeOp(
6385 node, javascript()->Call(
6386 JSCallNode::ArityForArgc(arity), p.frequency(), p.feedback(),
6387 ConvertReceiverMode::kNotNullOrUndefined, p.speculation_mode(),
6388 CallFeedbackRelation::kUnrelated));
6389 return Changed(node).FollowedBy(ReducePromisePrototypeThen(node));
6390}
6391
6392Node* JSCallReducer::CreateClosureFromBuiltinSharedFunctionInfo(
6393 SharedFunctionInfoRef shared, Node* context, Node* effect, Node* control) {
6394 DCHECK(shared.HasBuiltinId())((void) 0);
6395 Handle<FeedbackCell> feedback_cell =
6396 isolate()->factory()->many_closures_cell();
6397 Callable const callable = Builtins::CallableFor(
6398 isolate(), static_cast<Builtins::Name>(shared.builtin_id()));
6399 return graph()->NewNode(
6400 javascript()->CreateClosure(shared.object(), callable.code()),
6401 jsgraph()->HeapConstant(feedback_cell), context, effect, control);
6402}
6403
6404// ES section #sec-promise.prototype.finally
6405Reduction JSCallReducer::ReducePromisePrototypeFinally(Node* node) {
6406 DisallowHeapAccessIf no_heap_access(should_disallow_heap_access());
6407
6408 JSCallNode n(node);
6409 CallParameters const& p = n.Parameters();
6410 int arity = p.arity_without_implicit_args();
6411 Node* receiver = n.receiver();
6412 Node* on_finally = n.ArgumentOrUndefined(0, jsgraph());
6413 Effect effect = n.effect();
6414 Control control = n.control();
6415 if (p.speculation_mode() == SpeculationMode::kDisallowSpeculation) {
6416 return NoChange();
6417 }
6418
6419 MapInference inference(broker(), receiver, effect);
6420 if (!DoPromiseChecks(&inference)) return inference.NoChange();
6421 MapHandles const& receiver_maps = inference.GetMaps();
6422
6423 if (!dependencies()->DependOnPromiseHookProtector()) {
6424 return inference.NoChange();
6425 }
6426 if (!dependencies()->DependOnPromiseThenProtector()) {
6427 return inference.NoChange();
6428 }
6429 if (!dependencies()->DependOnPromiseSpeciesProtector()) {
6430 return inference.NoChange();
6431 }
6432 inference.RelyOnMapsPreferStability(dependencies(), jsgraph(), &effect,
6433 control, p.feedback());
6434
6435 // Check if {on_finally} is callable, and if so wrap it into appropriate
6436 // closures that perform the finalization.
6437 Node* check = graph()->NewNode(simplified()->ObjectIsCallable(), on_finally);
6438 Node* branch =
6439 graph()->NewNode(common()->Branch(BranchHint::kTrue), check, control);
6440
6441 Node* if_true = graph()->NewNode(common()->IfTrue(), branch);
6442 Node* etrue = effect;
6443 Node* catch_true;
6444 Node* then_true;
6445 {
6446 Node* context = jsgraph()->Constant(native_context());
6447 Node* constructor =
6448 jsgraph()->Constant(native_context().promise_function());
6449
6450 // Allocate shared context for the closures below.
6451 context = etrue =
6452 graph()->NewNode(javascript()->CreateFunctionContext(
6453 native_context().scope_info().object(),
6454 PromiseBuiltins::kPromiseFinallyContextLength -
6455 Context::MIN_CONTEXT_SLOTS,
6456 FUNCTION_SCOPE),
6457 context, etrue, if_true);
6458 etrue = graph()->NewNode(
6459 simplified()->StoreField(
6460 AccessBuilder::ForContextSlot(PromiseBuiltins::kOnFinallySlot)),
6461 context, on_finally, etrue, if_true);
6462 etrue = graph()->NewNode(
6463 simplified()->StoreField(
6464 AccessBuilder::ForContextSlot(PromiseBuiltins::kConstructorSlot)),
6465 context, constructor, etrue, if_true);
6466
6467 // Allocate the closure for the reject case.
6468 SharedFunctionInfoRef promise_catch_finally(
6469 broker(), factory()->promise_catch_finally_shared_fun());
6470 catch_true = etrue = CreateClosureFromBuiltinSharedFunctionInfo(
6471 promise_catch_finally, context, etrue, if_true);
6472
6473 // Allocate the closure for the fulfill case.
6474 SharedFunctionInfoRef promise_then_finally(
6475 broker(), factory()->promise_then_finally_shared_fun());
6476 then_true = etrue = CreateClosureFromBuiltinSharedFunctionInfo(
6477 promise_then_finally, context, etrue, if_true);
6478 }
6479
6480 Node* if_false = graph()->NewNode(common()->IfFalse(), branch);
6481 Node* efalse = effect;
6482 Node* catch_false = on_finally;
6483 Node* then_false = on_finally;
6484
6485 control = graph()->NewNode(common()->Merge(2), if_true, if_false);
6486 effect = graph()->NewNode(common()->EffectPhi(2), etrue, efalse, control);
6487 Node* catch_finally =
6488 graph()->NewNode(common()->Phi(MachineRepresentation::kTagged, 2),
6489 catch_true, catch_false, control);
6490 Node* then_finally =
6491 graph()->NewNode(common()->Phi(MachineRepresentation::kTagged, 2),
6492 then_true, then_false, control);
6493
6494 // At this point we definitely know that {receiver} has one of the
6495 // {receiver_maps}, so insert a MapGuard as a hint for the lowering
6496 // of the call to "then" below.
6497 {
6498 ZoneHandleSet<Map> maps;
6499 for (Handle<Map> map : receiver_maps) maps.insert(map, graph()->zone());
6500 effect = graph()->NewNode(simplified()->MapGuard(maps), receiver, effect,
6501 control);
6502 }
6503
6504 // Massage the {node} to call "then" instead by first removing all inputs
6505 // following the onFinally parameter, and then replacing the only parameter
6506 // input with the {on_finally} value.
6507 Node* target = jsgraph()->Constant(native_context().promise_then());
6508 NodeProperties::ReplaceValueInput(node, target, n.TargetIndex());
6509 NodeProperties::ReplaceEffectInput(node, effect);
6510 NodeProperties::ReplaceControlInput(node, control);
6511 for (; arity > 2; --arity) node->RemoveInput(2);
6512 for (; arity < 2; ++arity) {
6513 node->InsertInput(graph()->zone(), 2, then_finally);
6514 }
6515 node->ReplaceInput(2, then_finally);
6516 node->ReplaceInput(3, catch_finally);
6517 NodeProperties::ChangeOp(
6518 node, javascript()->Call(
6519 JSCallNode::ArityForArgc(arity), p.frequency(), p.feedback(),
6520 ConvertReceiverMode::kNotNullOrUndefined, p.speculation_mode(),
6521 CallFeedbackRelation::kUnrelated));
6522 return Changed(node).FollowedBy(ReducePromisePrototypeThen(node));
6523}
6524
6525Reduction JSCallReducer::ReducePromisePrototypeThen(Node* node) {
6526 DisallowHeapAccessIf no_heap_access(should_disallow_heap_access());
6527
6528 JSCallNode n(node);
6529 CallParameters const& p = n.Parameters();
6530 if (p.speculation_mode() == SpeculationMode::kDisallowSpeculation) {
6531 return NoChange();
6532 }
6533
6534 Node* receiver = n.receiver();
6535 Node* on_fulfilled = n.ArgumentOrUndefined(0, jsgraph());
6536 Node* on_rejected = n.ArgumentOrUndefined(1, jsgraph());
6537 Node* context = n.context();
6538 Effect effect = n.effect();
6539 Control control = n.control();
6540 FrameState frame_state = n.frame_state();
6541
6542 MapInference inference(broker(), receiver, effect);
6543 if (!DoPromiseChecks(&inference)) return inference.NoChange();
6544
6545 if (!dependencies()->DependOnPromiseHookProtector()) {
6546 return inference.NoChange();
6547 }
6548 if (!dependencies()->DependOnPromiseSpeciesProtector()) {
6549 return inference.NoChange();
6550 }
6551 inference.RelyOnMapsPreferStability(dependencies(), jsgraph(), &effect,
6552 control, p.feedback());
6553
6554 // Check that {on_fulfilled} is callable.
6555 on_fulfilled = graph()->NewNode(
6556 common()->Select(MachineRepresentation::kTagged, BranchHint::kTrue),
6557 graph()->NewNode(simplified()->ObjectIsCallable(), on_fulfilled),
6558 on_fulfilled, jsgraph()->UndefinedConstant());
6559
6560 // Check that {on_rejected} is callable.
6561 on_rejected = graph()->NewNode(
6562 common()->Select(MachineRepresentation::kTagged, BranchHint::kTrue),
6563 graph()->NewNode(simplified()->ObjectIsCallable(), on_rejected),
6564 on_rejected, jsgraph()->UndefinedConstant());
6565
6566 // Create the resulting JSPromise.
6567 Node* promise = effect =
6568 graph()->NewNode(javascript()->CreatePromise(), context, effect);
6569
6570 // Chain {result} onto {receiver}.
6571 promise = effect = graph()->NewNode(
6572 javascript()->PerformPromiseThen(), receiver, on_fulfilled, on_rejected,
6573 promise, context, frame_state, effect, control);
6574
6575 // At this point we know that {promise} is going to have the
6576 // initial Promise map, since even if {PerformPromiseThen}
6577 // above called into the host rejection tracker, the {promise}
6578 // doesn't escape to user JavaScript. So bake this information
6579 // into the graph such that subsequent passes can use the
6580 // information for further optimizations.
6581 MapRef promise_map = native_context().promise_function().initial_map();
6582 effect = graph()->NewNode(
6583 simplified()->MapGuard(ZoneHandleSet<Map>(promise_map.object())), promise,
6584 effect, control);
6585
6586 ReplaceWithValue(node, promise, effect, control);
6587 return Replace(promise);
6588}
6589
6590// ES section #sec-promise.resolve
6591Reduction JSCallReducer::ReducePromiseResolveTrampoline(Node* node) {
6592 DisallowHeapAccessIf no_heap_access(should_disallow_heap_access());
6593
6594 JSCallNode n(node);
6595 Node* receiver = n.receiver();
6596 Node* value = n.ArgumentOrUndefined(0, jsgraph());
6597 Node* context = n.context();
6598 Effect effect = n.effect();
6599 Control control = n.control();
6600 FrameState frame_state = n.frame_state();
6601
6602 // Only reduce when the receiver is guaranteed to be a JSReceiver.
6603 MapInference inference(broker(), receiver, effect);
6604 if (!inference.HaveMaps() || !inference.AllOfInstanceTypesAreJSReceiver()) {
6605 return NoChange();
6606 }
6607
6608 // Morph the {node} into a JSPromiseResolve operation.
6609 node->ReplaceInput(0, receiver);
6610 node->ReplaceInput(1, value);
6611 node->ReplaceInput(2, context);
6612 node->ReplaceInput(3, frame_state);
6613 node->ReplaceInput(4, effect);
6614 node->ReplaceInput(5, control);
6615 node->TrimInputCount(6);
6616 NodeProperties::ChangeOp(node, javascript()->PromiseResolve());
6617 return Changed(node);
6618}
6619
6620// ES #sec-typedarray-constructors
6621Reduction JSCallReducer::ReduceTypedArrayConstructor(
6622 Node* node, const SharedFunctionInfoRef& shared) {
6623 JSConstructNode n(node);
6624 ConstructParameters const& p = n.Parameters();
6625 int arity = p.arity_without_implicit_args();
6626 Node* target = n.target();
6627 Node* arg0 = n.ArgumentOrUndefined(0, jsgraph());
6628 Node* arg1 = n.ArgumentOrUndefined(1, jsgraph());
6629 Node* arg2 = n.ArgumentOrUndefined(2, jsgraph());
6630 Node* new_target = n.new_target();
6631 Node* context = n.context();
6632 FrameState frame_state = n.frame_state();
6633 Effect effect = n.effect();
6634 Control control = n.control();
6635
6636 // Insert a construct stub frame into the chain of frame states. This will
6637 // reconstruct the proper frame when deoptimizing within the constructor.
6638 frame_state = CreateArtificialFrameState(
6639 node, frame_state, arity, BailoutId::ConstructStubInvoke(),
6640 FrameStateType::kConstructStub, shared, context, common(), graph());
6641
6642 // This continuation just returns the newly created JSTypedArray. We
6643 // pass the_hole as the receiver, just like the builtin construct stub
6644 // does in this case.
6645 Node* const parameters[] = {jsgraph()->TheHoleConstant()};
6646 int const num_parameters = static_cast<int>(arraysize(parameters)(sizeof(ArraySizeHelper(parameters))));
6647 frame_state = CreateJavaScriptBuiltinContinuationFrameState(
6648 jsgraph(), shared, Builtins::kGenericLazyDeoptContinuation, target,
6649 context, parameters, num_parameters, frame_state,
6650 ContinuationFrameStateMode::LAZY);
6651
6652 Node* result =
6653 graph()->NewNode(javascript()->CreateTypedArray(), target, new_target,
6654 arg0, arg1, arg2, context, frame_state, effect, control);
6655 return Replace(result);
6656}
6657
6658// ES #sec-get-%typedarray%.prototype-@@tostringtag
6659Reduction JSCallReducer::ReduceTypedArrayPrototypeToStringTag(Node* node) {
6660 Node* receiver = NodeProperties::GetValueInput(node, 1);
6661 Node* effect = NodeProperties::GetEffectInput(node);
6662 Node* control = NodeProperties::GetControlInput(node);
6663
6664 NodeVector values(graph()->zone());
6665 NodeVector effects(graph()->zone());
6666 NodeVector controls(graph()->zone());
6667
6668 Node* check = graph()->NewNode(simplified()->ObjectIsSmi(), receiver);
6669 control =
6670 graph()->NewNode(common()->Branch(BranchHint::kFalse), check, control);
6671
6672 values.push_back(jsgraph()->UndefinedConstant());
6673 effects.push_back(effect);
6674 controls.push_back(graph()->NewNode(common()->IfTrue(), control));
6675
6676 control = graph()->NewNode(common()->IfFalse(), control);
6677 Node* receiver_map = effect =
6678 graph()->NewNode(simplified()->LoadField(AccessBuilder::ForMap()),
6679 receiver, effect, control);
6680 Node* receiver_bit_field2 = effect = graph()->NewNode(
6681 simplified()->LoadField(AccessBuilder::ForMapBitField2()), receiver_map,
6682 effect, control);
6683 Node* receiver_elements_kind = graph()->NewNode(
6684 simplified()->NumberShiftRightLogical(),
6685 graph()->NewNode(
6686 simplified()->NumberBitwiseAnd(), receiver_bit_field2,
6687 jsgraph()->Constant(Map::Bits2::ElementsKindBits::kMask)),
6688 jsgraph()->Constant(Map::Bits2::ElementsKindBits::kShift));
6689
6690 // Offset the elements kind by FIRST_FIXED_TYPED_ARRAY_ELEMENTS_KIND,
6691 // so that the branch cascade below is turned into a simple table
6692 // switch by the ControlFlowOptimizer later.
6693 receiver_elements_kind = graph()->NewNode(
6694 simplified()->NumberSubtract(), receiver_elements_kind,
6695 jsgraph()->Constant(FIRST_FIXED_TYPED_ARRAY_ELEMENTS_KIND));
6696
6697#define TYPED_ARRAY_CASE(Type, type, TYPE, ctype) \
6698 do { \
6699 Node* check = graph()->NewNode( \
6700 simplified()->NumberEqual(), receiver_elements_kind, \
6701 jsgraph()->Constant(TYPE##_ELEMENTS - \
6702 FIRST_FIXED_TYPED_ARRAY_ELEMENTS_KIND)); \
6703 control = graph()->NewNode(common()->Branch(), check, control); \
6704 values.push_back(jsgraph()->Constant( \
6705 broker()->GetTypedArrayStringTag(TYPE##_ELEMENTS))); \
6706 effects.push_back(effect); \
6707 controls.push_back(graph()->NewNode(common()->IfTrue(), control)); \
6708 control = graph()->NewNode(common()->IfFalse(), control); \
6709 } while (false);
6710 TYPED_ARRAYS(TYPED_ARRAY_CASE)TYPED_ARRAY_CASE(Uint8, uint8, UINT8, uint8_t) TYPED_ARRAY_CASE
(Int8, int8, INT8, int8_t) TYPED_ARRAY_CASE(Uint16, uint16, UINT16
, uint16_t) TYPED_ARRAY_CASE(Int16, int16, INT16, int16_t) TYPED_ARRAY_CASE
(Uint32, uint32, UINT32, uint32_t) TYPED_ARRAY_CASE(Int32, int32
, INT32, int32_t) TYPED_ARRAY_CASE(Float32, float32, FLOAT32,
float) TYPED_ARRAY_CASE(Float64, float64, FLOAT64, double) TYPED_ARRAY_CASE
(Uint8Clamped, uint8_clamped, UINT8_CLAMPED, uint8_t) TYPED_ARRAY_CASE
(BigUint64, biguint64, BIGUINT64, uint64_t) TYPED_ARRAY_CASE(
BigInt64, bigint64, BIGINT64, int64_t)
6711#undef TYPED_ARRAY_CASE
6712
6713 values.push_back(jsgraph()->UndefinedConstant());
6714 effects.push_back(effect);
6715 controls.push_back(control);
6716
6717 int const count = static_cast<int>(controls.size());
6718 control = graph()->NewNode(common()->Merge(count), count, &controls.front());
6719 effects.push_back(control);
6720 effect =
6721 graph()->NewNode(common()->EffectPhi(count), count + 1, &effects.front());
6722 values.push_back(control);
6723 Node* value =
6724 graph()->NewNode(common()->Phi(MachineRepresentation::kTagged, count),
6725 count + 1, &values.front());
6726 ReplaceWithValue(node, value, effect, control);
6727 return Replace(value);
6728}

6734 Node* value = jsgraph()->FalseConstant();
6735 ReplaceWithValue(node, value);
6736 return Replace(value);
6737 }
6738 Node* input = n.Argument(0);
6739 Node* value = graph()->NewNode(simplified()->ObjectIsFiniteNumber(), input);
6740 ReplaceWithValue(node, value);
6741 return Replace(value);
6742}

6785
6786Reduction JSCallReducer::ReduceMapPrototypeGet(Node* node) {
6787 // We only optimize if we have target, receiver and key parameters.
6788 JSCallNode n(node);
6789 if (n.ArgumentCount() != 1) return NoChange();
6790 Node* receiver = NodeProperties::GetValueInput(node, 1);
6791 Node* effect = NodeProperties::GetEffectInput(node);
6792 Node* control = NodeProperties::GetControlInput(node);
6793 Node* key = NodeProperties::GetValueInput(node, 2);
6794
6795 MapInference inference(broker(), receiver, effect);
6796 if (!inference.HaveMaps() || !inference.AllOfInstanceTypesAre(JS_MAP_TYPE)) {
6797 return NoChange();
6798 }
6799
6800 Node* table = effect = graph()->NewNode(
6801 simplified()->LoadField(AccessBuilder::ForJSCollectionTable()), receiver,
6802 effect, control);
6803
6804 Node* entry = effect = graph()->NewNode(
6805 simplified()->FindOrderedHashMapEntry(), table, key, effect, control);
6806
6807 Node* check = graph()->NewNode(simplified()->NumberEqual(), entry,
6808 jsgraph()->MinusOneConstant());
6809
6810 Node* branch = graph()->NewNode(common()->Branch(), check, control);
6811
6812 // Key not found.
6813 Node* if_true = graph()->NewNode(common()->IfTrue(), branch);
6814 Node* etrue = effect;
6815 Node* vtrue = jsgraph()->UndefinedConstant();
6816
6817 // Key found.
6818 Node* if_false = graph()->NewNode(common()->IfFalse(), branch);
6819 Node* efalse = effect;
6820 Node* vfalse = efalse = graph()->NewNode(
6821 simplified()->LoadElement(AccessBuilder::ForOrderedHashMapEntryValue()),
6822 table, entry, efalse, if_false);
6823
6824 control = graph()->NewNode(common()->Merge(2), if_true, if_false);
6825 Node* value = graph()->NewNode(
6826 common()->Phi(MachineRepresentation::kTagged, 2), vtrue, vfalse, control);
6827 effect = graph()->NewNode(common()->EffectPhi(2), etrue, efalse, control);
6828
6829 ReplaceWithValue(node, value, effect, control);
6830 return Replace(value);
6831}
6832
6833Reduction JSCallReducer::ReduceMapPrototypeHas(Node* node) {
6834 // We only optimize if we have target, receiver and key parameters.
6835 JSCallNode n(node);
6836 if (n.ArgumentCount() != 1) return NoChange();
6837 Node* receiver = NodeProperties::GetValueInput(node, 1);
6838 Node* effect = NodeProperties::GetEffectInput(node);
6839 Node* control = NodeProperties::GetControlInput(node);
6840 Node* key = NodeProperties::GetValueInput(node, 2);
6841
6842 MapInference inference(broker(), receiver, effect);
6843 if (!inference.HaveMaps() || !inference.AllOfInstanceTypesAre(JS_MAP_TYPE)) {
6844 return NoChange();
6845 }
6846
6847 Node* table = effect = graph()->NewNode(
6848 simplified()->LoadField(AccessBuilder::ForJSCollectionTable()), receiver,
6849 effect, control);
6850
6851 Node* index = effect = graph()->NewNode(
6852 simplified()->FindOrderedHashMapEntry(), table, key, effect, control);
6853
6854 Node* value = graph()->NewNode(simplified()->NumberEqual(), index,
6855 jsgraph()->MinusOneConstant());
6856 value = graph()->NewNode(simplified()->BooleanNot(), value);
6857
6858 ReplaceWithValue(node, value, effect, control);
6859 return Replace(value);
6860}

6864InstanceType InstanceTypeForCollectionKind(CollectionKind kind) {
6865 switch (kind) {
6866 case CollectionKind::kMap:
6867 return JS_MAP_TYPE;
6868 case CollectionKind::kSet:
6869 return JS_SET_TYPE;
6870 }
6871 UNREACHABLE()V8_Fatal("unreachable code");
6872}
