6876Reduction JSCallReducer::ReduceCollectionIteration(
6877 Node* node, CollectionKind collection_kind, IterationKind iteration_kind) {
6878 DCHECK_EQ(IrOpcode::kJSCall, node->opcode())((void) 0);
6879 Node* receiver = NodeProperties::GetValueInput(node, 1);
6880 Node* context = NodeProperties::GetContextInput(node);
6881 Node* effect = NodeProperties::GetEffectInput(node);
6882 Node* control = NodeProperties::GetControlInput(node);
6883
6884 InstanceType type = InstanceTypeForCollectionKind(collection_kind);
6885 MapInference inference(broker(), receiver, effect);
6886 if (!inference.HaveMaps() || !inference.AllOfInstanceTypesAre(type)) {
6887 return NoChange();
6888 }
6889
6890 Node* js_create_iterator = effect = graph()->NewNode(
6891 javascript()->CreateCollectionIterator(collection_kind, iteration_kind),
6892 receiver, context, effect, control);
6893 ReplaceWithValue(node, js_create_iterator, effect);
6894 return Replace(js_create_iterator);
6895}
6896
6897Reduction JSCallReducer::ReduceCollectionPrototypeSize(
6898 Node* node, CollectionKind collection_kind) {
6899 DCHECK_EQ(IrOpcode::kJSCall, node->opcode())((void) 0);
6900 Node* receiver = NodeProperties::GetValueInput(node, 1);
6901 Node* effect = NodeProperties::GetEffectInput(node);
6902 Node* control = NodeProperties::GetControlInput(node);
6903
6904 InstanceType type = InstanceTypeForCollectionKind(collection_kind);
6905 MapInference inference(broker(), receiver, effect);
6906 if (!inference.HaveMaps() || !inference.AllOfInstanceTypesAre(type)) {
6907 return NoChange();
6908 }
6909
6910 Node* table = effect = graph()->NewNode(
6911 simplified()->LoadField(AccessBuilder::ForJSCollectionTable()), receiver,
6912 effect, control);
6913 Node* value = effect = graph()->NewNode(
6914 simplified()->LoadField(
6915 AccessBuilder::ForOrderedHashMapOrSetNumberOfElements()),
6916 table, effect, control);
6917 ReplaceWithValue(node, value, effect, control);
6918 return Replace(value);
6919}
6920
6921Reduction JSCallReducer::ReduceCollectionIteratorPrototypeNext(
6922 Node* node, int entry_size, Handle<HeapObject> empty_collection,
6923 InstanceType collection_iterator_instance_type_first,
6924 InstanceType collection_iterator_instance_type_last) {
6925 JSCallNode n(node);
6926 CallParameters const& p = n.Parameters();
6927 if (p.speculation_mode() == SpeculationMode::kDisallowSpeculation) {
6928 return NoChange();
6929 }
6930
6931 Node* receiver = n.receiver();
6932 Node* context = n.context();
6933 Effect effect = n.effect();
6934 Control control = n.control();
6935
6936 // A word of warning to begin with: This whole method might look a bit
6937 // strange at times, but that's mostly because it was carefully handcrafted
6938 // to allow for full escape analysis and scalar replacement of both the
6939 // collection iterator object and the iterator results, including the
6940 // key-value arrays in case of Set/Map entry iteration.
6941 //
6942 // TODO(turbofan): Currently the escape analysis (and the store-load
6943 // forwarding) is unable to eliminate the allocations for the key-value
6944 // arrays in case of Set/Map entry iteration, and we should investigate
6945 // how to update the escape analysis / arrange the graph in a way that
6946 // this becomes possible.
6947
6948 InstanceType receiver_instance_type;
6949 {
6950 MapInference inference(broker(), receiver, effect);
6951 if (!inference.HaveMaps()) return NoChange();
6952 MapHandles const& receiver_maps = inference.GetMaps();
6953 receiver_instance_type = MapRef(broker(), receiver_maps[0]).instance_type();
6954 for (size_t i = 1; i < receiver_maps.size(); ++i) {
6955 if (MapRef(broker(), receiver_maps[i]).instance_type() !=
6956 receiver_instance_type) {
6957 return inference.NoChange();
6958 }
6959 }
6960 if (receiver_instance_type < collection_iterator_instance_type_first ||
6961 receiver_instance_type > collection_iterator_instance_type_last) {
6962 return inference.NoChange();
6963 }
6964 inference.RelyOnMapsPreferStability(dependencies(), jsgraph(), &effect,
6965 control, p.feedback());
6966 }
6967
6968 // Transition the JSCollectionIterator {receiver} if necessary
6969 // (i.e. there were certain mutations while we're iterating).
6970 {
6971 Node* done_loop;
6972 Node* done_eloop;
6973 Node* loop = control =
6974 graph()->NewNode(common()->Loop(2), control, control);
6975 Node* eloop = effect =
6976 graph()->NewNode(common()->EffectPhi(2), effect, effect, loop);
6977 Node* terminate = graph()->NewNode(common()->Terminate(), eloop, loop);
6978 NodeProperties::MergeControlToEnd(graph(), common(), terminate);
6979
6980 // Check if reached the final table of the {receiver}.
6981 Node* table = effect = graph()->NewNode(
6982 simplified()->LoadField(AccessBuilder::ForJSCollectionIteratorTable()),
6983 receiver, effect, control);
6984 Node* next_table = effect =
6985 graph()->NewNode(simplified()->LoadField(
6986 AccessBuilder::ForOrderedHashMapOrSetNextTable()),
6987 table, effect, control);
6988 Node* check = graph()->NewNode(simplified()->ObjectIsSmi(), next_table);
6989 control =
6990 graph()->NewNode(common()->Branch(BranchHint::kTrue), check, control);
6991
6992 // Abort the {loop} when we reach the final table.
6993 done_loop = graph()->NewNode(common()->IfTrue(), control);
6994 done_eloop = effect;
6995
6996 // Migrate to the {next_table} otherwise.
6997 control = graph()->NewNode(common()->IfFalse(), control);
6998
6999 // Self-heal the {receiver}s index.
7000 Node* index = effect = graph()->NewNode(
7001 simplified()->LoadField(AccessBuilder::ForJSCollectionIteratorIndex()),
7002 receiver, effect, control);
7003 Callable const callable =
7004 Builtins::CallableFor(isolate(), Builtins::kOrderedHashTableHealIndex);
7005 auto call_descriptor = Linkage::GetStubCallDescriptor(
7006 graph()->zone(), callable.descriptor(),
7007 callable.descriptor().GetStackParameterCount(),
7008 CallDescriptor::kNoFlags, Operator::kEliminatable);
7009 index = effect =
7010 graph()->NewNode(common()->Call(call_descriptor),
7011 jsgraph()->HeapConstant(callable.code()), table, index,
7012 jsgraph()->NoContextConstant(), effect);
7013
7014 index = effect = graph()->NewNode(
7015 common()->TypeGuard(TypeCache::Get()->kFixedArrayLengthType), index,
7016 effect, control);
7017
7018 // Update the {index} and {table} on the {receiver}.
7019 effect = graph()->NewNode(
7020 simplified()->StoreField(AccessBuilder::ForJSCollectionIteratorIndex()),
7021 receiver, index, effect, control);
7022 effect = graph()->NewNode(
7023 simplified()->StoreField(AccessBuilder::ForJSCollectionIteratorTable()),
7024 receiver, next_table, effect, control);
7025
7026 // Tie the knot.
7027 loop->ReplaceInput(1, control);
7028 eloop->ReplaceInput(1, effect);
7029
7030 control = done_loop;
7031 effect = done_eloop;
7032 }
7033
7034 // Get current index and table from the JSCollectionIterator {receiver}.
7035 Node* index = effect = graph()->NewNode(
7036 simplified()->LoadField(AccessBuilder::ForJSCollectionIteratorIndex()),
7037 receiver, effect, control);
7038 Node* table = effect = graph()->NewNode(
7039 simplified()->LoadField(AccessBuilder::ForJSCollectionIteratorTable()),
7040 receiver, effect, control);
7041
7042 // Create the {JSIteratorResult} first to ensure that we always have
7043 // a dominating Allocate node for the allocation folding phase.
7044 Node* iterator_result = effect = graph()->NewNode(
7045 javascript()->CreateIterResultObject(), jsgraph()->UndefinedConstant(),
7046 jsgraph()->TrueConstant(), context, effect);
7047
7048 // Look for the next non-holey key, starting from {index} in the {table}.
7049 Node* controls[2];
7050 Node* effects[3];
7051 {
7052 // Compute the currently used capacity.
7053 Node* number_of_buckets = effect = graph()->NewNode(
7054 simplified()->LoadField(
7055 AccessBuilder::ForOrderedHashMapOrSetNumberOfBuckets()),
7056 table, effect, control);
7057 Node* number_of_elements = effect = graph()->NewNode(
7058 simplified()->LoadField(
7059 AccessBuilder::ForOrderedHashMapOrSetNumberOfElements()),
7060 table, effect, control);
7061 Node* number_of_deleted_elements = effect = graph()->NewNode(
7062 simplified()->LoadField(
7063 AccessBuilder::ForOrderedHashMapOrSetNumberOfDeletedElements()),
7064 table, effect, control);
7065 Node* used_capacity =
7066 graph()->NewNode(simplified()->NumberAdd(), number_of_elements,
7067 number_of_deleted_elements);
7068
7069 // Skip holes and update the {index}.
7070 Node* loop = graph()->NewNode(common()->Loop(2), control, control);
7071 Node* eloop =
7072 graph()->NewNode(common()->EffectPhi(2), effect, effect, loop);
7073 Node* terminate = graph()->NewNode(common()->Terminate(), eloop, loop);
7074 NodeProperties::MergeControlToEnd(graph(), common(), terminate);
7075 Node* iloop = graph()->NewNode(
7076 common()->Phi(MachineRepresentation::kTagged, 2), index, index, loop);
7077
7078 Node* index = effect = graph()->NewNode(
7079 common()->TypeGuard(TypeCache::Get()->kFixedArrayLengthType), iloop,
7080 eloop, control);
7081 {
7082 Node* check0 = graph()->NewNode(simplified()->NumberLessThan(), index,
7083 used_capacity);
7084 Node* branch0 =
7085 graph()->NewNode(common()->Branch(BranchHint::kTrue), check0, loop);
7086
7087 Node* if_false0 = graph()->NewNode(common()->IfFalse(), branch0);
7088 Node* efalse0 = effect;
7089 {
7090 // Mark the {receiver} as exhausted.
7091 efalse0 = graph()->NewNode(
7092 simplified()->StoreField(
7093 AccessBuilder::ForJSCollectionIteratorTable()),
7094 receiver, jsgraph()->HeapConstant(empty_collection), efalse0,
7095 if_false0);
7096
7097 controls[0] = if_false0;
7098 effects[0] = efalse0;
7099 }
7100
7101 Node* if_true0 = graph()->NewNode(common()->IfTrue(), branch0);
7102 Node* etrue0 = effect;
7103 {
7104 // Load the key of the entry.
7105 STATIC_ASSERT(OrderedHashMap::HashTableStartIndex() ==static_assert(OrderedHashMap::HashTableStartIndex() == OrderedHashSet
::HashTableStartIndex(), "OrderedHashMap::HashTableStartIndex() == OrderedHashSet::HashTableStartIndex()"
)
7106 OrderedHashSet::HashTableStartIndex())static_assert(OrderedHashMap::HashTableStartIndex() == OrderedHashSet
::HashTableStartIndex(), "OrderedHashMap::HashTableStartIndex() == OrderedHashSet::HashTableStartIndex()"
);
7107 Node* entry_start_position = graph()->NewNode(
7108 simplified()->NumberAdd(),
7109 graph()->NewNode(
7110 simplified()->NumberAdd(),
7111 graph()->NewNode(simplified()->NumberMultiply(), index,
7112 jsgraph()->Constant(entry_size)),
7113 number_of_buckets),
7114 jsgraph()->Constant(OrderedHashMap::HashTableStartIndex()));
7115 Node* entry_key = etrue0 = graph()->NewNode(
7116 simplified()->LoadElement(AccessBuilder::ForFixedArrayElement()),
7117 table, entry_start_position, etrue0, if_true0);
7118
7119 // Advance the index.
7120 index = graph()->NewNode(simplified()->NumberAdd(), index,
7121 jsgraph()->OneConstant());
7122
7123 Node* check1 =
7124 graph()->NewNode(simplified()->ReferenceEqual(), entry_key,
7125 jsgraph()->TheHoleConstant());
7126 Node* branch1 = graph()->NewNode(common()->Branch(BranchHint::kFalse),
7127 check1, if_true0);
7128
7129 {
7130 // Abort loop with resulting value.
7131 Node* control = graph()->NewNode(common()->IfFalse(), branch1);
7132 Node* effect = etrue0;
7133 Node* value = effect =
7134 graph()->NewNode(common()->TypeGuard(Type::NonInternal()),
7135 entry_key, effect, control);
7136 Node* done = jsgraph()->FalseConstant();
7137
7138 // Advance the index on the {receiver}.
7139 effect = graph()->NewNode(
7140 simplified()->StoreField(
7141 AccessBuilder::ForJSCollectionIteratorIndex()),
7142 receiver, index, effect, control);
7143
7144 // The actual {value} depends on the {receiver} iteration type.
7145 switch (receiver_instance_type) {
7146 case JS_MAP_KEY_ITERATOR_TYPE:
7147 case JS_SET_VALUE_ITERATOR_TYPE:
7148 break;
7149
7150 case JS_SET_KEY_VALUE_ITERATOR_TYPE:
7151 value = effect =
7152 graph()->NewNode(javascript()->CreateKeyValueArray(), value,
7153 value, context, effect);
7154 break;
7155
7156 case JS_MAP_VALUE_ITERATOR_TYPE:
7157 value = effect = graph()->NewNode(
7158 simplified()->LoadElement(
7159 AccessBuilder::ForFixedArrayElement()),
7160 table,
7161 graph()->NewNode(
7162 simplified()->NumberAdd(), entry_start_position,
7163 jsgraph()->Constant(OrderedHashMap::kValueOffset)),
7164 effect, control);
7165 break;
7166
7167 case JS_MAP_KEY_VALUE_ITERATOR_TYPE:
7168 value = effect = graph()->NewNode(
7169 simplified()->LoadElement(
7170 AccessBuilder::ForFixedArrayElement()),
7171 table,
7172 graph()->NewNode(
7173 simplified()->NumberAdd(), entry_start_position,
7174 jsgraph()->Constant(OrderedHashMap::kValueOffset)),
7175 effect, control);
7176 value = effect =
7177 graph()->NewNode(javascript()->CreateKeyValueArray(),
7178 entry_key, value, context, effect);
7179 break;
7180
7181 default:
7182 UNREACHABLE()V8_Fatal("unreachable code");
7183 break;
7184 }
7185
7186 // Store final {value} and {done} into the {iterator_result}.
7187 effect =
7188 graph()->NewNode(simplified()->StoreField(
7189 AccessBuilder::ForJSIteratorResultValue()),
7190 iterator_result, value, effect, control);
7191 effect =
7192 graph()->NewNode(simplified()->StoreField(
7193 AccessBuilder::ForJSIteratorResultDone()),
7194 iterator_result, done, effect, control);
7195
7196 controls[1] = control;
7197 effects[1] = effect;
7198 }
7199
7200 // Continue with next loop index.
7201 loop->ReplaceInput(1, graph()->NewNode(common()->IfTrue(), branch1));
7202 eloop->ReplaceInput(1, etrue0);
7203 iloop->ReplaceInput(1, index);
7204 }
7205 }
7206
7207 control = effects[2] = graph()->NewNode(common()->Merge(2), 2, controls);
7208 effect = graph()->NewNode(common()->EffectPhi(2), 3, effects);
7209 }
7210
7211 // Yield the final {iterator_result}.
7212 ReplaceWithValue(node, iterator_result, effect, control);
7213 return Replace(iterator_result);
7214}
7215
7216Reduction JSCallReducer::ReduceArrayBufferIsView(Node* node) {
7217 DisallowHeapAccessIf disallow_heap_access(should_disallow_heap_access());
7218
7219 JSCallNode n(node);
7220 Node* value = n.ArgumentOrUndefined(0, jsgraph());
7221 RelaxEffectsAndControls(node);
7222 node->ReplaceInput(0, value);
7223 node->TrimInputCount(1);
7224 NodeProperties::ChangeOp(node, simplified()->ObjectIsArrayBufferView());
7225 return Changed(node);
7226}
7227
7228Reduction JSCallReducer::ReduceArrayBufferViewAccessor(
7229 Node* node, InstanceType instance_type, FieldAccess const& access) {
7230 DisallowHeapAccessIf disallow_heap_access(should_disallow_heap_access());
7231
7232 Node* receiver = NodeProperties::GetValueInput(node, 1);
7233 Node* effect = NodeProperties::GetEffectInput(node);
7234 Node* control = NodeProperties::GetControlInput(node);
7235
7236 MapInference inference(broker(), receiver, effect);
7237 if (!inference.HaveMaps() ||
7238 !inference.AllOfInstanceTypesAre(instance_type)) {
7239 return NoChange();
7240 }
7241
7242 // Load the {receiver}s field.
7243 Node* value = effect = graph()->NewNode(simplified()->LoadField(access),
7244 receiver, effect, control);
7245
7246 // See if we can skip the detaching check.
7247 if (!dependencies()->DependOnArrayBufferDetachingProtector()) {
7248 // Check whether {receiver}s JSArrayBuffer was detached.
7249 Node* buffer = effect = graph()->NewNode(
7250 simplified()->LoadField(AccessBuilder::ForJSArrayBufferViewBuffer()),
7251 receiver, effect, control);
7252 Node* buffer_bit_field = effect = graph()->NewNode(
7253 simplified()->LoadField(AccessBuilder::ForJSArrayBufferBitField()),
7254 buffer, effect, control);
7255 Node* check = graph()->NewNode(
7256 simplified()->NumberEqual(),
7257 graph()->NewNode(
7258 simplified()->NumberBitwiseAnd(), buffer_bit_field,
7259 jsgraph()->Constant(JSArrayBuffer::WasDetachedBit::kMask)),
7260 jsgraph()->ZeroConstant());
7261
7262 // TODO(turbofan): Ideally we would bail out here if the {receiver}s
7263 // JSArrayBuffer was detached, but there's no way to guard against
7264 // deoptimization loops right now, since the JSCall {node} is usually
7265 // created from a LOAD_IC inlining, and so there's no CALL_IC slot
7266 // from which we could use the speculation bit.
7267 value = graph()->NewNode(
7268 common()->Select(MachineRepresentation::kTagged, BranchHint::kTrue),
7269 check, value, jsgraph()->ZeroConstant());
7270 }
7271
7272 ReplaceWithValue(node, value, effect, control);
7273 return Replace(value);
7274}
7275
7276namespace {
7277uint32_t ExternalArrayElementSize(const ExternalArrayType element_type) {
7278 switch (element_type) {
7279#define TYPED_ARRAY_CASE(Type, type, TYPE, ctype) \
7280 case kExternal##Type##Array: \
7281 DCHECK_LE(sizeof(ctype), 8)((void) 0); \
7282 return sizeof(ctype);
7283 TYPED_ARRAYS(TYPED_ARRAY_CASE)TYPED_ARRAY_CASE(Uint8, uint8, UINT8, uint8_t) TYPED_ARRAY_CASE
(Int8, int8, INT8, int8_t) TYPED_ARRAY_CASE(Uint16, uint16, UINT16
, uint16_t) TYPED_ARRAY_CASE(Int16, int16, INT16, int16_t) TYPED_ARRAY_CASE
(Uint32, uint32, UINT32, uint32_t) TYPED_ARRAY_CASE(Int32, int32
, INT32, int32_t) TYPED_ARRAY_CASE(Float32, float32, FLOAT32,
float) TYPED_ARRAY_CASE(Float64, float64, FLOAT64, double) TYPED_ARRAY_CASE
(Uint8Clamped, uint8_clamped, UINT8_CLAMPED, uint8_t) TYPED_ARRAY_CASE
(BigUint64, biguint64, BIGUINT64, uint64_t) TYPED_ARRAY_CASE(
BigInt64, bigint64, BIGINT64, int64_t)
7284 default:
7285 UNREACHABLE()V8_Fatal("unreachable code");
7286#undef TYPED_ARRAY_CASE
7287 }
7288}
7289} // namespace
7290
7291Reduction JSCallReducer::ReduceDataViewAccess(Node* node, DataViewAccess access,
7292 ExternalArrayType element_type) {
7293 JSCallNode n(node);
7294 CallParameters const& p = n.Parameters();
7295 size_t const element_size = ExternalArrayElementSize(element_type);
7296 Effect effect = n.effect();
7297 Control control = n.control();
7298 Node* receiver = n.receiver();
7299 Node* offset = n.ArgumentOr(0, jsgraph()->ZeroConstant());
7300 Node* value = nullptr;
7301 if (access == DataViewAccess::kSet) {
7302 value = n.ArgumentOrUndefined(1, jsgraph());
7303 }
7304 const int endian_index = (access == DataViewAccess::kGet ? 1 : 2);
7305 Node* is_little_endian =
7306 n.ArgumentOr(endian_index, jsgraph()->FalseConstant());
7307
7308 if (p.speculation_mode() == SpeculationMode::kDisallowSpeculation) {
7309 return NoChange();
7310 }
7311
7312 // Only do stuff if the {receiver} is really a DataView.
7313 MapInference inference(broker(), receiver, effect);
7314 if (!inference.HaveMaps() ||
7315 !inference.AllOfInstanceTypesAre(JS_DATA_VIEW_TYPE)) {
7316 return NoChange();
7317 }
7318
7319 // Check that the {offset} is within range for the {receiver}.
7320 HeapObjectMatcher m(receiver);
7321 if (m.HasValue()) {
7322 // We only deal with DataViews here whose [[ByteLength]] is at least
7323 // {element_size}, as for all other DataViews it'll be out-of-bounds.
7324 JSDataViewRef dataview = m.Ref(broker()).AsJSDataView();
7325 if (dataview.byte_length() < element_size) return NoChange();
7326
7327 // Check that the {offset} is within range of the {byte_length}.
7328 Node* byte_length =
7329 jsgraph()->Constant(dataview.byte_length() - (element_size - 1));
7330 offset = effect = graph()->NewNode(simplified()->CheckBounds(p.feedback()),
7331 offset, byte_length, effect, control);
7332 } else {
7333 // We only deal with DataViews here that have Smi [[ByteLength]]s.
7334 Node* byte_length = effect =
7335 graph()->NewNode(simplified()->LoadField(
7336 AccessBuilder::ForJSArrayBufferViewByteLength()),
7337 receiver, effect, control);
7338
7339 if (element_size > 1) {
7340 // For non-byte accesses we also need to check that the {offset}
7341 // plus the {element_size}-1 fits within the given {byte_length}.
7342 // So to keep this as a single check on the {offset}, we subtract
7343 // the {element_size}-1 from the {byte_length} here (clamped to
7344 // positive safe integer range), and perform a check against that
7345 // with the {offset} below.
7346 byte_length = graph()->NewNode(
7347 simplified()->NumberMax(), jsgraph()->ZeroConstant(),
7348 graph()->NewNode(simplified()->NumberSubtract(), byte_length,
7349 jsgraph()->Constant(element_size - 1)));
7350 }
7351
7352 // Check that the {offset} is within range of the {byte_length}.
7353 offset = effect = graph()->NewNode(simplified()->CheckBounds(p.feedback()),
7354 offset, byte_length, effect, control);
7355 }
7356
7357 // Coerce {is_little_endian} to boolean.
7358 is_little_endian =
7359 graph()->NewNode(simplified()->ToBoolean(), is_little_endian);
7360
7361 // Coerce {value} to Number.
7362 if (access == DataViewAccess::kSet) {
7363 value = effect = graph()->NewNode(
7364 simplified()->SpeculativeToNumber(NumberOperationHint::kNumberOrOddball,
7365 p.feedback()),
7366 value, effect, control);
7367 }
7368
7369 // We need to retain either the {receiver} itself or it's backing
7370 // JSArrayBuffer to make sure that the GC doesn't collect the raw
7371 // memory. We default to {receiver} here, and only use the buffer
7372 // if we anyways have to load it (to reduce register pressure).
7373 Node* buffer_or_receiver = receiver;
7374
7375 if (!dependencies()->DependOnArrayBufferDetachingProtector()) {
7376 // Get the underlying buffer and check that it has not been detached.
7377 Node* buffer = effect = graph()->NewNode(
7378 simplified()->LoadField(AccessBuilder::ForJSArrayBufferViewBuffer()),
7379 receiver, effect, control);
7380
7381 // Bail out if the {buffer} was detached.
7382 Node* buffer_bit_field = effect = graph()->NewNode(
7383 simplified()->LoadField(AccessBuilder::ForJSArrayBufferBitField()),
7384 buffer, effect, control);
7385 Node* check = graph()->NewNode(
7386 simplified()->NumberEqual(),
7387 graph()->NewNode(
7388 simplified()->NumberBitwiseAnd(), buffer_bit_field,
7389 jsgraph()->Constant(JSArrayBuffer::WasDetachedBit::kMask)),
7390 jsgraph()->ZeroConstant());
7391 effect = graph()->NewNode(
7392 simplified()->CheckIf(DeoptimizeReason::kArrayBufferWasDetached,
7393 p.feedback()),
7394 check, effect, control);
7395
7396 // We can reduce register pressure by holding on to the {buffer}
7397 // now to retain the backing store memory.
7398 buffer_or_receiver = buffer;
7399 }
7400
7401 // Load the {receiver}s data pointer.
7402 Node* data_pointer = effect = graph()->NewNode(
7403 simplified()->LoadField(AccessBuilder::ForJSDataViewDataPointer()),
7404 receiver, effect, control);
7405
7406 switch (access) {
7407 case DataViewAccess::kGet:
7408 // Perform the load.
7409 value = effect = graph()->NewNode(
7410 simplified()->LoadDataViewElement(element_type), buffer_or_receiver,
7411 data_pointer, offset, is_little_endian, effect, control);
7412 break;
7413 case DataViewAccess::kSet:
7414 // Perform the store.
7415 effect = graph()->NewNode(
7416 simplified()->StoreDataViewElement(element_type), buffer_or_receiver,
7417 data_pointer, offset, value, is_little_endian, effect, control);
7418 value = jsgraph()->UndefinedConstant();
7419 break;
7420 }
7421
7422 ReplaceWithValue(node, value, effect, control);
7423 return Changed(value);
7424}

7426// ES6 section 18.2.2 isFinite ( number )
7427Reduction JSCallReducer::ReduceGlobalIsFinite(Node* node) {
7428 JSCallNode n(node);
7429 CallParameters const& p = n.Parameters();
7430 if (p.speculation_mode() == SpeculationMode::kDisallowSpeculation) {
7431 return NoChange();
7432 }
7433 if (n.ArgumentCount() < 1) {
7434 Node* value = jsgraph()->FalseConstant();
7435 ReplaceWithValue(node, value);
7436 return Replace(value);
7437 }
7438
7439 Effect effect = n.effect();
7440 Control control = n.control();
7441 Node* input = n.Argument(0);
7442
7443 input = effect =
7444 graph()->NewNode(simplified()->SpeculativeToNumber(
7445 NumberOperationHint::kNumberOrOddball, p.feedback()),
7446 input, effect, control);
7447 Node* value = graph()->NewNode(simplified()->NumberIsFinite(), input);
7448 ReplaceWithValue(node, value, effect);
7449 return Replace(value);
7450}

7452// ES6 section 18.2.3 isNaN ( number )
7453Reduction JSCallReducer::ReduceGlobalIsNaN(Node* node) {
7454 JSCallNode n(node);
7455 CallParameters const& p = n.Parameters();
7456 if (p.speculation_mode() == SpeculationMode::kDisallowSpeculation) {
7457 return NoChange();
7458 }
7459 if (n.ArgumentCount() < 1) {
7460 Node* value = jsgraph()->TrueConstant();
7461 ReplaceWithValue(node, value);
7462 return Replace(value);
7463 }
7464
7465 Effect effect = n.effect();
7466 Control control = n.control();
7467 Node* input = n.Argument(0);
7468
7469 input = effect =
7470 graph()->NewNode(simplified()->SpeculativeToNumber(
7471 NumberOperationHint::kNumberOrOddball, p.feedback()),
7472 input, effect, control);
7473 Node* value = graph()->NewNode(simplified()->NumberIsNaN(), input);
7474 ReplaceWithValue(node, value, effect);
7475 return Replace(value);
7476}

7478// ES6 section 20.3.4.10 Date.prototype.getTime ( )
7479Reduction JSCallReducer::ReduceDatePrototypeGetTime(Node* node) {
7480 Node* receiver = NodeProperties::GetValueInput(node, 1);
7481 Node* effect = NodeProperties::GetEffectInput(node);
7482 Node* control = NodeProperties::GetControlInput(node);
7483
7484 MapInference inference(broker(), receiver, effect);
7485 if (!inference.HaveMaps() || !inference.AllOfInstanceTypesAre(JS_DATE_TYPE)) {
7486 return NoChange();
7487 }
7488
7489 Node* value = effect =
7490 graph()->NewNode(simplified()->LoadField(AccessBuilder::ForJSDateValue()),
7491 receiver, effect, control);
7492 ReplaceWithValue(node, value, effect, control);
7493 return Replace(value);
7494}

7496// ES6 section 20.3.3.1 Date.now ( )
7497Reduction JSCallReducer::ReduceDateNow(Node* node) {
7498 Node* effect = NodeProperties::GetEffectInput(node);
7499 Node* control = NodeProperties::GetControlInput(node);
7500 Node* value = effect =
7501 graph()->NewNode(simplified()->DateNow(), effect, control);
7502 ReplaceWithValue(node, value, effect, control);
7503 return Replace(value);
7504}
7505
7506// ES6 section 20.1.2.13 Number.parseInt ( string, radix )
7507Reduction JSCallReducer::ReduceNumberParseInt(Node* node) {
7508 JSCallNode n(node);
7509 if (n.ArgumentCount() < 1) {
7510 Node* value = jsgraph()->NaNConstant();
7511 ReplaceWithValue(node, value);
7512 return Replace(value);
7513 }
7514
7515 Effect effect = n.effect();
7516 Control control = n.control();
7517 Node* context = n.context();
7518 FrameState frame_state = n.frame_state();
7519 Node* object = n.Argument(0);
7520 Node* radix = n.ArgumentOrUndefined(1, jsgraph());
7521 node->ReplaceInput(0, object);
7522 node->ReplaceInput(1, radix);
7523 node->ReplaceInput(2, context);
7524 node->ReplaceInput(3, frame_state);
7525 node->ReplaceInput(4, effect);
7526 node->ReplaceInput(5, control);
7527 node->TrimInputCount(6);
7528 NodeProperties::ChangeOp(node, javascript()->ParseInt());
7529 return Changed(node);
7530}
7531
7532Reduction JSCallReducer::ReduceRegExpPrototypeTest(Node* node) {
7533 DisallowHeapAccessIf disallow_heap_access(should_disallow_heap_access());
7534
7535 JSCallNode n(node);
7536 CallParameters const& p = n.Parameters();
7537 if (FLAG_force_slow_path) return NoChange();
7538 if (n.ArgumentCount() < 1) return NoChange();
7539
7540 if (p.speculation_mode() == SpeculationMode::kDisallowSpeculation) {
7541 return NoChange();
7542 }
7543
7544 Effect effect = n.effect();
7545 Control control = n.control();
7546 Node* regexp = n.receiver();
7547
7548 // Only the initial JSRegExp map is valid here, since the following lastIndex
7549 // check as well as the lowered builtin call rely on a known location of the
7550 // lastIndex field.
7551 Handle<Map> regexp_initial_map =
7552 native_context().regexp_function().initial_map().object();
7553
7554 MapInference inference(broker(), regexp, effect);
7555 if (!inference.Is(regexp_initial_map)) return inference.NoChange();
7556 MapHandles const& regexp_maps = inference.GetMaps();
7557
7558 ZoneVector<PropertyAccessInfo> access_infos(graph()->zone());
7559 AccessInfoFactory access_info_factory(broker(), dependencies(),
7560 graph()->zone());
7561 if (should_disallow_heap_access()) {
7562 // Obtain precomputed access infos from the broker.
7563 for (auto map : regexp_maps) {
7564 MapRef map_ref(broker(), map);
7565 PropertyAccessInfo access_info = broker()->GetPropertyAccessInfo(
7566 map_ref, NameRef(broker(), isolate()->factory()->exec_string()),
7567 AccessMode::kLoad);
7568 access_infos.push_back(access_info);
7569 }
7570 } else {
7571 // Compute property access info for "exec" on {resolution}.
7572 access_info_factory.ComputePropertyAccessInfos(
7573 MapHandles(regexp_maps.begin(), regexp_maps.end()),
7574 factory()->exec_string(), AccessMode::kLoad, &access_infos);
7575 }
7576
7577 PropertyAccessInfo ai_exec =
7578 access_info_factory.FinalizePropertyAccessInfosAsOne(access_infos,
7579 AccessMode::kLoad);
7580 if (ai_exec.IsInvalid()) return inference.NoChange();
7581
7582 // If "exec" has been modified on {regexp}, we can't do anything.
7583 if (ai_exec.IsDataConstant()) {
7584 Handle<JSObject> holder;
7585 // Do not reduce if the exec method is not on the prototype chain.
7586 if (!ai_exec.holder().ToHandle(&holder)) return inference.NoChange();
7587
7588 JSObjectRef holder_ref(broker(), holder);
7589
7590 // Bail out if the exec method is not the original one.
7591 base::Optional<ObjectRef> constant = holder_ref.GetOwnDataProperty(
7592 ai_exec.field_representation(), ai_exec.field_index());
7593 if (!constant.has_value() ||
7594 !constant->equals(native_context().regexp_exec_function())) {
7595 return inference.NoChange();
7596 }
7597
7598 // Add proper dependencies on the {regexp}s [[Prototype]]s.
7599 dependencies()->DependOnStablePrototypeChains(
7600 ai_exec.receiver_maps(), kStartAtPrototype,
7601 JSObjectRef(broker(), holder));
7602 } else {
7603 return inference.NoChange();
7604 }
7605
7606 inference.RelyOnMapsPreferStability(dependencies(), jsgraph(), &effect,
7607 control, p.feedback());
7608
7609 Node* context = n.context();
7610 FrameState frame_state = n.frame_state();
7611 Node* search = n.Argument(0);
7612 Node* search_string = effect = graph()->NewNode(
7613 simplified()->CheckString(p.feedback()), search, effect, control);
7614
7615 Node* lastIndex = effect = graph()->NewNode(
7616 simplified()->LoadField(AccessBuilder::ForJSRegExpLastIndex()), regexp,
7617 effect, control);
7618
7619 Node* lastIndexSmi = effect = graph()->NewNode(
7620 simplified()->CheckSmi(p.feedback()), lastIndex, effect, control);
7621
7622 Node* is_positive = graph()->NewNode(simplified()->NumberLessThanOrEqual(),
7623 jsgraph()->ZeroConstant(), lastIndexSmi);
7624
7625 effect = graph()->NewNode(
7626 simplified()->CheckIf(DeoptimizeReason::kNotASmi, p.feedback()),
7627 is_positive, effect, control);
7628
7629 node->ReplaceInput(0, regexp);
7630 node->ReplaceInput(1, search_string);
7631 node->ReplaceInput(2, context);
7632 node->ReplaceInput(3, frame_state);
7633 node->ReplaceInput(4, effect);
7634 node->ReplaceInput(5, control);
7635 node->TrimInputCount(6);
7636 NodeProperties::ChangeOp(node, javascript()->RegExpTest());
7637 return Changed(node);
7638}
7639
7640// ES section #sec-number-constructor
7641Reduction JSCallReducer::ReduceNumberConstructor(Node* node) {
7642 JSCallNode n(node);
7643 Node* target = n.target();
7644 Node* receiver = n.receiver();
7645 Node* value = n.ArgumentOr(0, jsgraph()->ZeroConstant());
7646 Node* context = n.context();
7647 FrameState frame_state = n.frame_state();
7648
7649 // Create the artificial frame state in the middle of the Number constructor.
7650 SharedFunctionInfoRef shared_info =
7651 native_context().number_function().shared();
7652 Node* stack_parameters[] = {receiver};
7653 int stack_parameter_count = arraysize(stack_parameters)(sizeof(ArraySizeHelper(stack_parameters)));
7654 Node* continuation_frame_state =
7655 CreateJavaScriptBuiltinContinuationFrameState(
7656 jsgraph(), shared_info, Builtins::kGenericLazyDeoptContinuation,
7657 target, context, stack_parameters, stack_parameter_count, frame_state,
7658 ContinuationFrameStateMode::LAZY);
7659
7660 // Convert the {value} to a Number.
7661 NodeProperties::ReplaceValueInputs(node, value);
7662 NodeProperties::ChangeOp(node, javascript()->ToNumberConvertBigInt());
7663 NodeProperties::ReplaceFrameStateInput(node, continuation_frame_state);
7664 return Changed(node);
7665}
7666
7667Reduction JSCallReducer::ReduceBigIntAsUintN(Node* node) {
7668 if (!jsgraph()->machine()->Is64()) return NoChange();
7669
7670 JSCallNode n(node);
7671 CallParameters const& p = n.Parameters();
7672 if (p.speculation_mode() == SpeculationMode::kDisallowSpeculation) {
7673 return NoChange();
7674 }
7675 if (n.ArgumentCount() < 2) {
7676 return NoChange();
7677 }
7678
7679 Effect effect = n.effect();
7680 Control control = n.control();
7681 Node* bits = n.Argument(0);
7682 Node* value = n.Argument(1);
7683
7684 NumberMatcher matcher(bits);
7685 if (matcher.IsInteger() && matcher.IsInRange(0, 64)) {
7686 const int bits_value = static_cast<int>(matcher.Value());
7687 value = effect = graph()->NewNode(simplified()->CheckBigInt(p.feedback()),
7688 value, effect, control);
7689 value = graph()->NewNode(simplified()->BigIntAsUintN(bits_value), value);
7690 ReplaceWithValue(node, value, effect);
7691 return Replace(value);
7692 }
7693
7694 return NoChange();
7695}
